name: Organic compounds
description: Compounds that contain at least carbon atom, excluding isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon trioxide, Carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.

name: Organoheterocyclic compounds
description: Compounds containing a ring with least one carbon atom and one non-carbon atom.

name: Thiepanes
description: Organic compounds containing a heptane ring in which one carbon atom is replaced by a sulfur atom.

name: Organosulfur compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a carbon-sulfur bond.

name: Benzoxazolines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an oxazoline ring. Oxazoline is five-membered unsaturated ring with a nitrogen atom and an oxygen atom at the 1- and 3-position, respectively. Additionally, it contains two double bonds.

name: Amidines
description: Derivatives of oxoacids RnE(=O)OH in which the hydroxy group is replaced by an amino group and the oxo group is replaced by =NR. Amidines include carboxamidines, sulfinamidines and phosphinamidines.

name: Cembrane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based a cembrane skeleton, which is characterized by the presence of an isopropyl group at C-1 and by three symmetrically disposed methyl groups a the t C-4, -8 and -12 positions.

name: Carbohydrates and carbohydrate conjugates
description: Monosaccharides, disaccharides, oligosaccharides, polysaccharides, and their derivatives.

name: Lipids and lipid-like molecules
description: Fatty acids and their derivatives, and substances related biosynthetically or functionally to these compounds.

name: Amino acids, peptides, and analogues
description: Organic compounds containing an amino acid or a peptide backbone, or derivatives thereof.

name: Phenylbutylamines
description: Compounds containing a phenylbutylamine moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the fourth carbon by an butan-1-amine.

name: Dibenzofurans
description: Compounds containing a dibenzofuran moiety, which consists of two benzene rings fused to a central furan ring.

name: Allenes
description: Compounds in which one carbon atom has double bonds with each of its two adjacent carbon centers. The definition includes both the hydrocarbon molecules and their derivatives obtained by substitution.

name: Cycloalkenes
description: Unsaturated monocyclic hydrocarbons having one endocyclic double bond.

name: Anthracenes
description: Organic compounds containing a system of three linearly fused benzene rings.

name: Dibenzocycloheptenes
description: Compounds containing a dibenzocycloheptene moiety, which consists of two benzene rings connected by a cycloheptene ring.

name: Fluorenes
description: Compounds containing a fluorene moiety, which consists of two benzene rings connected through either a cyclopentane, cyclopentene, or cyclopenta-1,3-diene.

name: Indenes and isoindenes
description: Compounds containing an indene moiety(which consists of a cyclopentadiene fused to a benzene ring), or a isoindene moiety (which consists of a cyclopentadiene fused to cyclohexadiene ring).

name: Naphthacenes
description: Compounds containing a naphthacene moiety, which is a polyaromatic hydrocarbon made of four linearly fused benzene rings.

name: Naphthalenes
description: Compounds containing a naphthalene moiety, which consists of two fused benzene rings.

name: Pentacenes
description: Compounds containing a pentacene moiety, which is consists of five linearly fused benzene rings.

name: Phenanthrenes and derivatives
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a phenanthrene moiety, which is a tricyclic aromatic compound with three non-linearly fused benzene.

name: Purine ribonucleoside bisphosphates
description: Purine Ribonucleotides in which the ribose sugar esterified with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxy groups on the sugar, usually at positions 2', 3', or 5'.

name: Indanes
description: Compounds containing an indane moiety, which consists of a cyclopentane fused to a benzene ring.

name: Cinnamaldehydes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a cinnamlaldehyde moiety, consisting of a benzene and an aldehyde group to form 3-phenylprop-2-enal.

name: Hydroxyeicosatrienoic acids
description: Eicosanoic acids with an attached hydroxyl group and three CC double bonds.

name: Benzenesulfonamides
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfonamide group that is S-linked to a benzene ring.

name: Benzenesulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfonic acid or a derivative thereof that is linked to a benzene ring.

name: Benzyl alcohols
description: Organic compounds containing the phenylmethanol substructure.

name: Sulfobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids carrying a sulfonyl group on the benzene ring.

name: Halobenzenes
description: Aromatic compounds containing a halogen atom linked to a benzene ring.

name: Nitrobenzenes
description: Compounds containing a nitrobenzene moiety, which consists of a benzene ring with a carbon bearing a nitro group.

name: Styrenes
description: Organic compounds containing an ethenylbenzene moiety.

name: Sulfanilides
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a sulfanilide moiety, with the general structure RS(=O)(=O)NC1=CC=CC=C1.

name: Sulfamic acid derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfamic acid moiety or a derivative, with the general structure R1N(R2)S(=O)2OR3  (R1,R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Indanediones
description: Compounds containing an indane ring bearing two ketone groups.

name: Biphenyls and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing to benzene rings linked together by a C-C bond.

name: Biphenylbenzimidazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a biphenyl attached to a benzimidazole. A carbon atom of the biphenyl moiety is boned to a carbon or the nitrogen atom of the benzimidazole moiety.

name: Phenylpropenes
description: Compounds containing a phenylpropene moiety, which consists of a propene substituent bound to a phenyl group.

name: Hydroxyeicosatetraenoic acids
description: Eicosanoic acids with an attached hydroxyl group and four CC double bonds.

name: Podophyllotoxins
description: Tetralin lignans in which the benzene moiety of the tetralin skeleton is fused to a 1,3-dioxolane and the cyclohexane is fused to a butyrolactone (pyrrolidin-2-one).

name: Tetralins
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a tetralin moiety, which consists of a benzene fused to a cyclohexane.

name: Tametralines
description: Compounds containing a tametraline moiety, which consists of a tetrahydronaphthalene linked to a phenyl group to form N-methyl-4-phenyl-1,2,3,4-tetrahydronaphthalen-1-amine skeleton.

name: Lactones
description: Cyclic esters of hydroxy carboxylic acids, containing a 1-oxacycloalkan-2-one structure, or analogues having unsaturation or heteroatoms replacing one or more carbon atoms of the ring.

name: Aromatic monoterpenoids
description: Monoterpenoids containing at least one aromatic ring.

name: Brominated biphenyls
description: Organic compounds containing a biphenyl moiety substituted at one or more positions by a bromine atom.

name: Aminoquinolines and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a quinoline ring system.

name: Benzylisoquinolines
description: Organic compounds containing an isoquinoline to which a benzyl group is attached.

name: Dibenzothiazepines
description: Compounds containing a dibenzothiazepine moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by a thiazepine ring.

name: Quinolones and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety which bears a ketone group.

name: Hydroxyquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety bearing a hydroxyl group.

name: Morphinans
description: Polycyclic compounds with a four-ring skeleton with three condensed six-member rings forming a partially hydrogenated phenanthrene moiety, one of which is aromatic while the two others are alicyclic.

name: Coumaric acids and derivatives
description: Aromatic compounds containing Aromatic compounds containing a cinnamic acid moiety (or a derivative thereof) hydroxylated at the C2 (ortho-), C3 (meta-), or C4 (para-) carbon atom of the benzene ring.

name: Alpha amino acids and derivatives
description: Amino acids in which the amino group is attached to the carbon atom immediately adjacent to the carboxylate group (alpha carbon), or a derivative thereof.

name: Indoloquinolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing an indole fused to a quinoline.

name: 2-sulfobenzoic acids
description: Sulfobenzoic acid carrying the sulfonyl group at the 2-position of the benzene group.

name: Macrolactams
description: Cyclic amides of amino carboxylic acids, having a 1-azacycloalkan-2-one structure, or analogues having unsaturation or heteroatoms replacing one or more carbon atoms of the ring.  They are nitrogen analogues (the a nitrogen atom replacing the o atom of the cyclic carboxylic acid group ) of the naturally occurring macrolides.

name: Oxazepines
description: Compounds containing an oxazepine moiety, which consists of an unsaturated aliphatic seven-member ring with one oxygen atom, a nitrogen atom, and five carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxazepine include 1,2-oxazepine, 1,3-oxazepine,and 1,4-oxazepine.

name: Pyrazines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazine ring, which is a six-member aromatic heterocycle, that consists of two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 4) and four carbon atoms.

name: Thiazepines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a seven-member aromatic ring with five carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen atom.

name: Azepines
description: Organic compounds containing an unsaturated seven-member heterocycle with one nitrogen atom replacing a carbon atom.

name: Oxetanes
description: Compounds containing an oxetane ring, which is a four-member saturated aliphatic ring with an oxygen, and three carbon atoms.

name: Diazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a seven-member heterocyclic moiety with five nitrogen atoms, and two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 2 (1,2-Diazepines), 1 and 3 (1,3-Diazepines), or 1 and 4 (1,4-Diazepines).

name: Dibenzodiazepines
description: Compounds containing a dibenzodiazepine moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by diazepine ring.

name: Oxetenes
description: Compounds containing an oxetene ring, which is a four-member unsaturated aliphatic ring with an oxygen, three carbon atoms, and one CC double bond.

name: Pyridazines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyridazine ring, which is a six-member aromatic ring containing two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 2, and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrimidines and pyrimidine derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidne ring, which is a six-member aromatic heterocycle which consists of two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 3) and four carbon atoms.

name: Furans
description: Compounds containing a furan ring, which is a five-member aromatic ring with one oxygen atom, four carbon atoms.

name: Imidazoles
description: Compounds containing an imidazole ring, which is an aromatic five-member ring with two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 3, and three carbon atoms.

name: Imidazolines
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazoline ring, which is an unsaturated ring (derived from imidazole) with two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 3 respectively, and containing only one CN double bond.

name: Indazoles
description: Compounds containing an indazole, which is structurally characterized by a pyrazole fused to a benzene.

name: Isoxazoles
description: Heterocyclic organic compounds containing an isoxazole moiety, with a structure characterized by a five-member aromatic ring with one oxygen atom and one nitrogen atom at ring positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: Oxazines
description: Compounds containing an oxazine moiety, which consists of an unsaturated aliphatic six-member ring with one oxygen atom, a nitrogen atom, four carbon atoms, and two double bonds. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxazine, 1,3-oxazine, and 1,4-oxazine.

name: Oxazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxazole ring, which is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole.

name: Oxazolines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-oxazoline, a five-membered ring with a nitrogen and an oxygen atoms at the 1- and 3-position, respectively. Additionally, it contains two double bonds.

name: Phosphinines
description: Compounds containing a phosphinine ring, which is a benzene derivative where a carbon ring is replaced by a phosphorus atom.

name: Pyrans
description: Compounds containing a pyran ring, which is a six-member heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring with five carbon atoms, one oxygen atom and  two ring double bonds.

name: Pyrazoles
description: Compounds containing a pyrazole ring, which is a five-member aromatic ring with two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 2) and three carbon atoms.

name: Pyrazolines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazoline ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic ring with two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 2) and three carbon atoms.

name: Pyridines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring, which is a six-member aromatic heterocycle which consists of one nitrogen atom and five carbon atoms.

name: Pyrroles
description: Compounds containing a pyrrole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrrolines
description: Compounds containing a pyrroline ring, which is a five-member unsaturated aliphatic ring with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Tetrazines
description: Organic compounds containing a tetrazine ring, which is a six-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a two carbon atoms.

name: Thiadiazoles
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a thiadiazole ring, which is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Thiazines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an aliphatic unsaturated six-member ring with four carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen. Isomers include 1,2-thiazines, 1,3-thiazines, and 1,4-thiazines.

name: Thiazoles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a five-member aromatic ring made up of one sulfur atom, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms.

name: Thiophenes
description: Compounds containing a five-membered aromatic moiety made up of one sulfur atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Triazines
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring, which is a heterocyclic ring, similar to the six-member benzene ring but with three carbons replaced by nitrogen atoms.

name: Triazoles
description: Compounds containing  a five-member aromatic ring of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms.

name: Phenanthridines and derivatives
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a phenanthridine moiety, which is a tricyclic system with two benzene rings joined by a pyridine forming a non-linear skeleton. Hydrogenated derivatives are also included.

name: Eudesmane, isoeudesmane or cycloeudesmane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the eudesmane skeleton.

name: Azetidines
description: Organic compounds containing a saturated four-member heterocycle where one nitrogen atom replaces a carbon atom.

name: Aziridines
description: Organic compounds containing a saturated three-member heterocycle with one amino group and two methylene groups.

name: Azirines
description: Organic compounds containing an unsaturated three-member heterocycle with one amino group and a double bond.

name: Dioxolanes
description: Compounds containing a dioxolane ring, which is a five-membered saturated ring of two oxygen atoms and three carbon atoms. The dioxolanes are divided in 1,2-dioxolanes, and 1,3-dioxolanes.

name: Oxathiolanes
description: Compounds containing an oxathiolane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic five-member ring with one oxygen atom, a sulfur atom, and three carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include meta-oxathiolane, and ortho-oxathiolane.

name: Oxazinanes
description: Compounds containing an oxazinane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic six-member ring with one oxygen atom, a nitrogen atom, and four carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxazinane, 1,3-oxazinane, and 1,4-oxazinane.

name: Oxazolidines
description: Compounds containing an oxazolidine moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic five-member ring with one oxygen atom, one nitrogen, three carbon atoms, and two double bonds.

name: Pteridines and derivatives
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pteridine moiety, which consists of a pyrimidine fused to a pyrazine ring to form  pyrimido(4,5-b)pyrazine.

name: Pterins and derivatives
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pterin moiety, which consist of a pteridine ring bearing a ketone and an amine group to form 2-aminopteridin-4(3H)-one.

name: Tetrazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a tetrazole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a one carbon atom.

name: Hydrazines and derivatives
description: Compounds comprising the hydrazine functional group, with the general formula R1R2NNR3R4.

name: Phenylhydrazines
description: Compounds containing a phenylhydrazide moiety, which consists of a hydrazide substituent attached to a phenyl group.

name: Semicarbazides
description: Organic compounds containing the semicarbazide functional group with the general structure R1(N)R2NR3C(=O)N(R4)R5 (R1-R5=H, alkyl, aryl), a derivative of urea, where the amine group on one side has been replace by a hydrazine group.

name: Semicarbazones
description: Organic compounds containing the semicarbazone functional group, with the general structure R2C=NNHC(=O)NH2.

name: Hydrazones
description: Compounds containing an N-Alkylidene derivative of hydrazine. They have the generic structure RNN=C(R')R\" (R,R',R\"= H or organyl group).

name: Imines
description: Compounds containing an imine functional group, with the general structure RN=CR2 (R = H, hydrocarbyl).

name: Ketones
description: Organic compounds  in which a carbonyl group is bonded to two carbon atoms R2C=O (neither R may be a hydrogen atom). Ketones that have one or more alpha-hydrogen atoms undergo keto-enol tautomerization, the tautomer being an enol.

name: Acetophenones
description: Organic compounds containing the acetophenone structure.

name: Benzophenones
description: Organic compounds containing a ketone attached to two phenyl groups.

name: Thioketones
description: Compounds in which the oxygen of a ketone has been replaced by divalent sulfur R2C=S ( R not H ). Thioketones that have an alpha-hydrogen interconvert with Thioenols. Moreover, they interconvert with thioaldehydes.

name: Alpha-amino ketones
description: Ketones containing a carboxylic acid, and an amine group attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group.

name: Benzopyrans
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyran ring. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds.

name: Aldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing the aldehyde functional group.

name: Quinomethanes
description: Organic compounds containing a cyclohexene or cyclohexadiene ring that bears a methylidene group and a ketone group. Isomers include m-quinomethane (6-methylidenecyclohex-2-en-1-one), o-quinomethane (5-methylidenecyclohex-2-en-1-one), and p-quinomethane (4-methylidenecyclohexa-2,5-dien-1-one).

name: Organic azides
description: Compounds bearing the group N3, viz. -N=N+=N-; usually attached to carbon, e.g. PhN3 phenyl azide or azidobenzene.

name: Isoindoles
description: Heteropolycyclic compounds with a structure containing isoindole, a benzo-fused pyrrole.

name: Alkyl aryl ethers
description: Organic compounds containing the alkyl aryl ether functional group with the generic formula R-O-R' , where R is an alkyl group and R' is an aryl group.

name: Alcohols and polyols
description: Organic compounds in which at least one hydroxyl functional group (-OH) is bound to a carbon atom, usually connected to other carbon or hydrogen atoms.

name: Azaspirodecane derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a spirodecane moiety with at least one nitrogen atom.

name: Enediols
description: Compounds containing the enediol functional group, with the formula HO(R)C=C(R')OH.

name: Enols
description: Compounds containing the enol functional group, with the structure HO(R)C=CR'. Ketones that have one or more alpha-hydrogen atoms undergo keto-enol tautomerization, the tautomer being an enol.

name: 1,3-dicarbonyl compounds
description: Carbonyl compounds with the generic formula O=C(R)C(H)C(R')=O, where R and R' can be any group.

name: Phenols
description: Compounds containing a phenol moiety, which is a benzene bearing a hydroxyl group.

name: Catechols
description: Compounds containing a 1,2-benzenediol moiety.

name: Hydroquinones
description: Compounds containing a hydroquinone moiety, which consists of a benzene ring with a hydroxyl groups at positions 1 and 4.

name: Resorcinols
description: Compounds containing a resorcinol moiety, which is a benzene ring bearing two hydroxyl groups at positions 1 and 3.

name: Anisoles
description: Organic compounds containing a methoxybenzene or a derivative thereof.

name: Tyrosols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a hydroxyethyl group attached to the C4 carbon of a phenol group.

name: Aminophenols
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a phenol.

name: Nitrophenols
description: Compounds containing a nitrophenol moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing both a hydroxyl group and a nitro group on two different ring carbon atoms.

name: Stilbene glycosides
description: Compounds structurally characterized by the presence of a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to the stilbene skeleton.

name: Bisphenols
description: Methylenediphenols, HOC6H4CH2C6H4OH, commonly p,p-methylenediphenol, and their substitution products (generally derived from condensation of two equivalent amounts of a phenol with an aldehyde or ketone).

name: Chromones
description: Compounds containing a benzopyran-4-one moiety.

name: Coumarins and derivatives
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a 1-benzopyran moiety with a ketone group at the C2 carbon atom (1-benzopyran-2-one).

name: Acylaminosugars
description: Organic compounds containing a sugar linked to a chain through N-acyl group.

name: Macrolides and analogues
description: Organic compounds containing a lactone ring of at least twelve members.

name: Dithiazoles
description: Compounds containing a dithiazole moiety, which consists of an unsaturated five-member ring containing two carbon atoms, one nitrogen atom, and two sulfur atoms.

name: Aflatoxins
description: Difuranocoumarin derivatives in which the coumarin is fused to either a cyclopentenone (difurocoumarocyclopentenone series) or a lactone (difurocoumarolactone series).

name: Dibenzoxazepines
description: Compounds containing a dibenzoxazepine moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by an oxazepine ring.

name: Anthraquinones
description: Organic compounds containing either anthracene-9,10-quinone, 1,4-anthraquinone, or 1,2-anthraquinone.

name: Naphthoquinones
description: Compounds containing a naphthohydroquinone moiety, which consists of a benzene ring linearly fused to a bezene-1,4-dione (quinone).

name: Tetracenequinones
description: Polyaromatic hydrocarbon derivatives containing a tetracyclic cycle made up of four linearly fused benzene rings, one of which bears two ketone groups at position 1 and 4.

name: Adamantanones
description: Organic compounds containing a ketone group is attached to the adamantane (tricyclo[3.3.1.1]decane) ring.

name: Carbodiimides
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group consisting of the formula RN=C=NR.

name: N-organohydroxylamines
description: Organic compounds comprising the hydroxylamine functional group, with the general structure R1ON(R2)R3 (R1,R3=H, organyl; R2 = organyl).

name: Epoxides
description: Compounds containing a cyclic ether with three ring atoms(one oxygen and two carbon atoms).

name: Lactams
description: Compounds containing a lactam ring, which is a cyclic amide of amino carboxylic acids, having a 1-azacycloalkan-2-one structure (or an analogue having unsaturation or heteroatoms replacing one or more carbon atoms of the ring).

name: Epothilones and analogues
description: Macrolides consisting of a 16-member lactone ring conjugated at the carbon 16 with a 1-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)prop-1-en-2-yl group. Some epothilone analogues containing a lactam ring instead of the lactone ring.

name: Beta lactams
description: Organic compounds containing a four-member lactam (a cyclic amide).

name: Caprolactams
description: Cyclic amides of caproic acid. Caproic acid is the carboxylic acid derived from hexane with the general formula C5H11COOH.

name: Delta lactams
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a piperidin-2-one moiety.

name: Thiolactams
description: Cyclic thioamides, obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from a lactam ring with sulfur.

name: Carbapenems
description: Beta-lactam derivatives in which the beta-lactam ring shares the nitrogen atom with a pyrrole-2-carboxylic acid.

name: Cephems
description: Organic compounds containing the 5-thia-1-azabicyclo[4.2.0]oct-2-en-8-one nucleus.

name: Clavams
description: Organic compounds containing a 4-oxa-1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]heptan-7-one moiety. Clavams are similar to penams, but with an oxygen substituted for the sulfur in the penam skeleton.

name: Monobactams
description: Compounds comprising beta-lactam ring is alone and not fused to another ring.

name: Oxacephems
description: Organic compounds containing the oxacepehem skeleton, which is similar to a cephem, but with oxygen substituted for the sulfur.

name: Penams
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing the 4-thia-1-azabicyclo[3.2.0]heptan-7-one structure.

name: Cephalosporins
description: Compounds containing a 1,2-thiazine fused to a 2-azetidinone to for a oxo-5-thia-1-azabicyclo[4.2.0]oct-2-ene-2-carboxylic acid moiety or a derivative thereof.

name: Penicillins
description: Organic compounds containing the penicillin core structure, which is structurally characterized by a penam ring bearing two methyl groups at position 2, and an amide group at position 6 [starting from the sulfur atom at position 1].

name: Glycerolipids
description: Lipids formed by joining fatty acids to glycerol by ester bonds.

name: Benzoic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid substituent attached to a benzene ring.

name: Imidazopyridinones
description: Compounds containing an imidazopyridine moiety where the pyridine ring bears a ketone group.

name: Benzamides
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxamido substituent attached to a benzene ring.

name: Hippuric acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a hippuric acid or a derivative, with a structure characterized the presence of a benzoyl group linked to the N-terminal of a glycine.

name: Tetracyclines
description: Polyketides having an octahydrotetracene-2-carboxamide skeleton, substituted with many hydroxy and other groups.

name: Catecholamines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing 4-(2-Aminoethyl)pyrocatechol [4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol] or a derivative thereof formed by substitution.

name: Tryptamines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing the tryptamine backbone, which is structurally characterized by an indole ring substituted at the 3-position by an ethanamine.

name: Pheniramines
description: Compounds containing a pheniramine moiety, which is structurally characterized by the presence of a 2-benzylpyridine linked to an dimethyl(propyl)amine to form a dimethyl[3-phenyl-3-(pyridin-2-yl)propyl]amine skeleton.

name: Phenylmethylamines
description: Compounds containing a phenylmethtylamine moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted by an methanamine.

name: Phenethylamines
description: Compounds containing a phenethylamine moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the second position by an ethan-1-amine.

name: Phenylpropylamines
description: Compounds containing a phenylpropylamine moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the third carbon by an propan-1-amine.

name: Amphetamines and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing or derived from 1-phenylpropan-2-amine.

name: Piperazines
description: Compounds containing a piperazine ring, which is a saturated aliphatic six-member heterocyclic with two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 4, as well as four carbon atoms.

name: Methoxyphenols
description: Compounds containing a methoxy group attached to the benzene ring of a phenol moiety.

name: Diazaspirononane derivatives
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a nine-membered saturated bicyclic moiety, consisting of two aliphatic saturated rings in a spiro-configuration, each of which contain a nitrogen atom. The bicyclic moiety is made up of two nitrogen and seven carbon atoms.

name: Cyclopyrrolones
description: Compounds belonging to a family of pyridin-2-ylpyrrole based chemicals. The pyrrole is usually fused to a benzene, pyrimidine, or dithiin.

name: Dioxoles
description: Compounds containing a dioxole ring, which is a five-membered unsaturated ring of two oxygen atoms and three carbon atoms. The dioxoles are divided in meta-dioxoles, and ortho-dioxoles.

name: Nitrofurans
description: Compounds containing a furan ring which bears a nitro group.

name: Piperidines
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring, which is a saturated aliphatic six-member ring with one nitrogen atom and five carbon atoms.

name: Oxazolidinones
description: Compounds containing an oxazolidinone moiety, which is an oxazolidine bearing a ketone group.

name: Oxazolidinediones
description: Compounds containing an oxazolidine ring which bears two ketones.

name: Oligosaccharides
description: Carbohydrates made up of 3 to 10 monosaccharide units linked to each other through glycosidic bonds.

name: Thioxanthenes
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing a thioxanthene moiety, which is an aromatic tricycle derived from xanthene by replacing the oxygen atom with a sulfur atom.

name: Xanthenes
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a xanthene moiety, which consists of two benzene rings joined to each other by a pyran ring.

name: Tocopherols
description: Vitamin E derivatives containing a saturated trimethyltridecyl chain attached to the carbon C6 atom of a benzopyran ring system. The differ from tocotrienols that contain an unsaturated trimethyltrideca-3,7,11-trien-1-yl chain.

name: Psoralens
description: Organic compounds containing a psoralen moiety, which consists of a furan fused to a chromenone to for 7H-furo[3,2-g]chromen-7-one.

name: Thioxanthones
description: Compounds containing a thioxanthene moiety which bears an ketone group.

name: Xanthones
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a xanthene moiety conjugated to a ketone group at carbon 9. Xanthene is a tricyclic compound made up of two benzene rings linearly fused to each other through a pyran ring.

name: Pyrazolones
description: Compounds containing a pyrazole ring which bears a ketone.

name: Cinnolines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene fused to a pyridazine ring.

name: Phthalazines
description: Compounds containing a phthalazine moiety, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyridazine, forming a 2,3-benzodiazine skeleton.

name: Pyridazinones
description: Compounds containing a pyridazine ring which bears a ketone.

name: Phthalazinones
description: Compounds containing a phthalazine bearing a ketone group.

name: Carbazoles
description: Compounds containing a three ring system containing a pyrrole ring fused on either side to a benzene ring.

name: Indoles and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an indole, which is a bicyclic ring system made up of a six-membered benzene ring fused to a five-membered nitrogen-containing pyrrole ring.

name: Porphyrins
description: Compounds containing a fundamental skeleton of four pyrrole nuclei united through the alpha-positions by four methine groups to form a macrocyclic structure.

name: Pyrrolopyridines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolopyridine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyridine. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center.

name: Hydroxyeicosapentaenoic acids
description: Eicosanoic acids with an attached hydroxyl group and five CC double bonds.

name: Sugar acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a saccharide unit which bears a carboxylic acid group.

name: Indolizines
description: Polycyclic  compounds containing an indolizine moiety, which is characterized by the presence of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyridine(Pyrrolo[1,2-a]pyridine).

name: Pyrazolidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazolidine ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic ring with two nitrogen atoms (at positions 1 and 2) and three carbon atoms.

name: Pyrrolidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine ring, which is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrrolizines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolizine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyrrolidine ring.

name: Pyrrolizidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolizidine, which is a bicyclic ring system made up of two fused pyrrolidine ring sharing a nitrogen atom.

name: Quinolizidines
description: Compounds containing a quinolizidine moiety, which is a  octahydro-2H-quinolizine derivative.

name: Quinolizines
description: Compounds containing a quinolizine moiety, which consists of two fused pyridine rings sharing a nitrogen atom.

name: Hydrophenanthrenes
description: A phenanthrene derivative where at least one ring CC bond is substituted by hydrogenation.

name: Thiadiazines
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a thiadiazine ring, which is a six-member unsaturated heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Nitrothiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring which bears a nitro group.

name: Thiazolidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a five-member saturated aliphatic ring with one nitrogen atom, one sulfur atom, three carbon atoms.

name: Thiazolidinones
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazolidinone ring which bears one ketone group.

name: Thiazolidinediones
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazolidine ring which bears two ketone groups.

name: Thiazolines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a five-member unsaturated aliphatic ring with one nitrogen atom, one sulfur atom, three carbon atoms.

name: Benzothiepins
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiepine ring (a seven-membered ring with six carbon atoms and one sulfur atom).

name: Dibenzothiepins
description: Compounds containing a dibenzothiepin moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by a thiepine ring.

name: Thiolanes
description: Organic compounds containing thiolane, a five-member saturated ring containing four carbon atoms and a sulfur atom.

name: Triazolones
description: Compounds containing a triazole ring which bears a ketone group.

name: Triazolidines
description: Compounds containing  a five-member saturated aliphatic ring of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms.

name: Ellagic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an ellagic acid moiety (4,4',5,5',6,6'-Hexahydroxydiphenic acid 2,6,2',6'-dilactone) or a derivative thereof.

name: Acyl monophosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a monophosphate linked to an acyl group. They have the general structure  R-CO-P(O)(O)OH, R=H or organyl.

name: Tannins
description: Naturally occurring polyphenols which be categorized into four main classes: hydrolyzable tannin (based on ellagic acid or gallic acid), condensed tannins (made of oligomeric or polymeric proanthocyanidins), complex tannins (made of a catechin bound to a gallotannin or elagitannin), and phlorotannins (oligomers of phloroglucinol).

name: Camptothecins
description: Heterocyclic compounds comprising a planar pentacyclic ring structure, that includes a pyrrolo[3,4-beta]-quinoline moiety (rings A, B and C), conjugated pyridone moiety (ring D) and one chiral center at position 20 within the alpha-hydroxy lactone ring with (S) configuration (the E-ring).

name: Nitroimidazoles
description: Compounds containing an imidazole ring which bears a nitro group.

name: Thienoimidazoles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to an imidazole ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions.

name: Biotin and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a ureido (tetrahydroimidizalone) ring fused with a tetrahydrothiophene ring.

name: Purines and purine derivatives
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: Hypoxanthines
description: Compounds containing the purine derivative 1H-purin-6(9H)-one. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: Xanthines
description: Purine derivatives with a ketone group conjugated at carbons 2 and 6 of the purine moiety.

name: 1,2-dioxoles
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-dioxole, an aliphatic five-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 2, and a double bond.

name: Thioxanthines
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing a thioxanthine moiety, which is an aromatic bicyclic structure derived from xanthine by replacing a carbonyl group with a thiocarbonyl group.

name: Imidazolidines
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazolidine ring, which is a saturated ring (derived from imidazole) with two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 3 respectively, and containing only single bonds.

name: Indolizidines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an indolizidine, which is a bicyclic heterocycle containing a saturated six-member ring fused to a saturated five-member ring, one of the bridging atoms being nitrogen.

name: Quinuclidines
description: Compounds containing a 1-azabicyclo[2.2.2]octane moiety.

name: Stilbenes
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-diphenylethylene moiety. Stilbenes (C6-C2-C6 ) are derived from the common phenylpropene (C6-C3) skeleton building block. The introduction of one or more hydroxyl groups  to a phenyl ring lead to stilbenoids.

name: Ethers
description: Compounds bearing an ether group with the formula Compounds ROR (R not H).

name: Folic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds based on the 4-[(pteridin-6-ylmethyl)amino]benzoic acid skeleton conjugated with one or more L-glutamate units (or derivatives thereof).

name: Glycerophospholipids
description: Derivatives of glycerophosphoric acid that contains at least one O-acyl, or O-alkyl, or O-(1-alkenyl) group attached to the glycerol residue.

name: Sphingolipids
description: Lipids  containing backbone of sphingoid bases (e.g. Sphinogsine, sphinganine) usually bound to a fatty acid derivative through N-acylation.

name: Steroids and steroid derivatives
description: Compounds based on the cyclopenta[a]phenanthrene carbon skeleton, partially or completely hydrogenated; there are usually methyl groups at C-10 and C-13, and often an alkyl group at C-17. By extension, one or more bond scissions, ring expansions and/or ring contractions of the skeleton may have occurred.

name: Prenol lipids
description: Lipids synthesized from the five-carbon-unit precursors isopentenyl diphosphate and dimethylallyl diphosphate.

name: Monohydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Bile acids, alcohols or any of their derivatives bearing a hydroxyl group.

name: Phenylpropanoids and polyketides
description: Organic compounds that are synthesized either from the amino acid phenylalanine (phenylpropanoids) or the decarboxylative condensation of malonyl-CoA (polyketides). Phenylpropanoids are aromatic compounds based on the phenylpropane skeleton. Polyketides usually consist of alternating carbonyl and methylene groups (beta-polyketones), biogenetically derived from repeated condensation of acetyl coenzyme A (via malonyl coenzyme A), and usually the compounds derived from them by further condensations.

name: Fatty acids and conjugates
description: Aliphatic monocarboxylic acids with a saturated or unsaturated aliphatic tail (with at least 4 Carbon atoms).

name: Organic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds an organic acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group with the formula -C(=O)OH or a derivative thereof.

name: Short-chain hydroxy acids and derivatives
description: Hydroxy acids with an alkyl chain the contains less than 6 carbon atoms.

name: Organohalogen compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a bond between a carbon atom and a halogen atom (At, F, Cl, Br, I).

name: Organosulfenic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds derived from sulfenic acid, with the general formula R1SR2 ( R1= organyl, R2=any heteroatom).

name: Sulfinic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds derived from sulfinic acid, with the general formula RS(=O)R' ( R not H, R'=any heteroatom).

name: Organosulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a sulfonic acid or derivative, with the general structure RS(=O)2X (R=alkyl, aryl; X=any heteroatom).

name: Carbamic acids
description: Compounds containing the carbamic acid functional group, with the general structure RN(R')C(=O)OH or RN(R')C(=O)[O-] where R,R' = H or organyl group.

name: 1,3-dioxoles
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-dioxole, an aliphatic five-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 3 and a double bond.

name: Acridines
description: Organic compounds containing the acridine moiety, a linear tricyclic heterocycle which consists of two benzene rings joined by a pyridine ring.

name: Acryloyl compounds
description: Organic compounds containing the acryloyl functional group (which has the core fragment but-3-en-2-one).

name: Organonitrogen compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a nitrogen atom.

name: Alkaloids and derivatives
description: Naturally occurring chemical compounds that contain mostly basic nitrogen atoms. This group also includes some related compounds with neutral and even weakly acidic properties. Also some synthetic compounds of similar structure are attributed to alkaloids. In addition to carbon, hydrogen and nitrogen, alkaloids may also contain oxygen, sulfur and more rarely other elements such as chlorine, bromine, and phosphorus.

name: Beta-amino ketones
description: Ketones containing a carboxylic acid, and an amine group attached to the beta carbon atom, relative to the C=O group.

name: Aminobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids (or derivative thereof) containing an amine group attached to the benzene moiety.

name: Aminoglycosides
description: Molecules or a portion of a molecule composed of amino-modified sugars.

name: Aminopyridines and derivatives
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an amino group attached to a pyridine ring.

name: Aniline and substituted anilines
description: Organic compounds containing an aminobenzene moiety.

name: Anilides
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds derived from oxoacids RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l not 0) by replacing an OH group by the NHPh group or derivative formed by ring substitution.

name: Primary alcohols
description: Compounds comprising the primary alcohol functional group, with the general structure RCOH (R=alkyl, aryl).

name: Nucleosides, nucleotides, and analogues
description: Compounds containing a nucleobase linked to a ribose or deoxyribose sugar via a beta-glycosidic linkage. The ribose or deoxyribose moiety bears at least a phosphate group in case of nucleotides.

name: Azulenes
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing the azulene skeleton, which consists of the cyclopentadiene ring fused to a cycloheptadiene ring.

name: Pyrimidones
description: Compounds that contain a pyrimidine ring, which bears a ketone. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Barbituric acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing a perhydropyrimidine ring substituted at C-2, -4 and -6 by oxo groups.

name: Benzazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an azepine ring (unsaturated seven-membered heterocycle with one nitrogen atom replacing a carbon atom).

name: Benzimidazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an imidazole ring (five member ring containing a nitrogen atom, 4 carbon atoms, and two double bonds).

name: Benzodiazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to either isomers of diazepine(unsaturated seven-member heterocycle with two nitrogen atoms replacing two carbon atoms).

name: Benzodioxoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to either isomers of dioxole. Dioxole is a five-membered unsaturated ring of two oxygen atoms and three carbon atoms.

name: Lysophosphatidylglycerols
description: Glycerophosphoglycerols  (molecules containing a glycerol moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) in which only one fatty acid is bonded to the 1-glycerol moiety (through an ester linkage).

name: Fatty aldehydes
description: Long chain aldehydes with a chain of at least 12 carbon atoms.

name: Medium-chain hydroxy acids and derivatives
description: Hydroxy acids with a 6 to 12 carbon atoms long side chain.

name: Benzofurans
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a furan. Furan is a five-membered aromatic ring with four carbon atoms and one oxygen atom.

name: Benzoxazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazole ring Oxazole is five-membered aromatic ring with a nitrogen and an oxygen atoms at the 1- and 3-position, respectively.

name: Phenylpiperidines
description: Compounds containing a phenylpiperidine skeleton, which consists of a piperidine bound to a phenyl group.

name: Pyrazolopyridines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazolopyridine skeleton, which consists of a pyrazole fused to a pyridine. Pyrazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring with four carbon and one nitrogen atoms.

name: Pyrazolopyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazolopyrimidine skeleton, which consists of a pyrazole fused to a pyrimidine. Pyrazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers. Pyrimidine is 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen atoms at the 1- and 3- ring position.

name: Phenyltetrazoles and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phenyltetrazole skeleton, which consists of a tetrazole bound to a phenyl group.

name: Azepanes
description: Organic compounds containing a saturated seven member heterocycle, with one nitrogen atom.

name: Benzothiadiazines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiadiazine ring (a six-member ring with two nitrogen atoms and a sulfur atom).

name: Benzothiazines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiazine ring (a six-membered ring with four carbon atoms, one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom).

name: Phenothiazines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a phenothiazine moiety, which is a linear tricyclic system that consists of a two benzene rings joined by a para-thiazine ring.

name: Benzothiazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiazole ring (a five-membered ring with four carbon atoms, one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom).

name: Benzothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiepine ring (a five-membered ring with six carbon atoms and one sulfur atom).

name: Triazolopyrazines
description: Compounds containing a triazole ring fused to a pyrazine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyrazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of six carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at ring positions 1 and 4.

name: Triazolopyridines
description: Compounds containing a triazole ring fused to a pyridine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center.

name: Benzotriazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a triazole ring (a five-membered ring with two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms).

name: Benzopyrenes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a pyrene(benzo[def]phenanthrene) ring system.

name: Benzothiazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a thiazepine ring (a seven-membered ring with a nitrogen atom and a sulfur atom replacing two carbon atoms).

name: Carbamic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds comprising the carbamic acid functional group or a derivative thereof. They have the general structure RN(R')C(=O)OH or RN(R')C(=O)R\", where R,R'= H or organyl group, R\"= OH, alkyloxy, acyloxy, or halogen.

name: Benzoxazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazepine ring (a seven-membered ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and a nitrogen atom).

name: Dibenzazepines
description: Compounds with two benzene rings connected by an azepine ring. Azepine is an unsaturated seven-member heterocycle with one nitrogen atom replacing a carbon atom.

name: Benzoyl derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an acyl moiety of benzoic acid with the formula (C6H5CO-).

name: Organooxygen compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a bond between a carbon atom and an oxygen atom.

name: Fatty acid esters
description: Carboxylic ester derivatives of a fatty acid.

name: Biphenols
description: Organic compounds containing two phenol groups linked together by a C-C bond.

name: Bipyridines and oligopyridines
description: Organic compounds containing two pyridine rings linked to each other.

name: Bisphosphonates
description: Organic compounds containing two phosphonate groups linked together through a carbon atoms.

name: Imidazopyridines
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a pyridine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center.

name: Phenylazirines
description: Compounds containing a phenylazirine moiety, which consists of an azirine ring attached to a phenyl group.

name: Phenylbenzimidazoles
description: Compounds containing a phenylbenzimidazole skeleton, which consists of a benzimidazole moiety where its imidazole ring is attached to a phenyl group.

name: Fatty amides
description: Carboxylic acid amide derivatives of fatty acids, that are formed from a fatty acid and an amine.

name: Phosphatidylglycerophosphates
description: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphates in which two fatty acids are bonded to the 1-glycerol moiety through ester linkages.

name: Straight chain fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with a straight aliphatic chain.

name: Flavonoids
description: Plant secondary metabolites that contain the 2-phenylchromene skeleton. Plant secondary metabolites that contain the 2-phenylchromene skeleton.

name: N-acylpiperidines
description: Compounds containing an N-acyethanolamine moiety, which is characterized by an acyl group is linked to the nitrogen atom of a piperidine.

name: Anthocyanidins
description: Sugar-free counterparts of anthocyanins based on the flavylium ion or 2-phenylchromenylium ion.

name: Flavans
description: Compounds containing a flavan moiety, with a structure characterized by a 2-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton.

name: Branched fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a branched chain.

name: Unsaturated fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with a chain that contains at least one CC double bond.

name: Hydroperoxy fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a hydroperoxide group attached to the chain.

name: Hydroxy fatty acids
description: Fatty acids in which the chain bears a hydroxyl group.

name: Pyridinylpyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyridinylpyrimidine skeleton, which consists of a pyridine linked (not fused) to a pyrimidine by a bond.

name: Pyrrolopyrazines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolopyrazine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyrazine. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyrazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of six carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at ring positions 1 and 4.

name: Thienopyridines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a pyridine ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center.

name: Dicarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing exactly two carboxylic acid groups.

name: Amino acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an amine group, a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof), and a side-chain that is specific to each amino acid.

name: Peptides
description: Compounds containing an amide derived from two or more amino carboxylic acid molecules (the same or different) by formation of a covalent bond from the carbonyl carbon of one to the nitrogen atom of another.

name: Butyrophenones
description: Compounds containing 1-phenylbutan-1-one moiety.

name: Biflorane and serrulatane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based either on the biflorane or the serrulatane skeleton.

name: Corrinoids
description: Derivatives of the corrin nucleus, which contain four reduced or partly reduced pyrrole rings joined in a macrocycle by three =CH- groups and one direct carbon-carbon bond linking alpha positions.

name: Coumestans
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a coumestan moiety, which consists of a benzoxole fused to a chromen-2-one to form 1-Benzoxolo[3,2-c]chromen-6-one. They are oxidation products of pterocarpan.

name: Cumenes
description: Aromatic compounds containing a prop-2-ylbenzene moiety.

name: Curcuminoids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a curcumin moiety, which is composed of two aryl buten-2-one (feruloyl) chromophores joined by a methylene group.

name: Sesquaterpenoids
description: Terpenoids with at least 7 consecutive isoprene units.

name: Furanocoumarins
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a coumarin moiety.

name: Thietanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated four-member ring with three carbon atoms and one sulfur atom.

name: Nitriles
description: Compounds having the structure RC#N; thus C-substituted derivatives of hydrocyanic acid, HC#N.

name: Cyanates
description: Organic compounds containing the cyanate functional group with the formula [OCN]-.

name: Organic carbonic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds comprising the organic carbonic acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Cyclamates
description: Compounds containing a cyclohexylsulfamic acid moiety.

name: Nitrosimines
description: Compounds containing the nitrosimine functional group, with the general structure O=NN=CR2.

name: Dihydropyridines
description: Compounds containing a dihydropyridine moiety, which is a semi-saturated pyridine derivative with two double bonds.

name: Dioxanes
description: Compounds containing a dioxane ring, which is a six-membered saturated ring of two oxygen atoms and four carbon atoms. The dioxanes are divided in 1,2-dioxanes, 1,3-dioxanes, and 1,4-dioxanes.

name: Diphenylmethanes
description: Compounds containing a diphenylmethane moiety, which consists of a methane wherein two hydrogen atoms are replaced by two phenyl groups.

name: Phenylmorpholines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a morpholine ring and a benzene ring linked to each other through a CC or a CN bond.

name: Fentanyls
description: Compounds containing the fentanyl moiety or a derivative, which is based on a N-(1-(2-phenylethyl)-4-piperidinyl)-N-phenylpropanamide skeleton.

name: Glucosinolates
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing a  N-(sulfooxy)ethenimidothioic acid derivative attached to the C1 carbon of glucose moiety.

name: Glucuronides
description: Compounds comprising the glucuronic acid linked to another substance via a glycosidic bond.

name: Guanidines
description: Compounds containing a guanidine moiety, with the general structure (R1R2N)(R3R4N)C=N-R5.

name: Hydroxamic acids
description: Compounds containing a hydroxamic acid functional group in which a hydroxylamine is inserted into a carboxylic acid. Its general structure is R-CO-NH-OH, with an R as an organic residue.

name: Thiiranes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated three-member ring with two carbon atoms and one sulfur atom.

name: Dithietanes
description: Compounds comprising a dithietane moiety, which is four-member saturated ring containing two divalent sulfur atoms and two carbon atoms.

name: Proanthocyanidins
description: Molecules containing an oligomeric moiety of C4-C8 and/or C4-C6 and/or C2-C7 oligo/polymers of flavan-3-ols.

name: Hydroxyquinols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a 1,2,4-trihydroxybenzene moiety.

name: Aporphines
description: Quinoline alkaloids containing the dibenzo[de,g]quinoline ring system or a dehydrogenated derivative thereof.

name: Phloroglucinols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phloroglucinol (benzene-1,3,5-triol) moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing one hydroxyl group at positions 1,3, and 5.

name: Alloxazines and isoalloxazines
description: Organic compounds comprising the (iso)alloxazine structure (Benzo[g]pteridine-2,4-dione).

name: Acyl cholines
description: Acylated derivatives of choline. Choline or 2-Hydroxy-N,N,N-trimethylethanaminium is a quaternary ammonium salt with the chemical formula (CH3)3N+(CH2)2OH.

name: Hydroperoxyeicosatetraenoic acids
description: Eicosanoic acids with an attached hydroperoxyl group and four CC double bonds.

name: Ketenes
description: Organic compounds in which a carbonyl group is connected by a double bond to an alkylidene group R2C=C=O.

name: Keto acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a ketone group and a carboxylic acid group.

name: Indolequinones
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an indolequinone moiety, which consists of an indole bearing two ketones at positions 5 and 6 (or 4 and 7).

name: Mitomycins
description: Polycyclic compounds with a structure based on an aziridine ring linked to a 7-amino-6-methyl-cyclohexa[b]pyrrolizine-5,8-dione.

name: Morpholines
description: Organic compounds containing a morpholine moiety, which consists of a six-member aliphatic saturated ring with the formula C4H9NO, where the oxygen and nitrogen atoms lie at positions 1 and 4, respectively.

name: Alpha amino acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of alpha amino acids.

name: Organic nitrates
description: Organic compounds containing the nitrate oxoanion, with the formula NO3-.

name: Organic nitrites
description: Organic compounds containing the nitrite oxoanion, with the formula NO2-.

name: Pyrogallols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a 1,2,3-trihydroxybenzene moiety.

name: Nitrogen mustard compounds
description: Compounds having two beta-haloalkyl groups bound to a nitrogen atom.

name: Phenylazides
description: Compounds containing a phenylazide moiety, which consists of a linear azide substituent attached to a phenyl group.

name: Organophosphorus compounds
description: Organic compounds containing the phosphorus atom.

name: Organic phosphines and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphine derivative, with the general formula B1P(R2)R3 (R1-R3=alkyl, aryl).

name: Organic phosphoric acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing phosphoric acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Organic sulfuric acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfuric acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Organoarsenic compounds
description: Compounds containing bond between a carbon atom and an arsenic atom.

name: Phosphate esters
description: Organic compounds containing phosphoric acid ester functional group, with the general structure R1P(=O)(R2)OR3. R1,R2 = O,N,  or halogen atom; R3 = organyl group.

name: Keto fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a ketone group attached to the acyl chain.

name: Azo compounds
description: Derivatives of diazene(diimide), HN=NH, wherein both hydrogens are substituted by hydrocarbyl groups, e.g. PhN=NPh azobenzene or diphenyldiazene.

name: Oximes
description: Compounds containing the oxime functional group, with the general structure R1(R2)C=NOH.

name: Dioxetanes
description: Compounds containing a dioxetane ring, which is a four-member ring of two oxygen atoms and two carbon atoms. The dioxetanes are divided in 1,2-dioxetanes, and 1,3-dioxetanes.

name: Pentalenes
description: Compounds containing a pentalene moiety, which consists of two fused cyclopentadiene rings.

name: Organic peroxides
description: Organic compounds containing the peroxide group, with the formula  R1OOR2 (R1,R2=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Boronic acids
description: Compounds comprising the boronic acid functional group RB(O)O  (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Phenazines and derivatives
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a phenazine moiety, which is a linear tricyclic system that consists of a two benzene rings joined by a pyrazine ring.

name: Phenoxyacetic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing an anisole where the methane group is linked to an acetic acid or a derivative.

name: Phenylacetic acids
description: Compounds containing a phenylacetic acid moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the second position by an acetic acid.

name: Organic phosphonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing phosphonic acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Chlorinated dibenzo-p-dioxins
description: Organic compounds containing a chlorine atom attached to a dibenzo-p-dioxin moiety.

name: Azoles
description: Organic compounds comprising a five-member nitrogen heterocyclic ring containing at least one other non-carbon atom of either nitrogen, sulfur, or oxygen. The parent compounds are aromatic and have two double bonds; there are successively reduced analogs (azolines and azolidines) with fewer.

name: Organometallic compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a bond between a carbon atom and metal atom.

name: Organic oxoanionic compounds
description: Organic compounds containing an oxoanion.

name: Coumaric acid esters
description: Aromatic compounds containing an ester derivative of coumaric acid.

name: Phenylcarbamic acids
description: Compounds containing a phenylazide moiety, which consists of a carbamic acid substituent attached to a phenyl group.

name: Monoalkylamines
description: Organic compounds containing an primary aliphatic amine group.

name: Enamines
description: Compounds containing the enamine functional group with the general structure R1N(R2)CR=C(R3)R4.

name: Nitro fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a nitro group.

name: Hydroxy acids and derivatives
description: Compounds comprising one or more hydroxy acid groups.

name: Biguanides
description: Organic compounds containing two N-linked guanidines.

name: Carboxylic acid amides
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing a carbonyl group in which the carbon atom is linked to a nitrogen atom (substituted or not). The general formula of the carboxylic acid amide is R1C(=O)N(R2)R3 (R1,R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Cinnamic acids and derivatives
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene and a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof) forming 3-phenylprop-2-enoic acid.

name: Polyprenyl phosphates
description: Prenol lipids in which the phosphate group is linked to one end of the polyprenol moiety.

name: Purine nucleosides
description: Compounds comprising a purine base attached to a ribosyl or deoxyribosyl moiety.

name: Pyrimidine nucleosides
description: Compounds comprising a pyrimidine base attached to a ribosyl or deoxyribosyl moiety.

name: Pyranones and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyran ring which bears a ketone.

name: Trithiolanes
description: Organic compounds containing a six-member aliphatic saturated heterocycle made up of three sulfur atoms and two carbon atoms.

name: Halogenated fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with a chain that carries a halogen atom (Cl,F,I,Br).

name: Dithiolanes
description: Compounds containing a dithiolane ring,  which consists of a sulfur heterocycle derived from cyclopentane by replacing two CH2 groups with thioether groups.

name: Quinazolines
description: Compounds containing a quinazoline moiety, which is made up of two fused six-member aromatic rings, a benzene ring and a pyrimidine ring.

name: Quinoxalines
description: Compounds containing a quinoxaline moiety, a bicyclic heterocycle made up of a benzene ring fused to a pyrazine ring.

name: Salicylic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a 2-hydroxybenzoic acid moiety or a derivative thereof.

name: Organic nitric acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an organonitric acid group or a derivative thereof.

name: Amino fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing an amine group.

name: Sulfonylureas
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfonyl group with the structure R-S(=O)2-R', where R' is an urea.

name: Sulfoxides
description: Compounds containing a sulfoxide functional group, with the structure RS(=O)R' (R,R' not H).

name: Tropane alkaloids
description: Organic compounds containing the nitrogenous bicyclic alkaloid parent N-Methyl-8-azabicyclo[3.2.1]octane.

name: Thiaziridines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a 3-membered saturated ring with a thioether group and an amine group in the 1 and 2 positions, respectively.

name: Isoflavones
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a 2-isoflavene skeleton which bears a ketone group at the C4 carbon atom.

name: Carbocyclic fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a carbocyclic ring .

name: Amine oxides and derivatives
description: Organic compounds that contains the amine oxide functional group with the formula R3N+-O-, which substituted by at least one organic group.

name: Aminals
description: Compounds having two amino groups bonded to the same carbon,  R2C(NR2)2 where R can by a hydrogen or an alkyl group.

name: Boronic acid derivatives
description: Compounds comprising any derivative of the boronic acid functional group, with the general structure RB(X)Y (R=alkyl, aryl; X,Y= any O, N, Hal residue).

name: Imidoesters
description: Organic ester derivatives of imidic acid. They have the general structure ROC(CR')=NR\", where R=organyl group, R'-R\"= H or organyl group.

name: Chlorinated biphenyls
description: Organic compounds containing at least one chlorine atom attached to either benzene ring of the biphenyl moiety.

name: Isocyanates
description: Organic compounds containing the isocyanic acid tautomer, HN=C=O, of cyanic acid, HOC#N or its hydrocarbyl derivatives RN=C=O.

name: Xanthanolides
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the xanthanolide skeleton consistsing of a cycloheptane ring usually attached to a four-carbon chain (at carbon 1 ) and a methyl group (at carbon 10), and fused to a five-member lactone ring (sharing carbons 7 and 8). The lactone ring can be conjugated with a methyl or methylene group at position 11.

name: Quaternary ammonium salts
description: Compounds containing positively charged polyatomic ion of the structure NR4+, R being an alkyl group or an aryl group.

name: Lineolic acids and derivatives
description: Derivatives of lineolic acid. Lineolic acid is a polyunsaturated omega-6 18 carbon long fatty acid, with two CC double bonds at the 9- and 12-positions.

name: Sulfones
description: Compounds containing a sulfonyl group( which as the general structure RS(=O)2R' (R,R' =alkyl, aryl)) attached to two carbon atoms.

name: Sulfonyl halides
description: Compounds containing a sulfonyl (R-S(=O)2-R') functional group singly bonded to a halogen atom.

name: Isoflavonoid O-glycosides
description: O-glycosylated derivatives of isoflavonoids, which are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: Sultams
description: Sulfonamides in which the S-N bond is part of a ring.

name: Thioamides
description: Organic compounds containing the functional group with the general structure R-CS-NR'R, where R, R', and R are organic groups.

name: Jasmonic acids
description: Lipids containing or derived from a jasmonic acid, with a structure characterized by the presence of an alkene chain linked to a 2-(3-oxocyclopentyl)acetic acid moiety.

name: Eicosanoids
description: Unsaturated C20 fatty acids or skeletally related compounds. These include prostaglandins, thromboxanes, leukotrienes and other oxygenated derivatives, which are produced primarily by three classes of enzymes, cyclooxygenases (COX-1 and COX-2), lipoxygenases (LOX) and cytochrome P450 mono-oxygenases.

name: Prostaglandins and related compounds
description: Unsaturated carboxylic acids consisting of a 20 carbon skeleton that also contains a five member ring, and are based upon the fatty acid arachidonic acid.

name: Leukotrienes
description: Eicosanoids containing a hydroxyl group attached to the aliphatic chain of an arachidonic acid. Leukotrienes have four double bonds, three (and only three) of which are conjugated.

name: Dihydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing or derived from a bile acid or alcohol, and which bears exactly two carboxylic acid groups.

name: Ureas
description: Compounds containing two amine groups joined by a carbonyl (C=O) functional group.

name: Triphenylenes
description: Compounds containing a triphenylene moiety, which consists of four fused benzene rings forming a 9,10-benzo[l]phenanthrene.

name: Thromboxanes
description: Eicosanoids structurally characterized by the presence of a 6-member ether containing ring.

name: Purinones
description: Purines in which the purine moiety bears a C=O group. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: Glycosylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids structurally characterized by the presence of one or more sugar residues attached to glycerol via a glycosidic linkage.

name: Benzimidazole ribonucleosides and ribonucleotides
description: Nucleosides with a structure that consists of an  imidazole moiety of benzimidazole is N-linked to a ribose (or deoxyribose). Nucleotides have a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon of the ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety.

name: Taxanes and derivatives
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based either on the taxane skeleton, or a derivative thereof. In term of phytochemistry, several derivatives of the taxane skeleton exist: 2(3->20)-abeotaxane, 3,11-cyclotaxane, 11(15->1),11(10->9)-abeotaxane, 3,8-seco-taxane, and 11(15->1)-abeotaxane, among others. More complex skeletons have been found recently, which include the taxane-derived [3.3.3] propellane ring system.

name: Chlorins
description: Large heterocyclic aromatic ring systems consisting, at the core, of three pyrroles and one pyrroline coupled through four methine linkages.

name: Phospholanes
description: Compounds containing a phospholane ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one phosphorus atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Imidazothiazoles
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a thiazole ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Thiazole is a 6-membered ring that contains both sulfur and nitrogen.

name: Oxaphospholanes
description: Compounds containing an oxaphospholane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic five-member ring with two oxygen atoms, a phosphorus atom, and two carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxaphosphane, and 1,3-oxaphospholane.

name: Dioxaphospholanes
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a five-member aliphatic single-bonded ring, with a phosphorine atom and two oxygen atoms at the ring positions 1, 2, and 3 respectively.

name: Phospholes
description: Compounds containing a phosphole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle with one phosphorus atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Dibenzazecins
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing two benzene rings joined by an azecin ring.

name: Oxime ethers
description: Compounds containing the oxime ether functional group, with the general structure R1(R2)C=NOR3 ( R3 not H).

name: Cholines
description: Organic compounds containing a N,N,N-trimethylethanolammonium cation.

name: Steroidal glycosides
description: Sterol lipids containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to the steroid skeleton.

name: Cycloalkanes
description: Saturated monocyclic hydrocarbons (with or without side chains).

name: Acyl bromides
description: Organic compounds containing the functional group -CO-Br.

name: Alkadienes
description: Acyclic hydrocarbons that contain exactly two carbon-to-carbon double bonds.

name: Hepoxilins
description: Eicosanoids containing an oxirane group attached to the fatty acyl chain.

name: Acyl chlorides
description: Organic compounds containing the functional group -CO-Cl.

name: Acyl fluorides
description: Organic compounds containing the functional group -CO-F.

name: Alkyl bromides
description: Organic compounds containing the alkyl bromide functional group with formula R-Br, where R is an alkyl group.

name: Alkyl chlorides
description: Organic compounds containing the alkyl chloride functional group with formula R-Cl , where R is an alkyl group.

name: Alkyl fluorides
description: Organic compounds containing the alkyl fluoride functional group with formula R-F , where R is an alkyl group.

name: Alkyl iodides
description: Organic compounds containing the alkyl iodide functional group with formula R-I , where R is an alkyl group.

name: Aryl bromides
description: Organic compounds containing the acyl bromide functional group.

name: Aryl chlorides
description: Organic compounds containing the acyl chloride functional group.

name: Aryl fluorides
description: Organic compounds containing the acyl fluoride functional group.

name: Aryl iodides
description: Organic compounds containing the acyl iodide functional group.

name: Imidoyl chlorides
description: Imidoyl halides with the general formula R(Br)C=NR' where X is a chlorine atom.

name: Imidoyl fluorides
description: Imidoyl halides with the general formula R(Br)C=NR' where X is a fluorine atom.

name: Sulfonyl chlorides
description: Compounds containing a sulfonyl (R-S(=O)2-R') functional group singly bonded to a chlorine atom.

name: Sulfonyl fluorides
description: Compounds containing a sulfonyl (R-S(=O)2-R') functional group singly bonded to a fluorine atom.

name: Sulfonyl iodides
description: Compounds containing a sulfonyl (R-S(=O)2-R') functional group singly bonded to an iodine atom.

name: Carboxamidines
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing the amidine group.

name: Sulfinamidines
description: Compounds containing a sulfinamidine group, with the general structure RS(=NR)NR2.

name: Phosphinamidines
description: Compounds containing a phosphinamidine group, with the general structure  R2P(=NR)NR2.

name: Tetrazolines
description: Organic compounds containing a tetrazoline ring, which is a five-member unsaturated aliphatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms, a one carbon atom, and one double bond.

name: Hemiaminals
description: Compounds comprising the hemiaminal functional group, with the general formula R2C(OH)NR2 where R can by a hydrogen or an alkyl group.

name: Acyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to an acyl chain.

name: Toluenes
description: Compounds containing a benzene ring which bears a methane group.

name: Hemiacetals
description: Compounds comprising the hemiacetal functional group, with the general formula R2C(OH)OR' ( R' not Hydrogen ).

name: Carboxylic acid derivatives
description: Derivatives of carboxylic acid.

name: Imidothioesters
description: Organic thioester derivatives of imidic acid. They have the general structure RSC(CR')=NR\", where R=organyl group, R'-R\"= H or organyl group.

name: Acyl carnitines
description: Organic compounds containing a fatty acid with the carboxylic acid attached to carnitine through an ester bond.

name: N-acyl amines
description: Compounds containing a fatty acid moiety linked to an amine group through an ester linkage.

name: Benzyloxycarbonyls
description: Organic compounds containing a carbonyl group substituted with a benzyloxyl group.

name: Bromobenzenes
description: Organic compounds containing a bromine atom attached to a benzene ring.

name: Chlorobenzenes
description: Compounds containing one or more chlorine atoms attached to a benzene moiety.

name: Fluorobenzenes
description: Compounds containing one or more fluorine atoms attached to a benzene ring.

name: Iodobenzenes
description: Aromatic compounds containing one or more iodine atoms attached to a benzene.

name: Acyl homoserine lactones
description: N-acyl-homoserine-lactones attached to a long aliphatic chain.

name: Trihydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Prenol lipids structurally characterized by a bile acid or alcohol which bears three hydroxyl groups.
