name: Phthalic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phthalic acid moiety (or a derivative thereof), which is a benzene ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at two different ring positions. Isomers of phthalic acid include meta-phthalic acid (benzene-1,3-dioic acid), ortho-phthalic acid (benzene-1,2-dioic acid), and para-phthalic acid (benzene-1,4-dioic acid).

name: M-phthalic acid and derivatives
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at ring carbon atoms 1 and 2.

name: P-phthalic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a benzene ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at ring carbon atoms 1 and 4.

name: Phthalic anhydrides
description: Compounds containing a phthalic anhydride moiety (or a derivative thereof), which consists of a benzene fused to a furan-1,3-dione.

name: Tetrahydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Prenol lipids structurally characterized by a bile acid or alcohol which bears four hydroxyl groups.

name: Flavonoid glycosides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is glycosidically linked to one of the flavonoid backbones (2-phenylchromen-4-one, 3-phenylchromen-4-one or 4-phenylcoumarin).

name: Thiocarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a derivative of thiocarboxylic acid, with the general structure RC(=S)R' (R=H, alkyl, aryl; R'=any heteroatom).

name: Alpha-keto acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a keto group on the adjacent carbon.

name: Beta-keto acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a keto group on the C3 carbon atom.

name: Gamma-keto acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a keto group on the C4 carbon atom.

name: Lipoic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a lipoic acid moiety (or a derivative thereof), which consists of a pentanoic acid (or derivative) attached to the C3 carbon atom of a 1,2-dithiolane ring.

name: Polyprenyl phospho carbohydrates
description: Polyprenyl phosphates with a carbohydrate moiety attached to it.

name: Gamma-amino ketones
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid, and an amine group attached to the C4 carbon atom.

name: Thiobarbituric acid derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a 2-thioxodihydropyrimidine-4,6(1H,5H)-dione skeleton.

name: Glycinated bile acids and derivatives
description: Compounds with a structure characterized by the presence of a glycine linked to a bile acid skeleton.

name: Steroid lactones
description: Sterol lipids containing a lactone moiety linked to the steroid skeleton.

name: 2,3-diphenylfurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a furan ring substituted with a phenyl group only the C2- and C3-positions.

name: Acyclic monoterpenoids
description: Monoterpenes that do not contain a cycle.

name: Dithiazolethiones
description: Compounds containing a dithiazole bearing a thioketone group.

name: Diacylglycerols
description: Glycerides consisting of two fatty acid chains covalently bonded to a glycerol molecule through ester linkages.

name: 1,2,4-dithiazole-3-thiones
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2,4-dithiazole ring with a thioketone group at ring position 3.

name: Pyrimidodiazepines
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidoazepine moiety, which consists of a pyrimidine fused to a piperazine ring by a bond. Pyrimidine is 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and two nitrogen atoms at ring positions 1 and 3. Diazepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers.

name: Monoacylglycerols
description: Glycerides consisting of one fatty acid chain covalently bonded to a glycerol molecule through an ester linkage.

name: Thionucleosides
description: Nucleoside analogues that contain a thiolane or a thietane that is 1,3-disubstituted with a hydroxyl group and pyrimidine or purine base, at the 1- and 3-position, respectively.

name: Triacylglycerols
description: Glycerides consisting of three fatty acid chains covalently bonded to a glycerol molecule through ester linkages.

name: Flavonols
description: Compounds that contain a flavone (2-phenyl-1-benzopyran-4-one) backbone carrying a hydroxyl group at the 3-position.

name: Monocarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids containing exactly one carboxyl groups.

name: Leucoanthocyanidins
description: Flavonoids consisting of a flavan (3,4-dihydro-2-phenyl-2H-1-benzopyran) moiety that carries two hydroxy groups at the C3- and C4-positions.

name: Phosphatidylinositol phosphates
description: Phosphorylated derivatives of phosphatidylinositols, which are glycerophosphoinositols where the glycerol is esterified with two fatty acids.

name: Harmala alkaloids
description: Compounds with a structure based on harmaline, harmine, harmalol, harman or a derivative of those parents. These parents are beta-carbolines, consisting of a pyrimidine fused to the pyrrole moiety of an indole to form a pyrido[3,4-b]indole.

name: Sulfonylanilines
description: Compounds containing an aniline moiety, which is para-substituted by a sulfonyl group.

name: Chrysenes
description: Compounds containing the polyaromatic chrysene moiety, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a phenanthrene ring system to form Benzo[a]phenanthrene.

name: Coenzyme A and derivatives
description: Derivative of vitamin B5 containing a 4'-phosphopantetheine moiety attached to a diphospho-adenosine.

name: Fluoroquinolones
description: Compounds containing a fluorine atom attached to a quinolone. Quinolone or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine, and bears a ketone group.

name: N-acylethanolamines
description: Compounds containing an N-acyethanolamine moiety, which is characterized by an acyl group is linked to the nitrogen atom of ethanolamine.

name: Indolines
description: Compounds containing an indole moiety, which consists of pyrrolidine ring fused to benzene  to form 2,3-dihydroindole.

name: Amino sugars
description: Sugars having one alcoholic hydroxy group replaced by an amino group; systematically known as x-amino-x-deoxymonosaccharides.  These compounds do not include Glycosylamines.

name: Imidazolidinones
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazolidinone moiety, which is an imidazolidine ring bearing a ketone.

name: Imidazolidinediones
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazolidinedione moiety, which is an imidazolidine ring bearing two ketones.

name: Indanones
description: Compounds containing an indane ring bearing a ketone group.

name: Organic nitro compounds
description: Compounds having the nitro group, -NO2 (free valence on nitrogen), which may be attached to carbon, nitrogen (as in nitramines), or oxygen (as in nitrates), among other elements (in the absence of specification, C-nitro compounds are usually implied).

name: Lipoamides
description: Compounds containing a lipoamide moiety, which consists of a pentanamide attached to the C3 carbon atom of a 1,2-dithiolane ring.

name: Nitroquinolines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a nitro group attached to a quinoline moiety.

name: Phenylaziridines
description: Compounds containing a phenylaziridine moiety, which consists of an aziridine ring attached to a phenyl group.

name: Sulfonyls
description: Compounds containing the sulfonyl group, with the general structure RS(=O)2R' ( R,R' must not be H).

name: Pyrrolidones
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine ring which bears a C=O group.

name: Taurinated bile acids and derivatives
description: Bile acid derivatives containing a taurine conjugated to the bile acid moiety.

name: Pyridinones
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring, which bears a ketone.

name: Thiosulfinic acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing an ester of thiosulfinic acid with the general structure RS(=S)OR' (R, R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Carbamate esters
description: Compounds containing an ester of carbamic acid with the general structure R2NC(=O)OR' (R' not H). They are esters of carbamic acids.

name: Amidrazones
description: Organic compounds containing the carboxylic acid amidrazone functional group.

name: Carboxylic acid hydrazides
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing a carbonyl group in which the carbon is directly linked to a hydrazide group (N-N).

name: Carboxylic acid salts
description: Ionic derivatives of carboxylic acid.

name: Dialkyl ethers
description: Organic compounds containing the dialkyl ether functional group, with the formula ROR', where R and R' are alkyl groups.

name: Ketene acetals
description: Organic compounds comprising the ketene acetal functional group, with the general structure XC(Y)=C(R3)R4 (R1,R2=H, alkyl, aryl; X,Y=any hetero atom).

name: Phosphonic acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing phosphonic acid ester functional group,  with the general structure ROP(=O)OH (R = organyl group).

name: Organosulfenic acid amides
description: Compounds derived from a sulfenic acid, RSOH (R= organyl, not H), by replacement of -OH by -NR2.

name: Sulfinic acid amides
description: Compounds derived from a sulfinic acid, RS(=O)OH (R not H), by replacement of -OH by -NR2.

name: Organosulfonic acid esters
description: Esters of sulfonic acid, which have the general structure RS(=O)2OR' (R,R' = organyl, not H).

name: Organosulfonic acids
description: Compounds containing the sulfonic acid group, which has the general structure RS(=O)2OH (R is not a hydrogen atom).

name: Sulfuric acid monoamides
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfuric acid amid functional group, with the generic structure ROS(=O)(=O)N(R')R'' (R = any atom, R' = organyl, R''=H or organyl).

name: Corroles
description: Compounds containing a corrole nucleus, which contains four pyrrole rings joined in a macrocycle by three  groups and one direct carbon-carbon bond linking alpha positions.

name: Sulfuric acid diamides
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfuric acid diamide functional group, with the generic structure R1N(R2)S(=O)(=O)ON(R3)R4 (R1-R4 = H or organyl.

name: Sulfuric acid diesters
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfuric acid diester functional group with the generic structure ROS(OR')(=O)=O, (R,R'=organyl group).

name: Sulfuric acid monoesters
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfuric acid monoester functional group, with the generic structure ROS(O)(=O)=O, (R=organyl group).

name: Thioacetals
description: Organic compounds containing either the monothiacetal functional group (R2C(OR')(SR')) or the dithioacetal (R2C(SR')2) functional group .

name: Thioaldehydes
description: An organic compounds in which the oxygen of an aldehyde has been replaced by divalent sulfur, RC(=S)H. Thioaldehydes interconvert with thioketones.

name: N-acyl-alpha amino acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid (or a derivative thereof) which bears an acyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: Thiocarbamic acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the general structure R1OC(=S)N(R2)R3 (R1=alkyl, aryl; R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Carbamic acid halides
description: Compounds containing a carbamic acid derivative linked to a halogen atom.

name: Oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group attached to steroid skeleton.

name: Thiocarbonic acid diesters
description: Organic compounds containing a diester derivative of thiocarbonic acid, with the general formula ROC(=S)OR' (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Thiocarbonyl compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the general structure R1C(=S)R2 (R1, R2=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Thiocarboxylic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a thiocarboxylic acid functional group, with the general structure HOC(=S)OH.

name: Thioesters
description: Organic compounds containing an ester of thiocarboxylic acid, with the general structure RC(=S)XR' (R=H, alkyl, aryl; R'=alkyl, aryl; X=O,S).

name: Thiocyanates
description: Salts or esters of thiocyanic acid, with the general formula RSC#N (R=alkyl, aryl).

name: Thioethers
description: Compounds containing the ester derivative of thiocarboxylic acid, with the general structure R-S-R' (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Organic phosphoramides
description: Organic compounds containing the phosphoric acid amide functional group.

name: Carboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group with the formula -C(=O)OH.

name: Thiosemicarbazides
description: Compounds containing a derivative of thiosemicarbazide with the general structure R1N(R2)N(R3)C(=S)N(R4)R5 (R1-R5=H, alkyl, aryl) where the ketone group has carbonyl group has been replaced with a thiocarbonyl group.

name: Thiosemicarbazones
description: Compounds containing the thiosemicarbazone functional group obtained by replacing the carbonyl group by a thiocarbonyl group.

name: Thioureas
description: Organic compounds containing the thiourea functional group, a derivative of urea with the general structure (R1(N)R2C(=S)(R3)R4, R1-R4=H, alkyl, aryl), obtained by replacing the carbonyl group of urea with a thiocarbonyl group.

name: Ynamines
description: N,N-Disubstituted alk-1-yn-1-amines RCCNR2.

name: Dihydropyranones
description: Compounds containing a hydrogenated pyran ring which bears a ketone, and contains one double bond.

name: Alkylthiols
description: Organic compounds containing the thiol functional group linked to an alkyl chain.

name: Pyridoindoles
description: Compounds containing a pyridoindole, which consists of a pyridine fused to an indole. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center. Indole is a bicyclic  compound consisting of a six-membered benzene ring fused to a five-membered nitrogen-containing pyrrole ring.

name: Thiolactones
description: Cyclic thioesters obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from a lactone ring with sulfur.

name: Benzyl cyanides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetonitrile with one hydrogen replaced by a phenyl group.

name: Precorrins
description: Intermediates formed by methylation at one or more of the four rings prior to the formation of the macrocyclic corrin ring.

name: Alpha-diketones
description: Organic compounds containing two ketone groups on two adjacent carbon atoms.

name: N-carbamoyl-alpha amino acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid (or a derivative thereof) which bears an carbamoyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: Aminoimidazoles
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group linked to an imidazole ring.

name: Imidazolyl carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid chain (of at least 2 carbon atoms) linked to an imidazole ring.

name: Pteroic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds that are composed of a pterin with a 4-aminobenzoic acid (or a derivative) at the 6 position on the pteridine ring. Pteridine is a ring system made up of a pyrazine fused to a pyrimidine.

name: Nitrosoureas
description: Compounds containing a nitro group and an urea group N-N linked together, with the general structure R1N(R2)C(=O)N(R3)N=O.

name: Thiocarboxylic acid amides
description: Organic compounds containing an amide of thiocarboxylic acid, with the general structure R1C(=S)N(R2)R3 (R1-R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Isoureas
description: Organic compounds containing the isourea group, with the general structure R1N(R2)C(=NR3)OR4, or its hydrocarbyl derivatives (R1,R2,R3,R4=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Isothioureas
description: Organic compounds containing the isothiourea group, with the general structure R1SC(=NR2)N(R3)R4 (R1,R2,R3,R4=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Cardiolipins
description: Glycerophospholipids in which the O1 and O3 oxygen atoms of the central glycerol moiety are each linked to one 1,2-diacylglycerol chain. Their general formula is OC(COP(O)(=O)OC[C@@H](CO[R1])O[R2])COP(O)(=O)OC[C@@H](CO[R3])O[R4], where R1-R4 are four fatty acyl chains.

name: Isothiocyanates
description: Organic compounds containing the isothiocyanate group, an isocyanate analogue with the general formula RN=C=S.

name: Organosulfenic acids
description: Compounds containing a sulfenic acid functional group, with the general structure RSOH (R not H).

name: Orthocarboxylic acid derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the orhtocarboxylic acid functional group, with the RC(X)(X)X (R=H, alkyl, aryl; X=OH, alkoxy, aryloxy, substituted amino, etc.).

name: Carboxylic acid orthoesters
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing a carbon atom form three single bonds, each with one oxygen atom.

name: Carboxylic acid esters
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives in which the carbon atom from the carbonyl group is attached to an alkyl or an aryl moiety through an oxygen atom (forming an ester group).

name: Carboxylic acid azides
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives a carbonyl group in which the carbon is directly linked to an azide group (-N=N+=N-).

name: Carboxylic acid anhydrides
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives two carbonyl groups where the carbon atoms are both linked to the same oxygen atom.

name: Beta propiolactones
description: Organic compounds containing a four-member lactone (a cyclic ester).

name: Delta valerolactones
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing an oxan-2- one moiety.

name: Gamma butyrolactones
description: Compounds containing a gamma butyrolactone moiety, which consists of an aliphatic five-member ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and bears a ketone group on the carbon adjacent to the oxygen atom.

name: Hydroxybenzoic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing a hydroxybenzoic acid (or a derivative), which is a benzene ring bearing a carboxyl and a hydroxyl groups.

name: Flavins
description: Compounds containing a flavin (7,8-dimethyl-benzo[g]pteridine-2,4-dione) moiety, with a structure characterized by an isoalloaxzine tricyclic ring.

name: Phosphocholines
description: Compounds containing a [2-(trimethylazaniumyl)ethoxy]phosphonic acid or derivative.

name: Gallic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a 3,4,5-trihydroxybenzoic acid moiety.

name: Indole-3-acetic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing an acetic acid (or a derivative) linked to the C3 carbon atom of an indole.

name: Quinolines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyrimidine ring to form benzo[b]azabenzene.

name: CDP-diacylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids containing a diacylglycerol, with a cytidine diphosphate attached to the oxygen O1 or O2 of the glycerol part.

name: Phenylacetaldehydes
description: Compounds containing a phenylacetaldehyde moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the second position by an acetalydehyde.

name: Neuraminic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing or derived from a neuraminic acid moiety (5-amino-3,5-dideoxy-D-glycero-D-galacto-non-2-ulosonic acid), which is a 9-carbon monosaccharide.

name: Aminopyrimidines and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a pyrimidine ring. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: CDP-glycerols
description: Glycerolipids with a cytidine diphosphate attached to the oxygen O1 or O2 of the glycerol part. As is the case with diacylglycerols, phosphatidylserines can have many different combinations of fatty acids of varying lengths and saturation attached to the C-1 and C-2 atoms.

name: Phosphoethanolamines
description: Compounds containing a phosphate linked to the second carbon of an ethanolamine.

name: Aldimines
description: Organic compounds containing the aldimine functional group.

name: Nicotinamide nucleotides
description: Pyridine nucleotides, in which the pyridine base is nicotinamide or a derivative thereof.

name: Sulfinic acids
description: Compounds containing a sulfinic acid functional group, with the general structure RS(=O)OH (R = organyl, not H).

name: Thiodiacetic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing a thiodiacetic acid group (or esters/salts thereof) which is made up of two 2-sulfanylacetic (OC(=O)CS) acid moieties sharing their sulfur atom.

name: Cresols
description: Aromatic compounds containing a methoxyphenol moiety.

name: Meta cresols
description: Aromatic compounds containing a meta-cresol moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing a methyl group and a hydroxyl group at ring positions 1 and 3, respectively.

name: Ortho cresols
description: Organic compounds containing an ortho-cresol moiety, which consists of a benzene bearing one hydroxyl group at ring positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: Para cresols
description: Compounds containing a para cresol moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing one hydroxyl group at ring positions 1 and 4.

name: Phenylpyruvic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phenylpyruvic acid moiety, which consists of a phenyl group substituted at the second position by an pyruvic acid.

name: Carotenoids
description: Organic compounds formed by eight consecutive isoprene fragments. Carotenoids are a subgroup of tetraterpenes, and are subdivided in two categories: Carotenes and Xanthophylls.

name: Sulfur mustard compounds
description: Compounds containing having two beta-haloalkyl groups bound to a sulfur atom.

name: Alpha ketoaldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a keto group on the adjacent carbon.

name: Terpene lactones
description: Prenol lipids containing a lactone ring.

name: Thiamines
description: Compounds containing a thiamine moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 3-[(4-Amino-2-methyl-pyrimidin-5-yl)methyl]-4-methyl-thiazol-5-yl backbone.

name: Benzenediols
description: Organic compounds containing two hydroxyl groups attached to a benzene ring.

name: Thiamine phosphates
description: Thiamine derivatives in which the hydroxyl group of the ethanol moiety is substituted by a phosphate group.

name: Indolyl carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid chain (of at least 2 carbon atoms) linked to an indole ring.

name: Pyranoquinolines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a quinoline moiety.  Quinoline or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine.

name: Cyclic alcohols and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an aliphatic ring substituted with at least one hydroxyl group.

name: Purine nucleotide sugars
description: Purine nucleotides bound to a saccharide derivative through the terminal phosphate group.

name: Polyprenylbenzoquinones
description: Compounds containing a polyisoprene chain attached to a quinone at the second ring position.

name: Hydroxysteroids
description: Compounds containing an steroid backbone, with at least one hydrogen substituted by a hydroxyl group.

name: Pyrimidine nucleotide sugars
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides bound to a saccharide derivative through the terminal phosphate group.

name: Pyridine nucleotides
description: Compounds containing a (deoxy)ribose phosphate with the ribose unit N-linked to a pyridine ring.

name: 1,2-diacylglycerol-3-phosphates
description: Glycerol-3-phosphates in which the glycerol moiety is bonded to two aliphatic chains through ester linkages.

name: Alkynes
description: acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having a carbon-carbon triple bond and the general formula CnH2n-2.

name: Organic phosphonic acids
description: Organic compounds containing phosphonic acid.

name: Organic thiophosphoric acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure RP(R')(R'')=S, where R,R',R'' = O,N, halogen residue.

name: Brevetoxins and derivatives
description: A group of cyclic polyether compounds produced naturally by a species of dinoflagellate known as Karenia brevis. They contain a Pentaoxapentacycloheptacos- 23-en-7-one derivative (type a brevetoxin) or a pentaoxapentacyclotetracosa- 8,23-dien-7-one derivative (type b brevetoxin).

name: Organic isocyanides
description: Organic compounds containing the isomer HN+#C- of hydrocyanic acid, HC#N, or its hydrocarbyl derivatives RNC (RN+#C-).

name: Organic hydroperoxides
description: Organic compounds comprising the hydroperoxide functional group, with the general formula [O-O]2-.

name: Organophosphine oxides
description: Organic compounds containing the phosphine oxide group, with the general formula R3P=O or R3P+O-.

name: Benzenetriols and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing three hydroxyl groups attached to a benzene ring.

name: Isoprenoid phosphates
description: Prenol lipids containing a phosphate group linked to an isoprene (2-methylbuta-1,3-diene) unit.

name: 1,2-dioxanes
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-dioxane, an aliphatic six-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,4-dioxanes
description: Organic compounds containing 1,4-dioxane, an aliphatic six-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 4.

name: 1,3-dioxanes
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-dioxane, an aliphatic six-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 3.

name: 1,2-dioxolanes
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-dioxolane, an aliphatic five-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,3-dioxolanes
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-dioxolane, an aliphatic five-member ring with two oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 3.

name: Hippuric acids
description: Compounds containing hippuric acid, which consists of a of a benzoyl group linked to the N-terminal of a glycine.

name: Pyrimidinecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Lysophosphatidic acids
description: Glycerophosphates where the glycerol is esterified with one fatty acid linked to the phosphate group at position O-3.

name: Pyrimidinecarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidine ring which bears a carboxamide.

name: Pyridinecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring bearing a carboxylic acid group or a derivative thereof.

name: Pyrrolizidinones
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolizidine moiety which bears a ketone. Pyrrolizidine is a bicyclic ring system made up of two fused pyrrolidine ring sharing a nitrogen atom.

name: Quinolizidinones
description: Compounds containing a quinolizidine moiety which bears a ketone group.

name: Pyridinecarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring bearing a carboxamide.

name: Triazolidinones
description: Compounds containing a triazolidine ring which bears a ketone group.

name: 3-oxo-acyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a 3-oxo acylated coenzyme A derivative.

name: Flavin nucleotides
description: Nucleotides containing a flavin moiety. Flavin is a compound that contains the tricyclic isoalloxazine ring system, which bears 2 oxo groups at the 2- and 4-positions.

name: Benzoins
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-hydroxy ketone attached to two phenyl groups.

name: Fatty alcohols
description: Aliphatic alcohols consisting of a chain of a least six carbon atoms.

name: 1,2-diazepines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-diazepine, a seven-member heterocyclic ring with two nitrogen atoms in positions 1 and 2.

name: 1,4-diazepines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,4-diazepine, a seven-member heterocyclic ring with two nitrogen atoms in positions 1 and 4.

name: 1,3-diazepines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-diazepine, a seven-member heterocyclic ring with two nitrogen atoms in positions 1 and 3.

name: 1,2-oxazepines
description: Organic compounds containing an aromatic seven-membered ring containing a nitrogen and an oxygen atom, a positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: 1,4-oxazepines
description: Organic compounds containing an aromatic seven-membered wring containing a nitrogen and an oxygen atom, a positions 1 and 4, respectively.

name: 1,3-oxazepines
description: Organic compounds containing an aromatic seven-membered wring containing a nitrogen and an oxygen atom, a positions 1 and 3, respectively.

name: 1,3-oxazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-oxazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and an oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 3 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: 1,4-oxazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,4-oxazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and an oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 4 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: 1,2-oxazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-oxazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and an oxygen atoms in ring positions 1 and 2 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: Phosphatidylinositols
description: Glycerophosphoinositols where the glycerol is esterified with two fatty acids.

name: Benzaldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring with a formyl substituent.

name: Diazines
description: Organic compounds containing a five-member heterocyclic compound with five nitrogen atoms, and two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 2 (Pyridazines), 1 and 3 (Pyrimidines), or 1 and 4 (Pyrazines).

name: 1,3-thiazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-thiazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and a sulfur atoms in ring positions 1 and 3 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: 1,2-thiazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,2-thiazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and a sulfur atoms in ring positions 1 and 2 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: 1,4-thiazines
description: Organic compounds containing 1,4-thiazine, a six-member ring with a nitrogen and a sulfur atoms in ring positions 1 and 4 respectively, as well as two double bonds.

name: Benzoic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of benzoic acid.

name: Meta thiazepines
description: Aromatic compounds containing meta thiazepine moiety, which is an unsaturated seven-member heterocyclic compound, with five carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at position 1 and 3.

name: Ortho thiazepines
description: Compounds containing a thiazepine ring, in which the sulfur and nitrogen atoms are at positions 1 and 2 respectively.

name: Para thiazepines
description: Compounds containing a para thiazepine moiety, which consists of an unsaturated seven-member ring with one nitrogen atom and one sulfur at positions 1 and 4, respectively, as well as two CC double bonds.

name: Lysophosphatidylinositols
description: Glycerophosphoinositols  (molecules containing an inositol moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) where the glycerol is esterified with one fatty acid.

name: Acyclic diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids (compounds made of four consecutive isoprene units) that do not contain a cycle.

name: Phosphatidylglycerols
description: Glycerophosphoglycerols in which two fatty acids are bonded to the 1-glycerol moiety through ester linkages. As is the case with diacylglycerols, phosphatidylglycerols can have many different combinations of fatty acids of varying lengths and saturation attached to the C-1 and C-2 positions.

name: Alpha hydroxy acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid substituted with a hydroxyl group on the adjacent carbon.

name: Anthocyanins
description: Organic compounds containing a flavylium ion or 2-phenylchromenylium based skeleton bound to a sugar.

name: Flavanonols
description: Compounds containing a flavan-3-one moiety, with a structure characterized by a 2-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran bearing a hydroxyl group and a ketone at the carbon C2 and C3, respectively.

name: Enones
description: Compounds containing the enone functional group, with the structure RC(=O)CR'.

name: Sugar amino acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a saccharide unit that bears both an amine group and a carboxylic acid group.

name: Phosphatidylserines
description: Glycerophosphoserines in which two fatty acids are bonded to the glycerol moiety through ester linkages. As is the case with diacylglycerols, phosphatidylserines can have many different combinations of fatty acids of varying lengths and saturation attached to the C-1 and C-2 positions.

name: Thiocarbamic acid derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the general structure OC(=S)NR2 or SC(=O)NR2.

name: Boronic acid esters
description: Compounds comprising the boronic acid ester functional group RN(X)OR' (R,R'=alkyl, aryl; X= any O, N, Hal residue).

name: Organometalloid compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a metalloid atom.

name: Ynones
description: Organic compounds containing the ynone functional group, an alpha,beta unsaturated ketone group with the general structure  RC#C-C(=O)R' (R'  not H).

name: Cyanohydrins
description: Organic compounds containing the cyanohydrin functional group, -C(OH)CN.

name: Beta ketoaldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a keto group on the second carbon atom.

name: Lysophosphatidylserines
description: Glycerophosphoserines  (molecules containing a serine moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) with one fatty acid bonded to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage.

name: Chlorinated dibenzofurans
description: Organic compounds containing a chlorine atom attached to a dibenzofuran moiety.

name: Benzo-p-dioxins
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,4-dioxin ring.

name: Dibenzo-p-dioxins
description: Compounds containing a dibenzo-p-dioxin moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by a para-dioxin ring.

name: Dioxins
description: Compounds containing a dioxin ring, which is a six-membered unsaturated ring of two oxygen atoms and four carbon atoms.

name: Ortho dioxins
description: Compounds containing a dioxin ring, in which the two oxygen atoms are at positions 1 and 2 respectively.

name: Para dioxins
description: Compounds containing a para dioxin moiety, which consists of an unsaturated six-member ring with two oxygen atoms at positions 1 and 4, as well as two CC double bonds.

name: Neoflavones
description: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on the 4-phenylcoumarin skeleton.

name: Hydroxycinnamic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an cinnamic acid (or a derivative thereof) where the benzene ring is hydroxylated.

name: Lignans, neolignans and related compounds
description: Plant products of low molecular weight formed primarily from oxidative coupling of two p-propylphenol moieties. They can also be described as micromolecules with two phenylpropanoid units coupled together. They can be attached in various manners, like C5-C5', C8-C8'. Most known natural lignans are oxidized at C9 and C9 and, based upon the way in which oxygen is incorporated into the skeleton and on the cyclization patterns, a wide range of lignans of very different structural types can be formed.

name: Phosphatidylethanolamines
description: Glycerophosphoetahnolamines in which two fatty acids are bonded to the glycerol moiety through ester linkages.

name: Ceramide phosphoethanolamines
description: Ceramides with phosphoethanolamine as substituent. Phosphoethanolamine is an organophosphorus compound with the general structure NCCOP(O)(O)=O.

name: Benzoxazines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazine ring (a six-membered aliphatic ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one nitrogen atom).

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acyl-glycerophosphates
description: Glycerophosphates that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position.

name: Menthane monoterpenoids
description: Monoterpenoids with a structure based on the o-, m-, or p-menthane backbone. P-menthane consists of the cyclohexane ring with a methyl group and a (2-methyl)-propyl group at the 1 and 4 ring position, respectively. The o- and m- menthanes are much rarer, and presumably arise by alkyl migration of p-menthanes.

name: Imidazolinones
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazolinone moiety, which is an imidazoline ring bearing a ketone.

name: Ergosterols and derivatives
description: Steroids containing ergosta-5,7,22-trien-3beta-ol or a  derivative thereof, which is based on the 3beta-hydroxylated ergostane skeleton.

name: 1-alkyl,2-acylglycerophosphates
description: Glycerophosphates  in which the O-1 atom of the glycerol is bonded to a fatty acid (saturated or unsaturated) through an ether linkage, and the O-2 atom is bonded to another fatty acid through an ester linkage.

name: Lysophosphatidylethanolamines
description: Glycerophosphoetahnolamines  (molecules containing an ethanolamine moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) with one  fatty acid chain bonded to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage.

name: Phosphatidylcholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines in which the two free -OH are attached to one fatty acid each through an ester linkage.

name: Xanthophylls
description: Carotenoids containing an oxygenated carotene backbone. Carotenes are characterized by the presence of two end-groups (mostly cyclohexene rings, but also cyclopentene rings or acyclic groups) linked by a long branched alkyl chain. Carotenes belonging form a subgroup of the carotenoids family. Xanthophylls arise by oxygenation of the carotene backbone.

name: Carotenes
description: A type of unsaturated hydrocarbons containing eight consecutive isoprene units. They are characterized by the presence of two end-groups (mostly cyclohexene rings, but also cyclopentene rings or acyclic groups) linked by a long branched alkyl chain. Carotenes belonging form a subgroup of the carotenoids family.

name: Lysophosphatidylcholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines (molecules containing a choline moiety attached to the phosphate group linked to a glycerol) in which the glycerol is esterified with  one fatty acid each through an ester linkage.

name: Medium-chain keto acids and derivatives
description: Keto acids with a 6 to 12  carbon atoms long side chain.

name: Short-chain keto acids and derivatives
description: Keto acids with an alkyl chain the contains less than 6 carbon atoms.

name: Ceramides
description: Lipid molecules containing a sphingosine in which the amine group is linked to a fatty acid.

name: Neutral glycosphingolipids
description: Glycosphingolipids in which the ceramide skeleton  is bound to an oligosaccharide (usually 3 to 5 units) moiety made up of a glucose (as primary unit bound to the ceramide moiety) and galactose (Gal), N-acetylglucosamine (GlcNAc), N-acetylgalactosamine (GalNAc) or mannose (Man) as the other monosaccharides.

name: 1-ribosyl-imidazolecarboxamides
description: Organic compounds containing the imidazole ring linked to a ribose ring through a 1-2 bond.

name: Glycidol esters
description: Compounds containing an ester derivative of glycidol (2,3-Epoxy-1-propanol).

name: Other hydroxyeicosapolyenoic acids
description: Hydroxyeicosapolyenoic acids which do not belong to the Hydroxyeicosapentaenoic acids, the Hydroxyeicosatetraenoic acids, or the Hydroxyeicosatrienoic acids.

name: Thia fatty acids
description: Fatty acid derivatives obtained by insertion of a sulfur atom at specific positions in the chain.

name: Sulfated fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing linked to a sulfate group linked to its tail.

name: Pyrophosphatidic acids
description: Lipids structurally characterized by the presence of a glycerol moiety bonded to two aliphatic chains through ester linkages, and to a pyrophosphate group.

name: Phosphoceramides
description: Compounds containing an n-acyl-ceramide phosphate skeleton.

name: Simple glycosylceramides
description: Compounds containing a ceramide linked to a simple glycosyl moiety.

name: GalNAcb1-3Gala1-4Galb1-4Glc- (Globo series)
description: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is GalNAcb1-3Gala1-4Galb1-4Glc.

name: Galb1-3GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc- (Lacto series)
description: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is Galb1-3GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc.

name: Galb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc- (Neolacto series)
description: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence of the oligosaccharide moiety is Galb1-4GlcNAcb1-3Galb1-4Glc. The differ from lacto series because of their 1-4 (instead of 1-3) bond between Galb and GlcNacb.

name: Betacyanins and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a glycoside of indolium-2-carboxylic acid attached, with the nitrogen ring of the indolium ring attached to an ethylpyridine-2,6-dicarboxylic acid derivative. Betacyanins are red nitrogenous pigments found in certain plants, such as beetroots.

name: Betalains
description: Organic compounds belonging to the class of Betaxanthins or Betacyanins. This class also contains derivatives of betalamic acid, which is the precursor of betalains.

name: Benzoxazinones
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazine ring (a six-member aliphatic ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one nitrogen atom) bearing a ketone group.

name: Organothiophosphorus compounds
description: Organic derivatives of thiophosphonic acid, thiophosphoric acid, dithiophosphoric acid, or phosphorotrithioic acid, or derivatives thereof. Thiophosphonic acid, dithiophosphoric acid, thiophosphoric acid, and phosphorotrithioic acid are thiophosphorus compounds with the formula OP(O)(=S), OP(S)(=S)O, OP(O)(=S)O, and OP(=S)(S)S, respectively.

name: Gangliosides
description: Lipid molecules composed of a glycosphingolipid (ceramide and saccharide) with one or more sialic acids linked on the sugar chain. They are usually oligoglycosylceramides derived from lactosylceramide and containing a sialic acid residue such as N-acetylneuraminic acid.

name: Alpha-amino acyl ester of carbohydrates
description: Compounds containing an amino acid esterified with a carbohydrate.

name: Triazolopyrimidines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing triazole ring fused to a pyrimidine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an alcohol or acid derivative of cholic acid.

name: Thienoimidazolidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to an imidazolidine ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Imidazolidine is 5-membered saturated ring of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions.

name: Steroid glucuronide conjugates
description: Sterol lipids containing a glucuronide moiety linked to the steroid skeleton.

name: Furoic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a furoic acid moiety, with a structure characterized by a furan ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at the C2 or C3 carbon atom.

name: Tetrapyrroles and derivatives
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing four pyrrole rings joined by one-carbon units linking position 2 of one pyrrole ring to position 5 of the next.

name: Cephams
description: Organic compounds containing the 5-thia-1-azabicyclo[4.2.0]octan-8-one nucleus.

name: Penems
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a penem moiety, which is a 2,3-didehydropenam derivative.

name: Cephamycins
description: Compounds containing a the cephalosporin (oxo-5-thia-1-azabicyclo[4.2.0]oct-2-ene-2-carboxylic acid) nucleus, with an alkyloxy group attached to the C6 carbon atom.

name: Vitamin D and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a secosteroid backbone, usually secoergostane or secocholestane.

name: Pyrethroids
description: Organic compounds similar to the pyrethrins. Some pyrethroids containing a chrysanthemic acid esterified with a cyclopentenone (pyrethrins), or with a phenoxybenzyl group.

name: Estrane steroids
description: Steroids with a structure based on the estrane skeleton.

name: Androgens and derivatives
description: 3-hydroxylated C19 steroid hormones. They are known to favor the development of masculine characteristics. They also show profound effects on scalp and body hair in humans.

name: Gluco/mineralocorticoids, progestogins and derivatives
description: Steroids with a structure based on a hydroxylated prostane moiety.

name: Cholesterols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a 3-hydroxylated cholestane core.

name: Cholesteryl esters
description: Compounds containing an esterified cholestane moiety.

name: Cyclic purine nucleotides
description: Purine nucleotides where one ribose group of the hydroxyl moiety and one phosphate group form a ring.

name: Epibatidine analogues
description: Compounds containing an epibatidine moiety, with a structure characterized by a 2-chloropyridine moiety connected to an 7-azabicyclo[2.2.1]heptane in exo position.

name: Pentoses
description: Monosaccharides in which the carbohydrate moiety contains five carbon atoms.

name: Hexoses
description: Monosaccharides in which the sugar unit is a is a six-carbon containing moeity.

name: Heptoses
description: Monosaccharides in which the sugar unit is a seven-carbon containing moeity.

name: Octoses
description: Monosaccharide compounds in which the sugar moiety is an octose (8 carbon atoms).

name: 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotides
description: Purine nucleotides in which the oxygen atoms linked to the C3 and C5 carbon atoms of the ribose moiety are both bonded the same phosphorus atom of the phosphate group.

name: Diacylglycerophosphates
description: Glycerophosphates in which the glycerol is esterified ta two positions with to fatty acids.

name: 6-oxopurines
description: Purines that carry a C=O group at position 6. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: Purine nucleotides
description: Nucleotides with a purine base attached to the ribosyl moiety.

name: Organic oxoazanium compounds
description: Organic compounds comprising the oxoazanium cation, with the formula N+=O.

name: Pyrimidine nucleotides
description: Nucleotides containing a pyrimidine base.

name: Lignan lactones
description: Lignans that contain a lactone moiety. They include 1-aryltetralin lactones, dibenzylbutyrolactone lignans, and podophyllotoxins, among others.

name: Lignan glycosides
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing a carbohydrate component glycosidically linked to a lignan moiety. They include 1-aryltetralin lactones.

name: Quinoline-3-sulfonamides
description: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by one sulfonamide group at the 3-position.

name: Organobromides
description: Compounds containing a chemical bond between a carbon atom and a bromine atom.

name: Organochlorides
description: Compounds containing a chemical bond between a carbon atom and a chlorine atom.

name: Organofluorides
description: Compounds containing a chemical bond between a carbon atom and a fluorine atom.

name: Organoiodides
description: Compounds containing a chemical bond between a carbon atom and an iodine atom.

name: Diphenylacetonitriles
description: Cyclic aromatic compounds containing a diphenylacetonitrile moiety, which consists of a diphenylmethane linked to and acetonitrile to form 2,2-diphenylacetonitrile.

name: Furanoid fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a 5-alkylfuran-2-alkanoic acid.

name: Benzonitriles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene bearing a nitrile substituent.

name: Difurocoumarocyclopentenones
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a cyclopenten-2-one ring fused to the coumarin moiety of the difurocoumarin skeleton.

name: Quinone and hydroquinone lipids
description: Lipids structurally characterized by the presence of a quinone or hydroquinone moiety.

name: Polyprenols
description: Prenols with more than 4 consecutive isoprene units.

name: Difurocoumarins
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing difurocoumarin moiety consisting of a system of two fused furan rings, which is linked to the benzene ring of a coumarin.

name: Epoxy fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing an oxirane ring as part of the aliphatic chain.

name: Diterpene lactones
description: Diterpenoids containing a lactone moiety.

name: Monosaccharides
description: Compounds containing one carbohydrate unit not glycosidically linked to another such unit, and no set of two or more glycosidically linked carbohydrate units. Monosaccharides have the general formula CnH2nOn.

name: Monosaccharide phosphates
description: Monosaccharides comprising a phosphated group linked to the carbohydrate unit.

name: Disaccharides
description: Compounds containing two carbohydrate moieties linked to each to each other through a glycosidic bond, no set of three or more glycosidically linked carbohydrate units.

name: Sesquiterpene lactones
description: Sesquiterpenoids containing a lactone ring.

name: Purine ribonucleotides
description: Nucleotides consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose to which at least one phosphate group is attached.

name: Ubiquinones
description: Coenzyme Q derivatives containing a 5, 6-dimethoxy-3-methyl(1,4-benzoquinone) moiety to which an isoprenyl group is attached at ring position 2(or 6).

name: Vitamin E compounds
description: A group of fat-soluble compounds containing or derived either from a tocopherol or a tocotrienol skeleton.

name: Vitamin K compounds
description: Quinone lipids containing a methylated naphthoquinone ring structure, and vary in the aliphatic side chain attached at the 3-position.

name: Alpha-halocarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids (or derivative thereof) containing a halogen atom bonded to the alpha carbon atom.

name: Monoterpenoids
description: Compounds containing a chain of two isoprene units.

name: Sesquiterpenoids
description: Terpenes with three consecutive isoprene units.

name: Diterpenoids
description: Terpene compounds formed by four isoprene units.

name: Sesterterpenoids
description: Terpenes composed of five consecutive isoprene units.

name: Triterpenoids
description: Terpene molecules containing 8 isoprene units.

name: Tetraterpenoids
description: Terpenoid molecules containing 10 consecutively linked isoprene units.

name: Cardenolides and derivatives
description: Steroid lactones containing a furan-2-one moiety linked to the C17 atom of a cyclopenta[a]phenanthrene derivative.

name: Bufanolides and derivatives
description: Steroid lactones containing a pyran-2-one moiety linked to the C17 atom of a cyclopenta[a]phenanthrene derivative.

name: Cardenolide glycosides and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate glycosidically bound to the cardenolide moiety.

name: Withanolides and derivatives
description: C28 steroids structurally characterized by an ergostane skeleton usually functionalized at carbons 1, 22 and 26 to form a lactone ring.

name: Dihydropyridinecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a dihydropyridine moiety bearing a carboxylic acid group.

name: Monocyclic monoterpenoids
description: Monoterpenoids containing 1 ring in the isoprene chain.

name: Bicyclic monoterpenoids
description: Monoterpenoids containing exactly 2 rings, which are fused to each other.

name: Iridoids and derivatives
description: Monoterpenes containing a skeleton structurally characterized by the presence of a cylopentane fused to a pyran ( forming a 4,7-dimethylcyclopenta[c]pyran), or a derivative where the pentane moiety is open.

name: Enynes
description: Hydrocarbons containing an alkene and an alkyne group.

name: Thiophosphoric acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where at least one R-group is an organyl group.

name: Retinoid esters
description: Ester derivatives of retinoic acid. These are obtained by formal condensation of the hydroxy group of retinol with the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid.

name: Benzofuranones
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a furanone.

name: Quinodimethanes
description: Compounds containing a cyclohexene or cyclohexadiene ring that bears two methylidene groups.

name: Triterpene glycosides
description: Triterpenoids in which an isoprene unit is glycosylated.

name: Piperidinones
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears a ketone.

name: Piperidinediones
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears two ketones.

name: Flavonoid O-glycosides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to the 2-phenylchromen-4-one flavonoid backbone.

name: Catechins
description: Compounds containing a catechin moiety, which is a 3,4-dihydro-2-chromene-3,5.7-tiol.

name: Organosulfonamides
description: Compounds containing the sulfonamide functional group, an amide of sulfonic acid with the general structure R1S(=O)2N(R2)R3 (R1=alkyl, aryl; R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Biflavonoids and polyflavonoids
description: Organic compounds containing at least two flavan/flavone units. These units are usually linked through CC or C-O-C bonds. Some examples include C2-O-C3, C2-O-C4, C3'-C3''', and C6-C8''.

name: Catechin gallates
description: Organic compounds containing a gallate moiety glycosidically linked to a catechin.

name: Bilirubins
description: Organic compounds containing a dicarboxylic acyclic tetrapyrrole derivative.

name: Epigallocatechins
description: Compounds containing epigallocatechin or a derivative. Epigallocatechin is a flavan-3-ol containing a benzopyran-3,5,7-triol linked to a 3,4,5-hydroxyphenyl moiety.

name: 1-monoacylglycerols
description: Monoacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at the 1-position.

name: Hydroxyanthraquinones
description: Compounds containing a hydroxyanthraquinone moiety, which consists of an anthracene bearing a quinone, and hydroxyl group.

name: Disaccharide phosphates
description: Disaccharides carrying  one or more phosphate group on a sugar unit.

name: Anthraquinone glycosides
description: Organic compounds containing an anthraquinone moiety glycosidically bound to a carbohydrate moiety.

name: Cyclosporins
description: Cyclic depsipeptides containing the cyclosporin backbone.

name: 2-monoacylglycerols
description: Monoacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at the 2-position.

name: Tetrahydrofuran lignans
description: Lignans with a structure that contains a tetrahydrofuran ring that arises from the joining of the two phenylpropanoid units.

name: Carbonyl hydrates
description: Organic compounds containing two hydroxyl groups attached to a carbon atom.

name: Retinoids
description: Oxygenated derivatives of 3,7-dimethyl-1-(2,6,6-trimethylcyclohex-1-enyl)nona-1,3,5,7-tetraene and derivatives thereof.

name: Rotenoids
description: Phenolic compounds containing a cis-fused tetrahydrochromeno[3,4-b]chromene nucleus. Many rotenoids contain an additional ring, e.g. rotenone. They are isoflavonoids characterized by the presence of an extra carbon atom in an additional heterocyclic ring.

name: Pterocarpans
description: Benzo-pyrano-furano-benzene compounds, containing the  6H-[1]benzofuro[3,2-c]chromene skeleton. They are derivatives of isoflavonoids.

name: Arylnaphthalene lignans
description: Lignans containing the arylnaphthalene skeleton, especially 9-(2H-1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl)-1H,3H-naphtho[2,3-c]furan-1-one or a derivative thereof. Arylnaphthalene lignans occur in nature and exhibit diverse biological activities.

name: Carbonic acid diesters
description: Compounds comprising the carbonic acid diester functional group.

name: Isoflavans
description: Polycyclic compounds with a structure based on the 3-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton.

name: Dibenzylbutyrolactone lignans
description: Lignan compounds containing a 3,4-dibenzyloxolan-2-one moiety.

name: Neoflavonoids
description: Compounds with a structure based on the 4-phenylchromene backbone.

name: Flavones
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on the backbone of 2-phenylchromen-4-one (2-phenyl-1-benzopyran-4-one).

name: Purine ribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Nucleotides consisting of a purine base linked to a ribose to which one monophosphate group is attached.

name: Purine ribonucleoside diphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with diphosphate group linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Purine ribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with a triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside diphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribonucleotides with diphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Dibenzocyclooctadiene lignans
description: Compounds containing a dibenzocyclooctadiene moiety, which consists of two hydroxylated benzene connected by a cycloheptene ring.

name: Phenanthrolines
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing the phenanthroline skeleton, which is a derivative of phenanthrene, and consists of two pyridine rings non-linearly joined by a benzene ring.

name: Purine ribonucleoside polyphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with polyphosphate (with 4 or more phosphate) group linked to the ribose moiety.

name: Benzopyrazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyrazole ring. Pyrazole is a 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers.

name: Chalcones and dihydrochalcones
description: Organic compounds containing 1,3-Diphenylpropenone (benzylideneacetophenone), ArCH=CH(=O)Ar, or its derivatives formed by substitution.

name: Aurone flavonoids
description: Flavonoids containing a 2-Benzylidene-1-benzofuran-3-one based core. Aurone flavonoids provide the bright yellow color of some important ornamental flowers, such as snapdragon (Antirrhinum majus).

name: Flavanones
description: Compounds containing a flavan-3-one moiety, with a structure characterized by a 2-phenyl-3,4-dihydro-2H-1-benzopyran bearing a ketone at the carbon C3.

name: Homoisoflavones
description: Homoisoflavonoids with a structure based on the chromone system. Chromone is a bicyclic compound consisting of a 1-benzopyran, which bears a ketone group at the 4-position.

name: Naphthofurans
description: Compounds containing a furan ring fused to a naphthalene moiety. Furan is a 5 membered- ring aromatic ring with four carbon and one oxygen atoms. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Serotonins
description: Compounds containing a serotonin moiety, which consists of an indole that bears an aminoethyl a position 2 and a hydroxyl group at position 5.

name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphocholine.

name: Naphthopyrans
description: Compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a naphthalene moiety. Furan is a 6 membered-ring non-aromatic ring with five carbon and one oxygen atoms. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Naphthopyranones
description: Compounds containing a naphthopyran skeleton where a ring carbon bears a carboxylic acid group. Naphthtopyran is made up of the pyran ring fused to a naphthalene ring system.

name: 1,2-diacylglycerols
description: Diacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at positions 1 and 2.

name: Depsides and depsidones
description: Polycyclic compounds that is either a polyphenolic compound composed of two or more monocyclic aromatic units linked by an ester bond (depside), or a compound containing the depsidone structure (depsidone).

name: Naphthopyranone glycosides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to a naphthopyranone moiety.

name: 1,3-diacylglycerols
description: Diacylglycerols containing a glycerol acylated at positions 1 and 3.

name: Isochromanequinones
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an isochromanequinone, which is structurally characterized by a quinone fused to an isochromane, and forming a naphtho[2,3-c]pyran-6,9-dione skeleton.

name: Tropones
description: Compounds containing a tropone ring, which is a cycloheptatrienone ring bearing a ketone group.

name: Biopterins and derivatives
description: Coenzymes containing a 2-amino-pteridine-4-one derivative. They are mainly synthesized in several parts of the body, including the pineal gland.

name: Long-chain fatty acyl CoAs
description: Acyl CoAs where the group acylated to the coenzyme A moiety is a long aliphatic chain of 13 to 21 carbon atoms.

name: Carbonic acid monoesters
description: Compounds comprising the carbonic acid monoester functional group.

name: Acetals
description: Compounds having the structure R2C(OR')2 ( R' not Hydrogen) and thus diethers of geminal diols. Originally, the term was confined to derivatives of aldehydes (one R = H), but it now applies equally to derivatives of ketones (neither R = H ). Mixed acetals have different R' groups.

name: Carboxylic acid imides
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing two carbonyl groups where the carbon atoms are both linked to the same nitrogen atom.

name: N-substituted carboxylic acid imides
description: Compounds comprising an N-substituted carboxylic acid imide group, with the general structure R1N(C(R2)=O)C(R3)=O (R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl; R1=Anything but H).

name: N-unsubstituted carboxylic acid imides
description: Compounds comprising an N-unsubstituted carboxylic acid imide group, with the general structure R1N(C(R2)=O)C(R3)=O (R1,R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Acyl cyanides
description: Organic compounds containing the cyanide functional group attached to an alkyl chain through an ester bond.

name: Secondary alcohols
description: Compounds containing a secondary alcohol functional group, with the general structure HOC(R)(R') (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Primary carboxylic acid amides
description: Compounds comprising primary carboxylic acid amide functional group, with the general structure RC(=O)NH2.

name: Secondary carboxylic acid amides
description: Compounds containing a secondary carboxylic acid amide functional group, with the general structure RC(=O)N(R')H (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Tertiary carboxylic acid amides
description: Compounds containing an amide derivative of carboxylic acid, with the general structure RN(R1)C(R2)=O (R1-R2 any atom but H).

name: Thiohemiaminal derivatives
description: Compounds containing the thiohemiaminal group with the general structure R1SC(R2)(R3)N(R4)R5 (R1-R5=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Carboxylic acid amide acetals
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives two hydroxyl groups attached to a carbon atom, which in turn is linked to a nitrogen atom(substituted or not).

name: Organic diazonium salts
description: Organic compounds comprising the diazonium functional group, with the general structure R-N=N+.

name: Long-chain ceramides
description: Ceramides bearing a long chain fatty acid.

name: Tertiary alcohols
description: Compounds in which a hydroxy group, -OH, is attached to a saturated carbon atom R3COH (R not H ).

name: Organic thiocarbonic acid derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the thiocarbonic acid structure or a derivative thereof.

name: Ketimines
description: Organic compounds bearing the ketimine functional group, with the general structure R2C=NR' ( R is not a hydrogen ).

name: Tropolones
description: Compounds containing tropone ring with a hydroxyl group at ring position 2.

name: Aminocyclitol glycosides
description: Organic compounds containing an amicocyclitol moiety glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety. There are two major classes of aminoglycosides containing a 2-streptamine core. They are called 4,5- and 4,6-disubstituted 2-deoxystreptamines.

name: Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphates
description: Phosphatidylinositol bisphosphates in which the two phosphate groups are at C-4 and C-5 of the inositol moiety.

name: 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamines
description: Glycerophoethanolamines in which the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position, and linked at position 3 to a phosphoethanolamine.

name: Acyclic allenes
description: Acyclic hydrocarbons (and by extension, derivatives formed by substitution) having two double bonds from one carbon atom to two others.

name: Cyclic allenes
description: Cyclic hydrocarbons (and by extension, derivatives formed by substitution) having two double bonds from one carbon atom to two others.

name: 1-acyl-glycerol-3-phosphoserines
description: Monoacylglycerol-3-phosphoserines with a fatty acyl chain linked to the O1-atom of the glycerol moiety.

name: Monoacylglycerophosphates
description: Monacylglyerophosphates in which the glycerol moiety is esterified at only position, and is attached to a phosphate group.

name: 1-acylglycerol-3-phosphates
description: Lysophosphatidic acids where the glycerol is esterified with a fatty acid at O-1 position.

name: Cucurbitacins
description: Polycyclic compounds containing the tetracyclic cucurbitane nucleus skeleton, 19-(10->9b)-abeo-10alanost-5-ene (also known as 9b-methyl-19-nor lanosta-5-ene), with a variety of oxygenation functionalities at different positions.

name: Cucurbitacin glycosides
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a carbohydrate derivative glycosidically linked to a curcubitane nucleus.

name: Steroid esters
description: Compounds containing a steroid moiety which bears a carboxylic acid ester group.

name: Sulfated steroids
description: Sterol lipids containing a sulfate group attached to the steroid skeleton.

name: Aminotriazines
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a triazine ring.

name: Aminopyrazines
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a pyrazine ring.

name: Furanoid amino acids and derivatives
description: Sugar amino acids containing a furan ring.

name: Pyranoid amino acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a (hydro)pyran ring bearing unprotected amino and carboxylic acid functionalities.

name: Bicyclic amino acids and derivatives
description: Sugar amino acids in which the amino acid is attached to or partly borne within a bicyclic ring system.

name: Spirostanes and derivatives
description: Steroidal alkaloids with a structure containing a spirostane skeleton. Spirostanes are 16b,22:22,26-diepoxycholestanes, or 22,26-epoxyfurostans. The sixth ring so formed is known as ring F. Chemically, the spiro centre at C-22 has the character of an internal acetal derived from a 16b, 26-dihydroxycholestan-22-one.

name: Furostanes and derivatives
description: Compounds containing or derived from the steroid parent furostane, which is a 16b,22-epoxycholestane derivative, the extra ring being labeled as\nring E.

name: Furospirostanes and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic steroids containing a furospirostane moiety, which a skeleton characterized by the presence of a 1,6-dioxaspiro[4.4]nonane ring system and an androstane moiety.

name: Solanidines and derivatives
description: Steroids with a structure based on the solanidane skeleton.  Solanidane arises from the conversion of a cholestane side-chain into a bicyclic system.

name: Spirosolanes and derivatives
description: Steroidal alkaloids with a structure containing a spirosolane skeleton. Siporosolane is a polycyclic compound that is characterized by a 1-oxa-6-azaspiro[4.5]decane moiety where the oxolane ring is fused to a docosahydronaphth[2,1:4',5']indene ring system. Spirosolane arises from the conversion of a cholestane side-chain into a bicyclic system containing a piperidine and a tetrahydrofuran ring.

name: Gingerols
description: Compounds containing a gingerol moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl group substituted at the C6 carbon atom by a 5-hydroxy-alkane-3-one.

name: Gingerdiones
description: Compounds containing a gingerdione moiety, which is structurally characterized by a 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl group substituted at the C6 carbon atom by an alkane-2,4-dione.

name: Shogaols
description: Ginger derivatives containing a shogaol moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing a dec-4-en-3-one moiety, a methoxyphenyl group, a hydroxyl group and at positions 1, 3, and 4, respectively.

name: Paradols
description: Compounds containing a paradol moiety, which is consists of a benzene ring with a decan-3-one moiety, a methoxyl group, and a hydroxyl group at positions 1,3, and 4 respectively.

name: Hydrolyzable tannins
description: Tannins with a structure characterized by either of the following models. In model 1, the structure contains galloyl units (in some cases, shikimic acid units) that are linked to diverse polyol carbohydrate-, catechin-, or triterpenoid units. In model 2, contains at least two galloyl units C-C coupled to each other, and do not contain a glycosidically linked catechin unit.

name: Complex tannins
description: Tannins made of a catechin bound to a gallotannin or elagitannin.

name: Beta hydroxy acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid substituted with a hydroxyl group on the C3 carbon atom.

name: Hydroxyquinolones
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety bearing a hydroxyl group and a ketone. Quinoline or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine.

name: Hydroquinolines
description: Derivatives of  quinoline in which in which at least one double bond in the quinoline moiety are reduced by adding two hydrogen atoms.

name: Hydroquinolones
description: Compounds containing a hydrogenated quinoline bearing a ketone group.

name: Oxaborine derivatives
description: Compounds containing a six-member aliphatic heterocycle made up of one oxygen atom, a boron atom, and three carbon atoms.

name: Fatty alcohol esters
description: Ester derivatives of a fatty alcohol.

name: Wax esters
description: Mixtures of long-chain apolar lipids. They are usually esters of an alcohol other than glycerol and a long chain acid.

name: Oxepanes
description: Compounds containing an oxepane ring, which is a seven-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one oxygen and six carbon atoms.

name: Dioxopiperazines
description: Compounds containing a piperazine ring bearing two ketone groups. These include the alkaloid class of naturally occurring 2,5-dioxopiperazines.

name: Thiodioxopiperazines
description: Compounds containing a piperazine ring which bears two ketone groups and a sulfanyl group.

name: Pyrroloindoles
description: Compounds containing a pyrroloindole moiety, which is a tricyclic heterocycle which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to an indole. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Indole is a bicyclic  compound consisting of a six-membered benzene ring fused to a five-membered nitrogen-containing pyrrole ring.

name: Pyrroloquinolines
description: Compounds containing a pyrroloquinoline moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a quinoline.

name: Furanochromones
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a 1-benzopyran-4-one ring system.

name: Benzochromones
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to the benzene moiety of chromone (1,4-benzopyrone).

name: Flavonoid C-glycosides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is C-glycosidically linked to the 2-phenylchromen-4-one flavonoid backbone.

name: Coumarin glycosides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically bound to a coumarin moiety.

name: Semilysobisphosphatidic acids
description: Bisphosphatidic acid analogues with three moles of fatty acid per mole of lipid.

name: Benzoylindoles
description: Organic compounds containing an indole attached to a benzoyl moiety through the acyl group.

name: Diterpene glycosides
description: Diterpenoids in which an isoprene unit is glycosylated.

name: Steviol glycosides
description: Prenol lipids containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically linked to a steviol (a diterpenoid based on a 13-Hydroxykaur-16-en-18-oic acid) moiety.

name: Colensane and clerodane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the clerodane or the colensane skeleton. Clerodanes arise from labdanes by two methyl migrations.

name: Dalbergiones
description: Quinone derivatives containing a dalbergione moiety, which consists of a 1-4 quinone conjugated to a phenyl group  at ring carbon 2.

name: Furanoflavones
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a flavan-3-one.

name: Dolabellane and neodolabellane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the dolabellane skeleton (3a,6,10-trimethyl-1-(propan-2-yl)-cyclopenta[11]annulene) or the neodolabellane skeleton.

name: Kavalactones
description: Lactones, which is structurally characterized by a benzene ring and a pyranone moiety, linked to each other to form a 4-methoxy-6-(2-phenylethyl)-2H-pyran-2-one skeleton.

name: Pyrroloacridines
description: Compounds containing a pyrroloacridine moiety, which is a tetracyclic heterocycle which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to an acridine.

name: Pyridoacridines
description: Compounds containing a pyridoacridine ring system, which consists of a pyridine fused to an acridine.

name: Pyridinium derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyridinium ring, which is the cationic form of pyridine.

name: Fatty acyl glycosides
description: Compounds containing fatty acyl chain linked to a carbohydrate moiety through a glycosidic bond. Fatty acyl glycosides are composed of a glycosyl moiety (one or several units) linked to one hydroxyl group of a fatty alcohol or of a phosphorylated alcohol (phosphoprenols), a hydroxy fatty acid or to one carboxyl group of a fatty acid (ester linkage) or to an amino alcohol.

name: Gibberellins
description: Diterpenoids containing the gibberellane skeleton ((8S)-4,4,8-trimethyl-13-methylidenetetracyclo[10.2.1.0^{1,9}.0^{3,8}]pentadecane), an aliphatic four-ring system.

name: Guaianolides and derivatives
description: Diterpene lactones with a structure characterized by the presence of a gamma-lactone fused to a guaiane, forming 3,6,9-trimethyl-azuleno[4,5-b]furan-2-one or a derivative.

name: Germacranolides and derivatives
description: Sesquiterpene lactones with a structure based on the germacranolide skeleton, characterized by a gamma lactone fused to a 1,7-dimethylcyclodec-1-ene moiety.

name: Eudesmanolides, secoeudesmanolides, and derivatives
description: Terpenoids with a structure based on the eudesmanolide (a 3,5a,9-trimethyl-naphtho[1,2-b]furan-2-one derivative) or secoeudesmanolide (a 3,6-dimethyl-5-(pentan-2-yl)-1-benzofuran-2-one derivative) skeleton.

name: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Isoquinoline alkaloids with a skeleton deriving from lycorine, norbelladine, homolycorine, hemanthamine, crinine, tazettine, montanine, plicamine, galanthindole, galanthamine, gracilline, among others. Amaryllidaceae Alkaloids represent a large group of biogenetically related isoquinoline alkaloids that are found exclusively in plants belonging to this family of Amaryllidaceae. This group of alkaloids is also derived from two tyrosine units which combine, with loss of one carbon atom, to give a benzylphenylethylamine precursor unit, e.g. Norbelladine, which by various oxidative cyclisation processes, prominent among which are phenol oxidative coupling reactions, can give rise to the nine major skeletal groups.

name: Illudanes and illudins
description: Sesquiterpenoids containing either the illudane moiety (based on a 3,6,6,7b-tetramethyl-decahydro-1H-cyclobuta[e]indene ring system), the illudin moiety (2',2',4',6'-tetramethyl-octahydrospiro[cyclopropane-1,5'-indene]), or a derivative thereof.

name: O-quinodimethanes
description: Compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to two methylidene groups at carbon atoms 1 and 2, respectively.

name: Guanidinobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Aromatic compounds containing a guanidine group linked to the benzene ring of a benzoic acid (or a derivative thereof).

name: Dihydrofuranoquinolines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure based on the dihydrofuranoquinoline skeleton.

name: Aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on an aromadendrane (a cyclopropa[e]azulene derivative) skeleton. Some aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids are found in essential oils. Certain aromadendrane Sesquiterpenoids from the Leaves of Xylopia brasiliensis were found to possess antifungal activities.

name: Erythrina alkaloids
description: Organic compounds with a structure based on a backbone containing a indole-6-ol sharing its nitrogen atom with an isoquinoline ring system.

name: Oxamorphinans
description: Polycyclic compounds with a four-ring skeleton with three condensed six-member rings forming a partially hydrogenated naphthopyran moiety, one of which is aromatic while the two others are alicyclic.

name: Yohimbine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids containing the pentacyclic yohimban skeleton. The Yohimbinoid alkaloids contain a carbocyclic ring E arising through C-17 to C-18 bond formation in a corynantheine precursor.

name: Zearalenones
description: Macrolides which contains a fourteen-member lactone fused to 1,3-dihydroxybenzene.

name: Trichothecenes
description: Sesquiterpene mycotoxins structurally characterized by the presence of an epoxide ring and a benzopyran derivative with a variant number of hydroxyl, acetyl, or other substituents. The most important structural features causing the biological activities of trichothecenes are the 12,13-epoxy ring, the presence of hydroxyl or acetyl groups at appropriate positions on the trichothecene nucleus and the structure and position of the side-chain.

name: Epipolythiodioxopiperazines
