description: Compounds containing an epipolythiodioxopiperazine moiety, which consists of a 2,3-dithia-5,7-diazabicyclo[2.2.2]octane-6,8-dione ring system. One distinct characteristics of Epipolythiodioxopiperazines is the presence of unique di- or polysulfide bridges.

name: Ajmaline-sarpagine alkaloids
description: Organic compounds containing either of the ajmalan, sarpagan skeleton, or derivative thereof. The Sarpagine (Akuammidine) group, based on the sarpagan nucleus, arises from bond formation between C-16 and C-5 of the corynantheine precursor.  Ajmaline alkaloids are based on a 17,19-secoyohimban skeleton (oxayohimban) which is invariably present as an ether.

name: Sparteine, lupanine, and related alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on either sparteine, lupanine, or derivatives thereof. These are tetracyclic compounds made of two fused quinolizidine ring systems.

name: Oxocins
description: Compounds containing an oxocin ring, which is a eight-member unsaturated aromatic ring containing one oxygen atom and seven carbon atoms.

name: Imidazopyrimidines
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a pyrimidine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Pyrrolotriazines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolotriazine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a triazine ring. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Triazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and three nitrogen centers.

name: Pyrrolopyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolopyrimidine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyrimidine. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Saxitoxins, gonyautoxins, and derivatives
description: Compounds with a structure based on a 2,6-diamino-4-methyl-pyrrolo[1,2-c]purin-10-ol skeleton.

name: Kainoids
description: Non-proteigenous amino acids with a structure characterized by the presence of a pyrrolidine ring bearing two dicarboxylic acid groups.

name: Organic pyrophosphates
description: Organic compounds containing the pyrophosphate oxoanion, with the structure OP([O-])(=O)OP(O)([O-])=O.

name: Quinuclidones
description: Compounds containing a quinuclidine moiety which bears a ketone group.

name: Spironolactones and derivatives
description: Steroid lactones with a structure based on the spironolactone skeleton.

name: Ciguatera toxins
description: Lipid-soluble polyether compounds consisting of 13 to 14 rings fused by ether linkages into a most rigid ladder-like structure.

name: Acridones
description: Acridines containing a ketone group attached to the C9 carbon atom of the acridine moiety.

name: Glycosyl-amino acids
description: Compounds consisting of saccharide linked through a glycosyl linkage (O-, N-, or S-) to an amino acid.

name: Peptidomimetics
description: Compounds containing non-peptidic structural elements that is capable of mimicking or antagonizing the biological action(s) of a natural parent peptide.

name: Phenylphosphines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phenylphosphine, which consists of phosphine substituent bound to a phenyl group.

name: Furofurans
description: Organic compounds containing a two furan rings fused to each other. Furan is a five-membered aromatic ring with four carbon atoms and one oxygen atom.

name: Furopyrans
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a pyran ring. Furan is a five-membered aromatic ring with four carbon atoms and one oxygen atom. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds.

name: Isoindoles and derivatives
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an isoindole moiety, which is structurally characterized by a cyclohexadiene fused to a pyrrole ring.

name: Isoindolones
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds that an isoindole bearing a ketone.

name: Cytochalasans
description: Fungal metabolites structurally characterized by the presence of an isoindolone nucleus fused to a macrocyclic ring, which can either a lactone, as in cytochalasin B, a carbonate, as in cytochalasin E, or a carbocycle, as in cytochalasin D,  H, and K.

name: Oxadiazoles
description: Organic compounds containing an oxadiazole ring, which is a five-member aromatic heterocycle with two nitrogen atoms, an oxygen atom, and a carbon atom.

name: Hopanoids
description: Terpenoids containing hopane skeleton(A'-Neogammacerane), a pentacyclic structure with four cyclohexane rings and one cyclopentane ring (and often, a side chain emerging from C30).

name: Polyterpenoids
description: Terpenoids consisting of more than eight isoprene units.

name: Isoflavanones
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an isoflavan skeleton which bears a ketone at position C4.

name: Isoflavanols
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a hydroxylated isoflavan skeleton.

name: M-terphenyls
description: Terphenyls with a structure containing the 1,3-diphenylbenzene skeleton.

name: Carbonyl compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a carbonyl group, with the general structure RC(=O)R', where R=organyl, R'=H, N, O, organyl group or halide group.

name: Thienopyrroles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a pyrrole ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom.

name: Pyrrolothiazoles
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolothiazole moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a thiazole ring. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Thiazole is a 6-membered ring that contains both sulfur and nitrogen.

name: Tetrazolidines
description: Organic compounds containing a tetrazolidine ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a one carbon atom.

name: Phenyltetrazolines and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a phenyltetrazoline skeleton, which consists of a tetrazoline bound to a phenyl group.

name: Flavonolignans
description: Non-conventional lignans that derived from flavonoids. They are characterized by a p-dioxin ring substituted at one carbon atom by a C3C6 (phenylpropan) group and fused to the B-ring of the 2-phenylchromene moiety.

name: Bromodiphenyl ethers
description: Compounds that contain two benzene groups linked to each other via an ether bond, and where at least one ring is substituted with a bromo group.

name: Acetanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetamide group conjugated to a phenyl group.

name: Thiophenols
description: Compounds containing a thiophenol ring, which a phenol derivative obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from the hydroxyl group (attached to the benzene) by a sulfur atom.

name: Pyrenes
description: Compounds containing a pyrene moiety, which consists four fused benzene rings, resulting in a flat aromatic system.

name: 1,3-aminoalcohols
description: Organic compounds containing an alkyl chain with an amine group bound to the C1 atom and an alcohol group bound to the C3 atom.

name: Trioxanes
description: Compounds containing a six-member aliphatic saturated heterocycle made up of three oxygen atoms and three carbon atoms.

name: Trioxolanes
description: Compounds containing a five-member aliphatic saturated heterocycle made up of three oxygen atoms and two carbon atoms.

name: Phenoxazines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a phenoxazine moiety, which is a linear tricyclic system that consists of a two benzene rings joined by a 1,4-oxazine ring.

name: Naphthyridines
description: Compounds containing a naphthyridine moiety, a naphthalene in which a carbon atom has been replaced by a nitrogen in each of the two rings. The naphthyridine skeleton can also be described as an assembly two fused pyridine rings, which do not share their nitrogen atom.

name: Naphthyridine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a naphthyridine moiety, where one of the ring atoms bears a carboxylic acid group.

name: Pyridopyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyridopyrimidine, which consists of a pyridine fused to a pyrimidine. Pyridine is 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and a nitrogen atom. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Pyridinesulfonamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted by one or more sulfonamide groups.

name: Trithianes
description: Organic compounds containing a six-member aliphatic saturated heterocycle made up of three sulfur atoms and three carbon atoms.

name: Dithianes
description: Compounds containing a dithiane moiety, which is composed of a cyclohexane core structure wherein two methylene units are replaced by sulfur centres.

name: Oxirane carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an oxirane ring bearing a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Pyrrolocarbazoles
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolocarbazole moiety, which is a tetracyclic heterocycle which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a carbazole.

name: Indolocarbazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing an indole fused to a carbazole.

name: Indole ribonucleosides and ribonucleotides
description: Compounds in which the C-1 of a ribosyl (or deoxyribosyl) moiety is linked to the N1-position of an indole. Nucleotides have a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon of the ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety.

name: Naphthalenecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a naphthalene moiety, which bears a carboxylic acid group or a derivative at one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: P-quinodimethanes
description: Compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to two methylidene groups at carbon atoms 1 and 4, respectively..

name: Phthalides
description: Compounds containing a 3-hydrocarbylidene-2-benzofuran-1(3H)-one moiety,.

name: Benzoxathioles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxathiole ring (a five-membered ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one sulfur atom).

name: Azetidinecarboxylic acids or derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof) attached to an azetidine ring.

name: Aziridinecarboxylic acids or derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group(or a derivative thereof) attached to an aziridine ring.

name: Beta amino acids and derivatives
description: Amino acids having a (-NH2) group attached to the beta carbon atom.

name: Delta amino acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group and an amino group at the C5 carbon atom.

name: Gamma amino acids and derivatives
description: Amino acids having a (-NH2) group attached to the gamma carbon atom.

name: Thiazetidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated four-member ring with two carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen.

name: Beta sultams
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfonamide group in which the N-S bond is part of a four member ring.

name: Gamma sultams
description: Organic compounds containing a gamma-sultam moiety, a five-member cyclic sulfonamide, containing the NS bond, and three carbon atoms.

name: Thiazinanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated six-member ring with four carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen.

name: Delta sultams
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a 1,2-thiazinane-1,1-dione moiety.

name: Gamma sultones
description: Organic compounds containing a gamma-sultone, a Intramolecular cyclic ester of hydroxy sulfonic acid, with a SO ring bond, and three ring carbon atoms.

name: Oxathianes
description: Compounds containing an oxathiane moiety, which consists of a saturated aliphatic six-member ring with one oxygen atom, a sulfur atom, and four carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxathiane, 1,3-oxathiane,and 1,4-oxathiane.

name: Isocoumarins and derivatives
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an isochromane which bears a ketone at the carbon C1.

name: Sulfinylbenzimidazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a sulfinyl group attached at the position 2 of a benzimidazole moiety.

name: Biphenylcarbonitriles
description: Organic compounds containing an acetonitrile with one hydrogen replaced by a biphenyl group.

name: Halopyrimidines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a halogen atom linked to a pyrimidine ring. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Thianes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated six-member ring with five carbon atoms and one sulfur atom.

name: Thiopyrans
description: Compounds containing a six-member aliphatic heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and five carbon atoms.

name: Thienoquinolines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a quinoline. Quinoline or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine.

name: 1,2-aminoalcohols
description: Organic compounds containing an alkyl chain with an amine group bound to the C1 atom and an alcohol group bound to the C2 atom.

name: Macrolide lactams
description: Cyclic polyketides containing  both a cyclic amide and a cyclic ester group.

name: Pyrrolidine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid or a derivative thereof. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside bisphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety.

name: Phenanthroindolizidines
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing the phenanthroindolizidine skeleton, which is structurally characterized by an indolizidine and a phenanthrene, where the indolizidine is fused to the second benzene ring of a phenanthrene.

name: Benzoquinolines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to a quinoline ring system.

name: Protoberberine alkaloids and derivatives
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on a protoberberine moiety, which consists of a 5,6-dihydrodibenzene moiety fused to a quinolizinium and forming 5,6-Dihydrodibenzo(a,g)quinolizinium skeleton.

name: Benzoxepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an oxepine ring (an unsaturated seven-membered heterocycle with one oxygen atom replacing a carbon atom).

name: Anthracenecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof) attached to an anthracene ring system.

name: Pyridoisoindoles
description: Compounds containing a pyridoisoindole, which consists of a pyridine fused to an isoindole.

name: Alpha carbolines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyrido[2,3-b]indole core (which is a pyridine fused to an indole).

name: Beta carbolines
description: Compounds containing a 9H-pyrido[3,4-b]indole moiety.

name: Gamma carbolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a gamma-carbazole(5H-pyrido[4,3-b]indole) moiety, with a structure characterized by the presence of pyridine fused to the pyrrole ring of an indole.

name: Aminobenzamides
description: Organic compounds containing a benzamide moiety with an amine group attached to the benzene ring.

name: Furopyrroles
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing a furan ring fused to a pyrrole ring. Furan is a five-membered aromatic ring with four carbon atoms and one oxygen atom. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom.

name: Thiazinanethiones
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thioketone group conjugated to a saturated six-member ring with four carbon atoms, one sulfur atom, and one nitrogen.

name: Triazinones
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring which bears a ketone group a carbon atom.

name: Pyrimidinethiones
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidine ring that bears a thioketone. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Triazinethiones
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring which bears a thioketone group.

name: Thiazolidinethiones
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazolidinethione ring which bears one thioketone group.

name: Aminopyridazines
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a pyridazine ring.

name: Aminobenzenesulfonamides
description: Organic compounds containing a benzenesulfonamide moiety with an amine group attached to the benzene ring.

name: Nitropyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidine ring which bears a nitro group. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Thienothiazines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a thiazine. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Thiazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon, one nitrogen and one sulfur atoms.

name: Thienothiazoles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a thiazole. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Thiazole is a 6-membered ring that contains both sulfur and nitrogen.

name: Benzoxadiazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxadiazole ring (a five-membered ring with two carbon atoms, one nitrogen atom, and one oxygen atom).

name: Oxatriazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxatriazole moiety, which consists of an unsaturated aliphatic five-member ring with one oxygen atom, three nitrogen, one carbon atom, and two double bonds. Isomers  of oxatriazole include 1,2,3,4-oxatriazole, and 1,2,3,5-oxatriazole.

name: Oxadiazolidines
description: Organic compounds containing an oxadiazole ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle with two nitrogen atoms, an oxygen atom, and two carbon atoms.

name: Tetrahydropyridines
description: Derivatives of  pyridine in which two double bonds in the pyridine moiety are reduced by adding four hydrogen atoms.

name: N-phenylureas
description: Compounds containing a N-phenylurea moiety, which is structurally characterized by a phenyl group linked to one nitrogen atom of a urea group.

name: Aminothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to a thiophene ring.

name: Polyprenyl quinols
description: Compounds containing a polyisoprene chain attached to a quinol(hydroquinone) at the second ring position.

name: Peptoids
description: Peptidomimetics made of N-substituted amino acids, in which the side chains are attached to the nitrogen atom of the peptide backbone, rather than to the alpha-carbons. Alpha-peptoids (commonly referred to as peptoids) are N-substituted glycines. But in general, this class also extends to oligo- or polymers of beta-, gamma-, delta peptoid analogues of amino acids.

name: Peptoid-peptide hybrids
description: Compounds containing a peptoid-peptide backbone, which consists alternating amino acid and n-substituted amino acids linked to each other by a peptide bond.

name: Pyridoxines
description: Pyridoxal derivatives in which the carbaldehyde group at position 2 of the pyridoxal moiety is replaced by a hydroxymethyl group.

name: Imidazole-pyrrole oligo- and polyamides
description: Polycyclic aromatic peptidomimetics consisting of alternating pyrrole and imidazole rings connected by a carboxamide group to form a N-(1H-pyrrol-3-yl)-1H-imidazole-2-carboxamide moiety.

name: Depsipeptides
description: Natural or synthetic compounds having sequences of amino and hydroxy carboxylic acid residues (usually -amino and -hydroxy acids), commonly but not necessarily regularly alternating.

name: Thienopyrans
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a pyran ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds.

name: Pyridoxamines
description: Pyridoxal derivatives in which the carbaldehyde moiety is substituted at position 2 by an amine.

name: Oxolanes
description: Organic compounds containing an oxolane (tetrahydrofuran) ring, which is a saturated aliphatic five-member ring containing one oxygen and five carbon atoms.

name: Dibenzylbutane lignans
description: Lignan compounds containing a 2,3-dibenzylbutane moiety.

name: Furofuran lignans
description: Lignans with a structure based on 1,4-diphenyl-hexahydrofuro[3,4-c]furan skeleton.

name: Benzoxazolones
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxazole ring (a five-member aliphatic ring with three carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one nitrogen atom) bearing a ketone group.

name: Piperidinecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Pyrrolidinylpyridines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidinylpyridine ring system, which consists of a pyrrolidine ring linked to a pyridine ring.

name: Pyridinylpiperazines
description: Compounds containing a pyridinylpiperazine skeleton, which consists of a pyridine linked (not fused) to a piperazine by a bond by a single bond that is not part of a ring.

name: Bipyrimidines and oligopyrimidines
description: Organic compounds containing two or more pyrimidine rings directly linked to each other. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Imidazodiazepines
description: Organic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a diazepine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Diazepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of five carbon and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Furanones
description: Compounds containing a furan ring bearing a ketone group.

name: Dihydrofurans
description: Compounds containing a dihydrofuran moiety, which is a furan derivative with only one double bond.

name: Phenylpiperazines
description: Compounds containing a phenylpiperazine skeleton, which consists of a piperazine bound to a phenyl group.

name: Dioxolopyrans
description: Compounds containing a dioxolopyran moiety, which consists of a dioxole ring fused to a pyran ring.

name: Tricarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids containing exactly three carboxyl groups.

name: Isosorbides
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing an isosorbide(1,4-Dianhydrosorbitol) moiety, which consists of two -oxolan-3-ol rings.

name: Dibenzoxepines
description: Compounds containing a dibenzoxepine moiety, which consists of two benzene connected by an oxazepine ring.

name: Heterocyclic fatty acids
description: Fatty acids containing a heterocyclic attached to the acyl chain.

name: Pyrroloazepines
description: Compounds containing a pyrroloazepine moiety, which is a bicyclic heterocycle which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to an azepine. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Azepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of six carbon and one nitrogen atom.

name: Nitrobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a nitrobenzoic acid moiety, which consists of a benzene ring bearing both a carboxylic acid group and a nitro group on two different ring carbon atoms.

name: Cyclic depsipeptides
description: Natural or synthetic compounds having sequences of amino and hydroxy carboxylic acid residues (usually -amino and -hydroxy acids) connected in a ring. The residues are commonly but not necessarily regularly alternating.

name: Cyclic peptides
description: Compounds containing a cyclic moiety bearing a peptide backbone.

name: Imidazole ribonucleosides and ribonucleotides
description: Organic compounds in which the C-1 of a ribosyl moiety is N-linked to an imidazole ring. Nucleotides have a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon of the ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety. This class does not contain benzimidazole nucleosides and nucleotides.

name: Purinethiones
description: Purines in which the purine moiety bears a thioketone.

name: Piperazinoazepines
description: Compounds containing a piperazinoazepine skeleton, which consists of an azepine ring fused to a piperazine.

name: Imidazotetrazines
description: Organic polycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a tetrazine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Tetrazine is a six-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a two carbon atoms.

name: Mutilin derivatives
description: Tricyclic diterpenoids structurally characterized by the presence of a 1-oxo-decahydro-3a,9-propanocyclopenta[8]annulene skeleton.

name: Pleuromutilin and derivatives
description: Mutilins with a hydroxyacetate derivative attached to the C8 carbon atom of the cyclopenta[8]annulene moiety.

name: Triquinane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the triquinane backbone.

name: Pyrazolotriazines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazolotriazine skeleton, which consists of a pyrazole fused to a triazine. Pyrazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers. Triazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and three nitrogen centers.

name: Pyrazolylpyridines
description: Compounds containing a pyrazolylpyridine skeleton, which consists of a pyrazole linked (not fused) to a pyridine by a bond.

name: Thiazolecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazole ring which bears a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Thiazolecarboxamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazole ring which bears a carboxylic acid amide group.

name: Hybrid glycopeptides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate component linked to a hybrid peptide component.

name: Hybrid peptides
description: Compounds containing at least two different types of amino acids (alpha, beta, gamma, delta) linked to each other through a peptide bond.

name: Pyranodioxins
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a pyranodioxin moiety, which consists of a pyran ring fused to a dioxin ring.

name: Oxanes
description: Compounds containing an oxane (tetrahydropyran) ring, which is a six-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one oxygen atom and five carbon atoms.

name: Indolecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof) linked to an indole.

name: Indolecarboxamides and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboxamide group attached to an indole.

name: Thiadiazolidines
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a thiadiazole ring, which is a five-member saturated aliphatic  heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Thiadiazolines
description: Cyclic organic compounds containing a thiadiazoline ring, which is a five-member unsaturated aliphatic  heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Thiophene carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a thiophene ring which bears a carboxylic acid group (or a salt/ester thereof).

name: Thiophene carboxamides
description: Compounds containing a thiophene ring which bears a carboxamide.

name: Phenylpyrazoles
description: Compounds containing a phenylpyrazole skeleton, which consists of a pyrazole bound to a phenyl group.

name: Thienopyrimidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a pyrimidine ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Bi- and oligothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing two or more linked thiophene rings. Thiophene is a five-member aromatic ring with one sulfur and four carbon atoms.

name: Ureides
description: Compounds containing an ureide group with the general structure R1-CO-NH-CO-N(R)2R3, formally derived by the acylation of urea. They can be subdivided in N-acyl or N,N'-diacyl ureas.

name: N-acyl ureas
description: Compounds containing an urea bearing a N-acyl group.

name: Thioketone s-oxides
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the general structure R2C=S=O (R not H).

name: Dipyrrins
description: Compounds containing two pyrrole rings fused via a methine (-C=) group.

name: Semioxamazones
description: Compounds containing a semioxamazone functional group, with the structure R2C=NNHC(=O)C(=O)NH2, which is derived from the condensation of aldehydes or ketones with semioxamazide.

name: Ergopeptines
description: Ergoline derivatives that contain a tripeptide structure attached to the basic ergoline ring in the same location as the amide group of the lysergic acid derivatives.

name: Stigmastanes and derivatives
description: Sterol lipids with a structure based on the stigmastane skeleton, which consists of a cholestane moiety bearing an ethyl group at the carbon atom C24.

name: Organic thiosulfuric acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the thiosulfuric acid functional group or a derivative thereof.

name: Azo imides
description: N-Imides of azo compounds, analogous to azoxy compounds, having a delocalized structure.

name: Azoxy compounds
description: Organic compounds sharing a common functional group with the general structure RN=N+(O-)R.

name: Formazans
description: Compounds containing the formazan group with the formula R1(R2)NN=CHN=NR3 (R1,R2,R3=H, alkyl, or aryl).

name: Gorgostanes and derivatives
description: Steroids containing a gorgostane moiety, which a skeleton characterized by the presence.

name: Selenols
description: Organic compounds that contains the functional group with the connectivity R-Se-H.

name: Terphenyls
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a terphenyl skeleton, which consists of a benzene ring substituted with two phenyl groups. Isomers of terphenyl include m-terphenyls (1,3-diphenylbenzenes),  o-terphenyls (1,2-diphenylbenzenes),  p-terphenyls (1,4-diphenylbenzenes).

name: Phenylnaphthalenes
description: Compounds containing a phenylnaphthalene skeleton, which consists of a naphthalene bound to a phenyl group.

name: Ambrosanolides and secoambrosanolides
description: Sesquiterpene lactones from the Ambrosia family, with a backbone derivative of azuleno[6,5-b]furan-2-one (ambrosanolides) or azuleno[4,5-b]furan-2-one (secoambrosanolides).

name: Eremophilanolides and secoeremophilanolides
description: Compounds containing the eremophilanolide skeleton, which is structurally characterized by a naphtho[2,3-b]furan-2-one ring system or a derivative thereof.

name: Terpene glycosides
description: Prenol lipids containing a carbohydrate moiety glycosidically bound to a terpene backbone.

name: Agarofurans
description: Organic compounds containing an agarofuran moiety( a three-ring system, with core fragment oxatricyclo[7.2.1.0^{1,6}]dodec-2-ene).

name: Metalloheterocyclic compounds
description: Heterocyclic compounds contain one metal ring atom.

name: Isoquinolones and derivatives
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing a ketone bearing isoquinoline moiety.

name: Dithiins
description: Compounds comprising a dithiin ring, which is an unsaturated six-member heterocycle containing four carbon atoms, two sulfur atoms and two double bonds.

name: Furazans
description: Compounds containing a furazan moiety, which consists of a five-membered aromatic ring with 1 oxygen and 2 nitrogen atoms at positions 2, 1, and 5, respectively.

name: Furoxans
description: Compounds containing a furoxan (1,2,5-oxadiazol-2-ium-2-olate) moiety.

name: Oxathiins
description: Compounds containing an oxathiin moiety, which consists of an unsaturated aliphatic six-member ring with one oxygen atom, a sulfur atom, and four carbon atoms. Isomers  of oxaphospholane include 1,2-oxathiin, 1,3-oxathiin,and 1,4-oxathiin.

name: Benzoxathiins
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene fused to an oxathiin ring (a six-membered aliphatic ring with four carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, and one sulfur atom).

name: Phenoxathiins
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a phenoxathiin moiety, which is a linear tricyclic system that consists of a two benzene rings joined by a 1,4-oxathiin ring.

name: Organic phosphites
description: Organic compounds containing the phosphite oxoanion, with the formula  [PO3]3-.

name: Sulfite esters
description: Organic compounds containing an organic group attached to the sulfite oxoanion, with the formula  R[SO3]2-.

name: M-quinomethanes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to a methylidene group and a ketone at carbon atoms 1 and 3, respectively.

name: Organic peroxomonosulfates
description: Organic compounds containing the peroxomonosulfate oxoanion, with the formula [SO5]2-.

name: Organic thiosulfates
description: Organic compounds containing the thiosulfate oxoanion, with the formula [S2O3]2-, or its conjugate base.

name: Organic hyposulfites
description: Organic compounds containing the hyposulfite oxoanion, with the formula [SO2]2-.

name: Isoxazolidines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazolidine moiety, with a structure characterized by a five-member saturated aliphatic ring with one oxygen atom and one nitrogen atom at ring positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: Pyrazinecarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a pyrazine ring which bears a carboxamide.

name: Sulfanylbenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids (or derivatives) which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring.

name: Indoloquinazolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing an indole fused to a quinazoline. Indole is a bicyclic  compound consisting of a six-membered benzene ring fused to a five-membered nitrogen-containing pyrrole ring. Quinazoline is a heterocyclic compound consisting of two fused six-membered simple aromatic rings, a benzene ring and a pyrimidine ring.

name: Acyloins
description: Organic compounds containing an alpha hydroxy ketone. Acyloins are formally derived from reductive coupling of carboxylic acyl groups.

name: Oxoprolines
description: Compounds containing an oxoproline moiety, which consists of a pyrrolidine ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at the ring position 2, and a ketone group.

name: Dithioles
description: Compounds comprising a dithiole ring, which is an unsaturated five-member heterocycle containing three carbon atoms, two sulfur atoms and a double bond.

name: Dihydrothiophenes
description: Compounds containing a dihydrothiophene moiety, which is a thiophene derivative with only one double bond.

name: Glucuronic acid derivatives
description: Compounds containing a glucuronic acid moiety (or a derivative), which consists of a glucose moiety with the C6 carbon oxidized to a carboxylic acid.

name: Methanesulfonates
description: Compounds containing a methanesulfonate moiety, which consists of a methane linked to the sulfur atom of a sulfonate group.

name: Cyclohexylphenols
description: Compounds containing a cyclohexane lined to a phenol group.

name: Benzodioxins
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a dioxin ring. Dioxin a six-membered unsaturated ring of two oxygen atoms and four carbon atoms.

name: 1-acyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphoinositols
description: Glycerophosphoinositols where the glycerol is acylated only at position O-1 with a fatty acid.

name: Glycosyl compounds
description: Carbohydrate derivatives in which a sugar group is bonded through its anomeric carbon to another group via a C-, S-,N-,O-, or Se- glycosidic bond.

name: Anthracyclines
description: Polyketides containing a tetracenequinone ring structure with a sugar attached by glycosidic linkage.

name: Benzomorpholines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a morpholine ring.

name: Dioxiranes
description: Compounds containing a three-membered cyclic with two oxygen atoms and a carbon atom.

name: Furoindazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a furan ring fused to the benzene ring of an indazole.

name: Pyranopyridines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a pyridine ring.

name: Azaborinines
description: Organic compounds containing a six-member unsaturated aliphatic ring containing a nitrogen atom, an arsenic atom, and four carbon atoms.

name: Naphthothiazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a thiazole fused to a naphthalene. Thiazole is a 5-membered aromatic ring containing three carbon, one oxygen, and one nitrogen atom. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Triazolopyridazines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a triazole fused to a pyridazine. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyridazine is a six-membered aromatic ring with two adjacent nitrogen atoms, and for carbon atoms.

name: Oxazolopyridines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an oxazole ring fused to a pyridine ring.

name: Quassinoids
description: A group of compounds chemically degraded from triterpenes. According to their basic skeleton, quassinoids are categorized into five distinct groups, C-18, C-19, C-20, C-22 and C-25 types. The C-20 quassinoids can be further classified into two types, tetracyclic and the pentacyclic. The tetracyclic variety does not have oxygenation at C-20, while the pentacyclic quassinoids possess additional oxygenation at C-20 that allows for the formation of an additional ring.

name: O-quinomethanes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to a methylidene group and a ketone at carbon atoms 1 and 2, respectively.

name: P-quinomethanes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring conjugated to a methylidene group and a ketone at carbon atoms 1 and 4, respectively.

name: Triazolothiazoles
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a triazole ring fused to a thiazole ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Thiazole is a 6-membered ring that contains both sulfur and nitrogen.

name: Alkyl glycosides
description: Lipids containing a glycosyl moiety (one or several units) linked to the hydroxyl group of a fatty alcohol.

name: P-terphenyls
description: Terphenyls with a structure containing the 1,4-diphenylbenzene skeleton.

name: Pyrazolopyrazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing to pyrazole rings fused to each other. Pyrazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers.

name: Pyrrolopyrazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pyrrole fused to a pyrazole ring. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyrazole is a 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms and two adjacent nitrogen centers.

name: Pyranopyrimidines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a pyrimidine ring.

name: Monothioketals
description: Compounds containing a monothioketal functional group with the general structure R2C(OR')(SR') with (R = any atom but H).

name: Monothioacetals
description: Compounds containing a monothioacetal functional group with the general structure R2C(OR')(SR').

name: Dithioacetals
description: Compounds containing a dithioacetal functional group with the general structure R2C(SR')2.

name: Dithioketals
description: Compounds containing a dithioketal functional group with the general structure R2C(SR')2 with R, R' = organyl.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleotides
description: Purine nucleotides where the purine moiety is linked to a ribose lacking a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Purine ribonucleotides with one monophosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleoside diphosphates
description: Purine ribonucleotides with one diphosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Purine ribonucleotides with one triphosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Purine nucleotides with monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Purine 3'-deoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Purine nucleotides with monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 3.

name: Purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Purine nucleotides with triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleotides
description: Nucleotides consisting of a pyrimidine base linked to a ribose to which at least phosphate group is attached.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleotides
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides where the purine moiety is linked to a ribose lacking a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside bisphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside diphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one diphosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one monophosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one triphosphate group attached to one hydroxyl group of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside diphosphates
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides with a diphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides with a monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides with a triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleoside monophosphates
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides with monophosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at positions 2 and 3.

name: Pyrimidine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleoside triphosphates
description: Pyrimidine nucleotides with triphosphate group  linked to the ribose moiety lacking a hydroxyl group at positions 2 and 3.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleoside bisphosphates
description: Purine ribonucleotides with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Purine deoxyribonucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to each of two different hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety, which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Purine 2'-deoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a purine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Purine 3'-deoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a purine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 3.

name: Purine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a purine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at positions 2 and 3.

name: Pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a pyrimidine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 2.

name: Pyrimidine 3'-deoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a pyrimidine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at position 3.

name: Pyrimidine 2',3'-dideoxyribonucleosides
description: Compounds consisting of a pyrimidine linked to a ribose which lacks a hydroxyl group at positions 2 and 3.

name: Phenyltriazoles
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a phenyl group substituted with a triazole ring.

name: Piperazinesulfonamides
description: Organic cyclic compounds containing a sulfonamide group attached to a piperazine ring.

name: Phthalide isoquinolines
description: Organic compounds with a structure characterized by an isoquinoline moiety linked to phthalide.

name: Oligosaccharide phosphates
description: Carbohydrates containing between 3 and 9 sugar units, one of which bear one or more phosphate groups.

name: 6,7-secoergolines
description: Compounds containing a tricyclic ergoline analog, where carbon atoms C6 and C7 are not linked to each other.

name: Hydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Bile acids, alcohols or derivatives bearing at least hydroxyl group.

name: Naphthylisoquinolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a naphthalene moiety linked to an isoquinoline through a CC or CN single bond.

name: Naphthylquinolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a naphthene moiety linked to a quinoline through a CC or CN single bond.

name: Pentahydroxy bile acids, alcohols and derivatives
description: Bile acids, alcohols or derivatives bearing five hydroxyl groups.

name: Phenylazetidines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a phenyl ring substituted with an azetidine ring.

name: Sophorolipids
description: Glycolipids containing a sophorose moiety linked glycosidically to the hydroxyl group of a 17-hydroxy-C18 saturated fatty acid. The carboxyl group of the fatty acid can be linked to the 4'-hydroxyl of the second glucose to form a lactone.

name: Hydropyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a hydrogenated pyrimidine ring (i.e. containing less than the maximum number of double bonds.).

name: Glycosylamines
description: Compounds consisting of an amine with a beta-N-glycosidic bond to a carbohydrate, thus forming a cyclic hemiaminal ether bond (alpha-amino ether).

name: C-glycosyl compounds
description: Glycoside in which a sugar group is bonded through one carbon to another group via a C-glycosidic bond.

name: Thioglycosides
description: Glycoside in which a sugar group is bonded through one carbon to another group via a S-glycosidic bond.

name: O-glycosyl compounds
description: Glycoside in which a sugar group is bonded through one carbon to another group via a O-glycosidic bond.

name: Purine ribonucleoside 2',5'-bisphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to 2' and 5' hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety.

name: Purine ribonucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphates
description: Purine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to 3' and 5' hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety.

name: Sugar alcohols
description: Hydrogenated forms of carbohydrate in which the carbonyl group (aldehyde or ketone, reducing sugar) has been reduced to a primary or secondary hydroxyl group.

name: Isoxazolines
description: Compounds containing a five-member unsaturated aliphatic ring,  with an oxygen atom adjacent to a nitrogen atoms, and three carbon atoms.

name: Pyridine carboxaldehydes
description: Aromatic compounds containing a pyridine ring which bears a carboxaldehyde group.

name: Glycerophosphocholines
description: Lipids containing a glycerol moiety carrying a phosphocholine at the 3-position.

name: Glycerophosphates
description: Compounds containing a glycerol linked to a phosphate group.

name: Glycerophosphoethanolamines
description: Glycerolipids characterized by an ethanolamine ester of glycerophosphoric acid. As is the case with diacylglycerols, glycerophosphoethanolamines can have many different combinations of fatty acids of varying lengths and saturation attached to the C-1 and C-2 atoms.

name: Glycerophosphoglycerols
description: Glycerophosphoglycerols are lipids that contain two glycerol moieties that are linked to each other through the only phosphate group.

name: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphates
description: Glycerophospholipids that contain two glycerophosphate skeleton linked to each other through one of the phosphate groups.

name: Glycerophosphoserines
description: Lipids containing a glycerol moiety carrying a phosphoserine at the 3-position.

name: Glycerophosphoinositols
description: Lipids containing a glycerol moiety carrying a phosphoinositol at the 3-position.

name: Glycerophosphoinositol phosphates
description: Lipids containing a common glycerophosphate skeleton linked to at least one fatty acyl chain and an inositol-5-phosphate moiety.

name: Polyprenylphenols
description: Compounds containing a polyisoprene chain attached to a phenol group.

name: Hydropyrimidine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a hydrogenated pyrimidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid group.

name: Butenolides
description: Dihydrofurans with a carbonyl group at the C2 carbon atom.

name: Hydropyridines
description: Compounds containing a hydrogenated pyridine ring (i.e. containing less than the maximum number of double bonds.).

name: Dioxaborolanes
description: Compounds containing a five-member saturated aliphatic heterocycle made up of two oxygen atoms, a boron atom, and three carbon atoms.

name: Oxaborole derivatives
description: Compounds containing a five-member aliphatic heterocycle made up of one oxygen atom, a boron atom, and three carbon atoms.

name: Dialkylamines
description: Organic compounds containing a dialkylamine group, characterized by two alkyl groups bonded to the amino nitrogen.

name: Medium-chain aldehydes
description: An aldehyde with a chain length containing between 6 and 12 carbon atoms.

name: Short-chain aldehydes
description: An aldehyde with a chain length containing between 2 and 5 carbon atoms.

name: Ubiquinols
description: Coenzyme Q derivatives containing a 5, 6-dimethoxy-3-methylbenzene-1,4-diol moiety to which an isoprenyl group is attached at ring position 2(or 6).

name: Isoxazolinones
description: Compounds containing an isoxazoline ring that bears a ketone group.

name: Aldazines
description: Azines of aldehydes containing a moiety with the formula RCH=NN=CHR.

name: Aminotetrazines
description: Compounds containing an amine group attached to a tetrazine. Tetrazine is a six-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of four nitrogen atoms and a two carbon atoms.

name: Ketazines
description: Azines of ketones containing a moiety with the formula R2C=NN=CR2.

name: Delta sultones
description: Organic compounds containing a delta-sultone, an intramolecular cyclic ester of hydroxy sulfonic acid, with a SO ring bond, and four ring carbon atoms.

name: Arylsulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an aryl group attached to the sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Trialkylamines
description: Organic compounds containing a trialkylamine group, characterized by exactly three alkyl groups bonded to the amino nitrogen.

name: Thiopyranoquinolines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a thiopyran ring fused to a quinoline moiety. Quinoline or benzo[b]pyridine is a bicyclic compound that consists of benzene fused to a pyridine.

name: Phenylacetylindoles
description: Compounds containing an indole moiety attached to phenylacetate derivative.

name: Abscisic acids and derivatives
description: Terpene compounds containing the abscisic acid moiety, which is characterized by a  3-methylpenta-2,4-dienoic acid attached to the C1 carbon of a 4-oxocyclohex-2-ene moiety.

name: Cinchona alkaloids
description: Alkaloids structurally characterized by the presence of the cinchonan skeleton, which consists of a quinoline linked to an azabicyclo[2.2.2]octane moiety.

name: Naphthoylindoles
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an indole moiety that is N-linked to the carboxamide group attached to naphthalene.

name: Pyrimidine ribonucleoside 3',5'-bisphosphates
description: Pyrimidine ribobucleotides with one phosphate group attached to 3' and 5' hydroxyl groups of the ribose moiety.

name: Thioaldehyde s-oxides
description: Compounds having the general structure RC(=S=O)H.

name: Quinoline-3-carboxamides
description: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by one carboxamide group at the 3-position.

name: Nicotinamides
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at position 3 by a carboxamide group.

name: N-substituted nicotinamides
description: Nicotnamides in which the pyridine ring is substituted at position 1.

name: Pyrrolidinecarboxamides
description: Pyrrolidines in which the pyrrolidine rings is substituted at one or more positions by a carboxamide group. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Substituted pyrroles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring substituted at one or more positions.

name: N-substituted pyrroles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring substituted at position 1.

name: Pentose phosphates
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing a pentose substituted by one or more phosphate groups.

name: Hexose phosphates
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing a hexose substituted by one or more phosphate groups.

name: Oxathioles
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated five-membered ring with three carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, one sulfur atom, and one double bond.

name: Gluconolactones
description: Polyhydroxy acids containing a gluconolactone molecule, which is characterized by a tetrahydropyran substituted by three hydroxyl groups, one ketone group, and one hydroxymethyl group.

name: Pyranopterins and derivatives
description: Pterin derivatives in which a pyran ring is fused either to the pyrimidine ring or the pyrazine ring of the pterin moiety.

name: Sulfoquinovosyldiacylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids made up of a sulfonic acid linked to the C6 atom of glucose, which in turn is bound to the O3 atom of the a 1,2-diacylglycerol moiety.

name: Pyrazine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups (or derivatives thereof).

name: Hydantoins
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazolidine  substituted by ketone group at positions 2 and 4.

name: Nitronaphthalenes
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a naphthalene moiety substituted by one or more nitro groups.

name: N-acyl-alpha-hexosamines
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing a hexose moiety in which the oxygen atom is replaced by an n-acyl group.

name: Benzene and substituted derivatives
description: Aromatic compounds containing one monocyclic ring system consisting of benzene.

name: Phenylhydantoins
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing an imiazolidinedione moiety substituted by a phenyl group.

name: Carboximidic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a carboximidic group, with the general formula R-C(=NR1)OR2.

name: Polyols
description: Organic compounds containing more than one hydroxyl groups.

name: Pyrroline carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrroline ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups (or derivative thereof).

name: Thiomorpholines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiomorpholine ring, which is a six-membered aliphatic ring containing one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom at positions 1 and 4 respectively, and four carbon atoms.

name: Thiomorpholine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiomorpholine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups (or derivative thereof). Thiomorpholine a six-membered aliphatic ring containing one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom at positions 1 and 4 respectively, and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrrolopyrimidine nucleosides and nucleotides
description: Nucleoside derivatives containing a ribose derivative which is n-glycosylated to a pyrrolopyrimidine. Also called deazapurine nucleosides, they are analogs of purine nucleosides with the N atom of the purine being replaced by a C atom at position 7.

name: Morpholine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a morpholine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups (or derivative thereof).

name: Phenylpyrimidines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyrimidine ring through a CC or CN bond.  Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Alpha amino acid amides
description: Amide derivatives of alpha amino acids.

name: Substituted imidazoles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring substituted at one or more positions.

name: N-substituted imidazoles
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring substituted at position 1.

name: Piperidinecarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring substituted with a carboxamide functional group.

name: Thienodiazepines
description: Heteropolycyclic containing a thiophene ring fused to a diazepine ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon and one sulfur atoms. Diazepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of five carbon and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Quinazolinamines
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing a quianazoline moiety substituted by one or more amine groups.

name: Piperazine carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups (or derivatives thereof).

name: Piperazine carboxamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring substituted by one or more carboxamide group.

name: Phenylpyridines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyridine ring through a CC or CN bond.

name: Carbacephems
description: A new class of beta-lactam antibiotics similar in structure to the cephalosporins. They differ from cephalosporins, however, in the substitution of a sulfur atom in the dihydrothiazine ring with a methylene group to form a tetrahydropyridine ring.

name: Phenol esters
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring substituted by a hydroxyl group and an ester group.

name: Halophenols
description: Aromatic compounds containing benzene substituted by a hydroxyl group and a halogen atom.

name: Cycloartanols and derivatives
description: Steroids containing a cycloartanol moiety.

name: Triazolodiazepines
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing a triazole ring fused to a diazepine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Diazepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of five carbon and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Benzothiadiazoles
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a thiadiazole ring. Thiadiazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle made up of one sulfur atom and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Thiadiazole sulfonamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted by at least one sulfonamide group.

name: Phenylimidazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to an imidazole ring through a CC or CN bond.

name: Aminothiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted by one or more amine groups.

name: Isoxazolopyridines
description: Aromatic compounds containing an isoxazole ring fused to a pyridine ring. Isoxazole is five-membered ring with three carbon atoms, and an oxygen atom next to a nitrogen atom. Pyridine is a 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one nitrogen center.

name: Benzisoxazoles
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an isoxazole ring. Isoxazole is five-membered ring with three carbon atoms, and an oxygen atom next to a nitrogen atom.

name: Benzisoxazolones
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to an isoxazolone moiety.

name: Phenylpyrroles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyrrole ring through a CC or CN bond.

name: Phenylpyrrolines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyrroline ring through a CC or CN bond.

name: Phenylpyrrolidines
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyrrolidine ring through a CC or CN bond. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Imidazolethiones
description: Aromatic compounds containing an imidazole ring which bears a thioketone group.

name: Cycloheptathiophenes
description: Polycyclic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a 7 member carbocyclic moiety. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom.

name: Chromenopyridines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds structurally characterized by a pyridine ring fused to a chromene moiety.

name: Azasteroids and derivatives
description: Steroid derivatives in which one carbon atom in the steroidal skeleton has been substituted with a nitrogen atom.

name: Phenol ethers
description: Aromatic compounds containing an ether group substituted with a benzene ring.

name: Triazole ribonucleosides and ribonucleotides
description: Nucleoside derivatives containing a ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety which is N-glycosylated to a triazole.  Nucleotides have a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon of the ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety.

name: Methoxybenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids in which a hydrogen atom of the benzene ring is replaced by a methoxy group.

name: O-methoxybenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids in which the hydrogen atom at position 2 of the benzene ring is replaced by a methoxy group.

name: P-methoxybenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids in which the hydrogen atom at position 4 of the benzene ring is replaced by a methoxy group.

name: M-methoxybenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids  in which the hydrogen atom at position 3 of the benzene ring is replaced by a methoxy group.

name: Phenylquinolines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a quinoline moiety substituted with a phenyl group.

name: Naphthalenecarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a naphthalene moiety, which bears a carboxylic acid amide group at one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Pyrazole carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazole ring in which a hydrogen atom is replaced by a carboxylic acid group.

name: Benzocycloheptapyridines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring and a pyridine ring fused to a seven membered carbocycle.

name: Thioenol ethers
description: Compounds containing the enol ether functional group, with the formula R3SCR2=CR1.

name: Thioenols
description: Compounds containing the enol functional group, with the structure HS(R)C=CR'. Thioenols interconvert with thioketones that have an alpha-hydrogen.

name: Enol esters
description: Ester derivatives of enols. They have the general formula RC=COC(=O)R' where R, R' = H or organyl group.

name: Benzoisochromanequinones
description: Benzo derivatives of isochromanequinones. Isochromanequinones are structurally characterized by a quinone fused to an isochromane, and forming a naphtho[2,3-c]pyran-6,9-dione skeleton.

name: Aminopiperidines
description: Compounds containing a piperidine that carries an amino group.

name: Triterpene saponins
description: Glycosylated derivatives of triterpene sapogenins. The sapogenin moiety backbone is usually based on the oleanane, ursane, taraxastane, bauerane,  lanostane, lupeol, lupane, dammarane, cycloartane, friedelane, hopane, 9b,19-cyclo-lanostane, cycloartane, or cycloartanol skeleton.

name: Thiophenol ethers
description: Thioether derivatives of thiophenols. Thiophenol is a phenol derivative obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from the hydroxyl group (attached to the benzene) by a sulfur atom.

name: Thiophenol esters
description: Thioester derivatives of thiophenols. Thiophenol is a phenol derivative obtained by replacing the oxygen atom from the hydroxyl group (attached to the benzene) by a sulfur atom.

name: Thiobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing thiobenzoic acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Thienamycins
description: Beta-lactam antibiotics that differ from penicillins in having the thiazolidine sulfur atom replaced by carbon, the sulfur then becoming the first atom in the side chain.

name: Phenylacetamides
description: Amide derivatives of phenylacetic acids.

name: Steroidal saponins
description: Saponins in which the aglycone moiety is a steroid. The steroidal aglycone is usually a spirostane, furostane, spirosolane, solanidane, or curcubitacin derivative.

name: Cyanogenic glycosides
description: Glycosides in which the aglycone moiety contains a cyanide group.

name: Furanoquinolines
description: Compounds containing a furan ring fused to a quinoline.

name: Secondary ketimines
description: Ketimines where the nitrogen of the ketimine group is linked to an alkyl or aryl group.

name: Piperazinopiperidines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a piperazine ring fused to a piperidine.

name: Pyrroloquinoxalines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring fused to a quinoxaline ring system.

name: Limonoids
description: Highly oxygenated, modified terpenoids with a prototypical structure either containing or derived from a precursor with a 4,4,8-trimethyl-17-furanylsteroid skeleton. All naturally occurring citrus limonoids contain a furan ring attached to the D-ring, at C-17, as well as oxygen containing functional groups at C-3, C-4, C-7, C-16 and C-17.

name: 17-furanylsteroids and derivatives
description: Steroidal compounds having a furanyl group linked to the steroid backbone at the C17 position.

name: Oxasteroids and derivatives
description: Steroid derivatives where a carbon atom of the steroid is replaced by an oxygen atom.

name: Benzoquinones
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring that carries two ketone group at the 1- and 4-positions (cyclohexa-2,5-diene-1,4-dione).

name: O-quinones
description: Quinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 2-positions, respectively.

name: Diazinanes
description: Organic compounds containing diazinane, a six-membered saturated heterocycle containing four carbon atoms and two nitrogen atoms.

name: Glycerol ethers
description: Lipids containing an ether derivative of glycerol.

name: Azines
description: Hydrazine derivatives in which the hydrazine group is conjugated to two aldehydes (forming aldazines) or ketones (forming ketazines).

name: Azomethines
description: Compounds having the general structure RN=CR2 (where R is not a hydrogen atom).

name: Shiff bases
description: Aldimines where the nitrogen atom of the aldimine group is linked to an alkyl or aryl group.

name: Primary aldimines
description: Aldimines where the nitrogen atom of the aldimine group is linked to a hydrogen atom.

name: Nitrones
description: N-oxides of imines, with the general structure R1C(R2)=[N+](R3)[O-] (R3 is not an Hydrogen atom).

name: N-acyl-alpha amino acids
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid which bears an acyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: N-carbamoyl-alpha amino acids
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid which bears an carbamoyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: Alpha amino acids
description: Amino acids in which the amino group is attached to the carbon atom immediately adjacent to the carboxylate group (alpha carbon).

name: Indolecarboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a carboxylic acid group linked to an indole.

name: Morpholine carboxylic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a morpholine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups.

name: Oxirane carboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing an oxirane ring bearing a carboxylic acid group.

name: Piperazine carboxylic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups.

name: Piperidinecarboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid group.

name: Pyrazine carboxylic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazine ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups.

name: Pyridinecarboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring bearing a carboxylic acid group.

name: Pyrimidinecarboxylic acids
description: Pyrimidines with a structure containing a carboxyl group attached to the pyrimidine ring.

name: Pyrrolidine carboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine ring which bears a carboxylic acid. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Pyrroline carboxylic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrroline ring substituted by one or more carboxylic acid groups.

name: Thiophene carboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a thiophene ring which bears a carboxylic acid group.

name: Naphthalenecarboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a naphthalene moiety, which bears a carboxylic acid group one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: Azetidinecarboxylic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an azetidine ring.

name: Aziridinecarboxylic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an aziridine ring.

name: Anthracenecarboxylic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid group attached to an anthracene ring system.

name: Carboselenoic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing at least one carboselenoyl group, with the formula RC(=O)Se (or a derivative thereof).

name: Selenazoles
description: Compounds containing a five-membered aromatic ring with a the carbon atom replaced by a selenium atom (at position 1) and a nitrogen atom (at position 2 or 3).

name: Selenoethers
description: Organic compounds containing a selenoether group, with the general formula RseR' ( where R, R' are not H atoms).

name: Selenoesters
description: Analogues of esters where an oxygen atom is replaced by a selenium atom. They generally have the formula RC(=O)SeR' or RC(=Se)OR'.

name: Alpha-bromoaldehydes
description: Aldehydes with the general formula C(Br)C(=O)H, with in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C-Br group.

name: Alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehydes
description: Aldehydes of general formula R(1)R(2)C=CR(3)-CH=O or RC#C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to an unsaturated C-C bond at the alpha,beta position.

name: Alpha-hydrogen aldehydes
description: Aldehydes with the general formula HC(H)(R)C(=O)H, where R is an organyl group.

name: Beta-hydroxy aldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a hydroxy group on the second carbon atom.

name: Enals
description: An alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehyde of general formula RC=C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C=C triple bond at the alpha,beta position.

name: Ynals
description: An alpha,beta-unsaturated aldehyde of general formula RC#C-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is conjugated to a C#C triple bond at the alpha,beta position.

name: Terminal alkynes
description: Alkynes featuring a carbon substituent on one acetylenic carbon, and a hydrogen on the other carbon.

name: Artemisinins
description: Sesquiterpenoids originally isolated from the herb Artemisia annua. Their structure is based on artemisinin, a tetracyclic compound that contains a 1,2-dioxepane fused to an octahydrobenzopyran moiety. The internal peroxide bridge is believed to be a key to the mode of action of artemisinins.

name: Naphthols and derivatives
description: Naphthalene derivatives carrying one or more hydroxyl (-OH) groups at any ring position.

name: Nitrosopiperidines
description: Piperidines with a nitroso functional group attached to the piperidine ring.

name: Nitrosothiols
description: nitroso compounds containing the nitrosothiol group, with the general formula RS=N=O.

name: N-methylnitrosoureas
description: Organonitrogen compounds with the general formula H3CN(N=O)R(N)=O (R = any atom).

name: Peroxycarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic acids with the general formula OOC(R)=O (R = H, organyl group).

name: Peroxycarboxylic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula [H]OOC(R)=O (R = H, organyl group).

name: Benzenoids
description: Aromatic compounds containing one or more benzene rings.

name: Amines
description: Compounds formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups, and having the general structures RNH2 (primary amines), R2NH (secondary amines), R3N (tertiary amines).

name: Primary amines
description: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly one hydrocarbyl group.

name: Secondary amines
description: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly two hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Tertiary amines
description: Amines having the nitrogen atom linked to exactly three hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Primary aromatic amines
description: Primary amines where the only hydrocarbyl substituent of the amine group is aromatic. Primary amines have the general formula RNH2 (R=aryl).

name: Tertiary alkylarylamines
description: Tertiary amines where the nitrogen atom is linked to at least one alkyl group and at least one aryl group.

name: Germacrane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids having the germacrane skeleton, with a structure characterized by a cyclodecane ring substituted with an isopropyl and two methyl groups.

name: Triarylamines
description: Organic compounds containing a trialkylamine group, characterized by exactly three aryl groups bonded to the amino nitrogen.

name: Secondary alkylarylamines
description: Secondary alkylarylamines with the general formula HN(R)R' (R = alkyl, R' = aryl).

name: Nitramines
description: Organyl derivatives of nitramide with the general formula RNHO2 (R = organyl group).

name: Alkanolamines
description: Organic compounds that carry a hydroxy and an amino functional groups on an alkane backbone.

name: Imidothioic acids and derivatives
description: Sulfur derivatives of imidic acid (a derivatives thereof) containing the functional group -RC(=N)S, obtained by replacing the oxygen atom by a sulfur atom.

name: Diarylethers
description: Organic compounds containing the dialkyl ether functional group, with the formula ROR', where R and R' are aryl groups.

name: Hydrazidines
description: Hydrazine derivatives with the general formula RC(NHNH2)2=NNH2.

name: Ynols
description: Organooxygen compounds with the general formula R#CO (R = organyl).

name: Oxazaphosphinanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an oxazaphosphinane ring, which consists of three carbon atoms, one nitrogen atom, and one phosphorus atom.

name: 1,2-diols
description: Polyols containing an alcohol group at two adjacent positions.

name: Organoselenium compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a carbon-selenium bond.

name: Selenocyanates
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RSeC#N.

name: Selenenyl halides
description: Organoselenium compounds with the general formula RSeX (R = organyl, X = halogen atom).

name: Diselenides
description: Organoselenium compounds with the general structure R-Se-Se-R' (R,R' = H or organic moiety).

name: Selenoxides
description: Organoselenium compounds with the general formula RSe(=O)R' (R,R'= organyl).

name: Dicarboxdiimides
description: Hydrazine derivatives in which each of the two nitrogen atoms is the central atom of a dicarboximide group.

name: Carboximidic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=N)-OH (R=H, organic group).

name: Thiols
description: Organic compounds containing a functional group with the structure RSH (R = organyl).

name: Dioxathiolanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a dioxathiolane, with a structure consisting of a five-membered saturated ring with one sulfur atom, two oxygen atoms, and two carbon atoms.

name: Azolines
description: Azole derivatives obtained by conversion of one double bond of the azole ring to a single bond.

name: Azolidines
description: Azole derivatives obtained by conversion of both double bonds of the azole ring to single bonds, yielding a saturated ring.

name: O-benzoquinones
description: Benzoquinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 2-positions, respectively.

name: M-benzoquinones
