description: Benzoquinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 3-position, respectively.

name: P-benzoquinones
description: Benzoquinones where the two C=O groups are attached at the 1- and 4-positions, respectively.

name: Quinones
description: Compounds having a fully conjugated cyclic dione structure, such as that of benzoquinones, derived from aromatic compounds by conversion of an even number of number of -CH= groups into -C(=O)- groups with any necessary rearrangement of double bonds (polycyclic and heterocyclic analogues are included).

name: Isoindolines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a 2,3-dihydro-1H-iso-indole moiety.

name: Indoles
description: Compounds containing an indole moiety, which consists of pyrrole ring fused to benzene  to form 2,3-benzopyrrole.

name: Isothiochromenes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an isothiochromene moiety.

name: Thiochromenes
description: Organosulfur compounds that are analogues to chromene, with the difference that a sulfur atom replaces the oxygen atom.

name: Alkanes
description: Acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having the general formula CnH2n+2 , and therefore consisting entirely of hydrogen atoms and saturated carbon atoms.

name: Alkenes
description: Acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having one carbon-carbon double bond and the general formula CnH2n.

name: Hydroxycinnamic acids
description: Compounds containing an cinnamic acid where the benzene ring is hydroxylated.

name: Cinnamic acids
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene and a carboxylic acid group forming 3-phenylprop-2-enoic acid.

name: Coumaric acids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a cinnamic acid moiety hydroxylated at the C2 (ortho-), C3 (meta-), or C4 (para-) carbon atom of the benzene ring.

name: Isoflavonoids
description: Natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: Homoisoflavonoids
description: Naturally occurring oxygen heterocycles with a structure based on a 16-carbon skeleton including a chromanone, chromone or chromane system with a benzyl group at position C-3.

name: Homoisoflavans
description: Homoisoflavonoids with a structure based on the chromane system. Chromone is a bicyclic compound consisting of a 3,4-dihydro-1-benzopyran.

name: Cyclitols and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a cycloalkane moiety with one hydroxyl group on each of three or more ring atoms. These of also include derivatives where the hydrogen atom of one or more of the hydroxyl groups is replaced with another atom.

name: Aminocyclitols and derivatives
description: Cyclitols, or derivatives thereof with at least one hydroxyl group replace by an amino group. These of also include derivatives where the hydrogen atom of one or more of the hydroxyl groups is replaced with another atom.

name: Inositol phosphates
description: Compounds containing a phosphate group attached to an inositol (or cyclohexanehexol) moiety.

name: Quinic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a quinic acid moiety (or a derivative thereof), which is a cyclitol made up of a cyclohexane ring that bears four hydroxyl groups at positions 1,3.4, and 5, as well as a carboxylic acid at position 1.

name: Salicylic acids
description: Ortho-hydroxylated benzoic acids.

name: Salicylamides
description: Carboxamide derivatives of salicylic acid. Salicylic acid is the ortho-hydroxylated derivative of benzoic acid.

name: N-piperazineacetamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperazine ring, which N-substituted with an acetamide group.

name: Chamigranes
description: Sesquiterpenoids characterized by a 1,1,5,9-tetramethylspiro[5,5]undecane skeleton, formally obtained by linking the C1-C6 and C6-C11 of farnesane together. They are predominantly isolated from algae.

name: Annonaceous acetogenins
description: Waxy derivatives of fatty acids (usually C32 or C34), containing a terminal carboxylic acid combined with a 2-propanol unit at the C-2 position to form a methyl- substituted alpha,beta-unsaturated-gamma-lactone. One of their interesting structural features is a single, adjacent, or nonadjacent tetrahydrofuran (THF) or tetrahydropyran (THP) system with one or two flanking hydroxyl group(s) at the center of a long hydrocarbon chain.

name: Acylphloroglucinols and derivatives
description: Phloroglucinol derivatives characterized by the presence of a COR group.

name: Cyclopropanecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof) attached to a cyclopropane ring.

name: Cyclopropanecarboxylic acids
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group attached to a cyclopropane ring.

name: 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing both a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof) and an amino group at position C1 of a cyclopropane ring.

name: Halohydrins
description: Alcohols substituted by a halogen atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups (usually used to mean beta-halo alcohols).

name: Carbonylimidazoles
description: Substituted imidazoles in which the imidazole ring bears a carbonyl group.

name: Epoxypiperidines
description: Heteropolycyclic compounds containing an oxirane fused to a piperidine ring.

name: Phenoxides
description: Salts or analogous metal derivatives of phenols.

name: Isothiocyanate acids
description: Acidic derivatives of isothiocyanates with the general formula RC(=O)N=C=S.

name: Hemiketals
description: Hemiacetals having the structure R2C(OH)OR' ( R' not H ), derived from ketones by formal addition of an alcohol to the carbonyl group.

name: Dihydroxyphosphanes
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RP(OH)OH.

name: Carbodithioic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=S)SH (R = organyl).

name: Benzylethers
description: Aromatic ethers with the general formula ROCR' (R = alkyl, aryl; R'=benzene).

name: Diazetidines
description: Organic compounds containing the diazetidine ring, a saturated four-membered ring with two nitrogen atoms and 2 carbon atoms.

name: Phenylimidazolidines
description: Polycyclic compounds containing an imidazoline substituted by a phenyl group.

name: Tanshinones, isotanshinones, and derivatives
description: A group of abietane-type norditerpenoid quinones.

name: Isocopalane and spongiane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the isocopalane  (Tetradecahydro-1,1,4a,7,8,8a-hexamethylphenanthrene) or the 15,16-epoxyisocopalane skeleton.

name: Phenylpropanoic acids
description: Compounds with a structure containing a benzene ring conjugated to a propanoic acid.

name: Quinoline carboxylic acids
description: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by a carboxyl group at one or more positions.

name: Quinoline carboxamides
description: Quinolines in which the quinoline ring system is substituted by one or more carboxamide groups.

name: Pyrrole carboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Pyrrole carboxylic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxyl group.

name: Pyrrole carboxamides
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring bearing a carboxamide.

name: Pyrrole 2-carboxylic acids
description: Pyrrole carboxylic acids where the carboxyl group is attached at position C2.

name: N-substituted phenoxazines
description: Phenoxyazines where the nitrogen atom is linked to an atom other than the hydrogen atom.

name: Sulfosalicylic acids and derivatives
description: Salicylic acids (or derivatives thereof) with a sulfate group attached to the benzene ring.

name: Thiatriazoles
description: Heteroaromatic compounds containing a thiatriazole ring, which is a five-membered aromatic ring with one sulfur atom, three nitrogen atom, and a carbon atom.

name: Aminothiadiazoles
description: Thiadiazoles with an amino group attached to the thiadiazole ring.

name: Methoxypyrazines
description: Pyrazines containing a methoxyl group attached to the pyrazine ring.

name: Dichlorobenzenes
description: Compounds containing a benzene with exactly two chlorine atoms attached to it.

name: Benzoic acids
description: Organic Compounds containing a benzene ring which bears at least one carboxyl group.

name: Isoquinolines and derivatives
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing an isoquinoline moiety, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyridine ring and forming benzo[c]pyridine.

name: Isoquinoline quinones
description: Isoquinoline derivative with a structure containing a 5,8-dihydroisoquinoline-5,8-dione skeleton.

name: Angular furanocoumarins
description: Furanocoumarins, with a structure characterized by a furan ring angularly fused to a coumarin.

name: Linear furanocoumarins
description: Furanocoumarins, with a structure characterized by a furan ring linearly fused to a coumarin.

name: Quinoline quinones
description: Quinoline derivative with a structure containing a 5,8-dihydroisoquinoline-5,8-dione skeleton.

name: Phenanthraquinones
description: Phenanthrene derivatives containing two ketone groups at position C9 and C10, respectively.

name: Naphthothiophenes
description: Compounds containing a naphthalene (or a derivative) fused to thiophene.

name: Thienobenzoxepines
description: Compounds containing a benzoxepine fused to a thiophene ring. Thiophene is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one sulfur atom.

name: Phenylisoxazolidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazolidine conjugated by a phenyl group.

name: 1,2-oxazinanes
description: Compounds containing an oxazinane ring with the nitrogen atom and the oxygen atom at positions 1  and 2, respectively.

name: Phenylthiomorpholines
description: Compounds containing a thiomorpholine ring conjugated to a phenyl group. Thiomorpholine a six-membered aliphatic ring containing one nitrogen atom and one sulfur atom at positions 1 and 4 respectively, and four carbon atoms.

name: Oxathiazolidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an oxathiazolidine, a saturated five-membered ring having two carbon atoms, one oxygen atom, one nitrogen atom, and one sulfur atom.

name: Neoflavans
description: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on a 3,4-dihydro-4-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton.

name: Neoflavenes
description: Neoflavonoids with a structure based on a 4-phenylchromene skeleton.

name: Phenylbenzofurans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a phenyl group attached to a benzofuran moiety. Benzofuran is a bicyclic compound containing a benzene fused to a furan.

name: O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups conjugated to the flavonoid backbone.

name: O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups conjugated to the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: 3-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C3 atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 5-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C5 atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 6-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C6 atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 7-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C7 atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 8-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C8 atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 2'-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C2' atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 3'-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C3' atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 4'-O-methylated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C4' atom of the flavonoid backbone.

name: 5-O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C5 atom of the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: 7-O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C7 atom of the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: 2'-O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C2' atom of the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: 3'-O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C3' atom of the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: 4'-O-methylated isoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids with methoxy groups attached to the C4' atom of the isoflavonoid backbone. Isoflavonoids are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: Bromohydrins
description: Alcohols substituted by a bromine atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Chlorohydrins
description: Alcohols substituted by a chlorine atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Fluorohydrins
description: Alcohols substituted by a fluorine atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Iodohydrins
description: Alcohols substituted by a iodine atom at a saturated carbon atom otherwise bearing only hydrogen or hydrocarbyl groups.

name: Dichlorobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids having two chlorine atoms attached to the carboxylated benzene ring.

name: 2-phenylbenzofurans
description: Phenylbenzofurans where the benzofuran moiety is conjugated at the 2-position to a phenyl group.

name: Furanoflavonoids and dihydrofuranoflavonoids
description: Flavonoids possessing a furan (or dihydrofuran) ring fused to the benzopyran moiety of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Furanoisoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids possessing a furan ring fused to the phenyl group of the isoflavonoid skeleton.

name: Tetrahydrofolic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds based on the 5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteroic acid skeleton conjugated with at least one L-glutamic acid unit (or a derivative thereof) .

name: N-benzylalanines
description: N-benzyl derivatives of alanine.

name: N-benzoylpiperidines
description: Heterocyclic Compounds containing a piperidine ring conjugated to a benzyl group through one nitrogen ring atom.

name: N-benzylpiperidines
description: Heterocyclic Compounds containing a piperidine ring conjugated to a benzyl group through one nitrogen ring atom.

name: Thiohydroquinones
description: Organic compounds similar to hydroquinones wit the difference that one hydroxyl group is replaced by a thiol group.

name: Aminohydroquinones
description: Organic compounds containing an amine group attached to a hydroquinone.

name: Phenylsulfates
description: Compounds containing a sulfuric acid group conjugated to a phenyl group.

name: Imidazopiperidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a piperidine ring. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Piperidine is a five-membered heterocycle containing five carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom.

name: Trisubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at exactly three different positions.

name: 1,2,4-trisubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at positions 1, 2, and 3.

name: 1,2,5-trisubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at positions 1, 2, and 5.

name: 2,4,5-trisubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at positions 2, 4, and 5.

name: Tetrasubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at exactly four different positions.

name: 1,2,4,5-tetrasubstituted imidazoles
description: Imidazoles in which the imidazole ring is substituted at for positions 1,2,4, and 5.

name: 2,4-disubstituted thiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted at the positions 2 and 3.

name: 2,5-disubstituted thiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted at positions 2 and 5 only.

name: 4,5-disubstituted thiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted at positions 4 and 5 only.

name: 2,4,5-trisubstituted thiazoles
description: Compounds containing a thiazole ring substituted at positions 2, 4 and 5 only.

name: 2,4-disubstituted oxazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2 and 4 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole.

name: 2,5-disubstituted oxazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole.

name: 4,5-disubstituted oxazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 4 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole.

name: 2,4,5-trisubstituted oxazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxazole ring substituted at positions 2, 4 and 5 only. Oxazole is a five-membered aromatic heterocycle with one  oxygen, one nitrogen, and three carbon atoms. Isomers include 1,2-oxazole and 1,3-oxazole.

name: 3,4-dihydrocoumarins
description: 3,4-dihydrogenated coumarins. Coumarin is a bicyclic compound that a 1-benzopyran carrying an oxo group at the 2-position.

name: 6,7-dihydroxycoumarins
description: Coumarins bearing two hydroxyl groups at positions 6 and 7 of the coumarin skeleton, respectively.

name: 7,8-dihydroxycoumarins
description: Coumarins bearing two hydroxyl groups at the C7- and C8-positions of the coumarin skeleton, respectively.

name: Halogenated steroids
description: Compounds containing an steroid backbone, with at least one hydrogen substituted by a halogen atom.

name: Cyclohexanols
description: Compounds containing an alcohol group attached to a cyclohexane ring.

name: Tetrahydrofurans
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated, aliphatic, five-membered ring where a carbon is replaced by an oxygen.

name: Diarylheptanoids
description: Phenylpropanoids with a structure containing two  aromatic rings joined by a seven carbons (a 1,7-diphenylheptane skeleton) and may have various substituents.

name: Linear diarylheptanoids
description: Diarylheptanoids with an open heptane chain. The two aromatic rings are linked only by the heptane chain.

name: Cyclic diarylheptanoids
description: Diarylheptanoids where the two aromatic rings of the skeleton are joined by a CC bond or an ether group, in addition to the heptane chain.

name: Phenalenes
description: Aromatic hydrocarbons containing a cyclohexene ring fused to both benzenes of a naphthalene ring system, so as to form a triad.

name: Phenalenones
description: Compounds containing a phenalene ring system, which carries a keto group.

name: Phenalanes
description: Aromatic hydrocarbons containing a cyclohexene ring fused to both benzenes of a naphthalene ring system, so as to form a triad.

name: Emetine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure characterized by the presence of both an isoquinoline and a benzoquinolizidine nuclei.

name: Aristolactams
description: Phenanthrenic compounds containing a five-membered lactam ring and a 1,3-dioxolane ring fused to the phenanthrene ring system.

name: Benzophenanthridine alkaloids
description: Polycyclic alkaloids with a structure based on the benzo[c]phenanthridine skeleton. They derived from tetrahydroprotoberberine precursors by oxidation of the C6-N bond followed by cyclization of C6 on to position 13.

name: Dihydrobenzophenanthridine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids containing a dihydrobenzophenanthridine skeleton, which is a tetracyclic compound containing a benzene fused to a dihydrophenanthridine moiety.

name: Eburnan-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the eburnan skeleton, that arises from rearrangement of the aspidospermidine ring system, involving migration of C-21 from C-7 to C-2, fission of the 2,16-bond, and attachment of C-16 to N-1.

name: Plumeran-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the plumeran skeleton. Plumeran is a pentacyclic compound that consists of a pyrrolidine  ring shed to the quinoline moiety of pyrido[3,2-c]carbazole ring system.

name: Benzylamines
description: Organic compounds containing benzylamine, which consists of a benzene group attached to an amine group.

name: Cyclohexylamines
description: Organic compounds containing a cyclohexylamine moiety, which consist of a cyclohexane ring attached to an amine group.

name: Peroxols
description: Monosubstituted derivatives of hydrogen peroxide, with the general formula ROOH, where R is an organic group.

name: Ergoline and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an ergoline moiety, which is structurally characterized by he presence of a 4,6,6a,7,8,9,10,10a-octahydroindolo[4,3-fg] quinoline.

name: Lysergic acids and derivatives
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the lysergic acid skeleton.

name: 4'-O-methylisoflavones
description: Isoflavones with methoxy groups attached to the C4' atom of the isoflavone backbone.

name: 7-O-methylisoflavones
description: Isoflavones with methoxy groups attached to the C7 atom of the isoflavone backbone.

name: 3'-O-methylisoflavones
description: Flavones with methoxy groups attached to the C2' atom of the isoflavone backbone.

name: Diazirines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a diazirine ring, which is a three-membered unsaturated cycle with one carbon atom, and two nitrogen atoms joined by a double bond.

name: Triazinanes
description: Compounds containing a triazinane ring, which is a six-membered saturated heterocycle with  three nitrogen ring atoms and three ring carbon atoms.

name: Diphenylpyrroles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds with a structure based on a pyrrole ring linked to exactly two phenyl groups.

name: Chlorocatechols
description: Catechols having one or more chlorine atoms attached to the benzene ring.

name: 4-chlorocatechols
description: Chlorocatechols with the chlorine atom attached at position C4 of the benzene ring.

name: 3-chlorocatechols
description: Chlorocatechols with the chlorine atom attached at position C3 of the benzene ring.

name: Benzodioxanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a dioxane ring. Dioxane a six-member saturated ring of two oxygen atoms and four carbon atoms.

name: Benzo-1,2-dioxanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,2-dioxane ring.

name: Benzo-1,3-dioxanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,3-dioxane ring.

name: Benzo-1,4-dioxanes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,4-dioxane ring.

name: Phenylbenzodioxanes
description: Benzodioxanes having a phenyl group attached to the dioxane moiety.

name: Phenylbenzo-1,3-dioxanes
description: Benzo-1,3-dioxanes having a phenyl group attached to the 1,3-dioxane moiety.

name: Phenylbenzo-1,4-dioxanes
description: Benzo-1,3-dioxanes having a phenyl group attached to the 1,4-dioxane moiety.

name: Anthocyanidin 3-O-p-coumaroyl glycosides
description: Anthocyanidin 3-O-glycosides where the carbohydrate moiety is esterified with a p-coumaric acid. P-coumaric acid is an organic derivative of cinnamic acid, that carries a hydroxyl group at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: Anthocyanidin 3-O-6-p-coumaroyl glycosides
description: Anthocyanidin 3-O-glycosides where the carbohydrate moiety is esterified at the C6 position with a p-coumaric acid. P-coumaric acid is an organic derivative of cinnamic acid, that carries a hydroxyl group at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: Polyphenyl ethers
description: Polymers of unsubstituted phenoxy groups linked through ether bonds.

name: Lupin alkaloids
description: Alkaloids extracted from the lupinus species. They usually possess a bi-, tri-, or tetracyclic skeleton consisting of one or more quinolizidine moieties.

name: Lupinine-type alkaloids
description: Lupin alkaloids with a structure based on the lupinine skeleton, which is a bicyclic compound consisting of a quinolizidine.

name: Cytisine and derivatives
description: Lupin alkaloids with a structure based on the cytisine skeleton, which is a tetracyclic ketone containing fused pyridine and piperidine rings that form pyrido[1,2a][1,5]diazocin-8-one.

name: Steroidal alkaloids
description: Alkaloids characterized by the presence of one or more alkylamino substituents attached to a steroidal skeleton. These are azasteroids in which a nitrogen atom forms an integral part of the steroid nucleus or may be present in the side chain.

name: Buxus alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a triterpenoid-steroid pregnane type structure with C-4 methyl groups, a 9beta,10beta-cycloartenol system, and a degraded C-20 side chain. Structurally, they are  derivatives of either a 9beta,10beta-cyclo-4,4,14alpha-trimethyl-5alpha-pregnane or a 9(10->19)abeo 4,4,14alpha-trimethyl-5alpha-pregnane system.

name: Samamine-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure that is based on the samamine skeleton, a tetracyclic compound consisting of and azepane ring fuse a saturated cyclopenta[a]naphthalene derivative.

name: Jerveratrum-type alkaloids
description: Steroidal alkaloids with a structure that is based on the jervane ring system. Jerveratrum alkaloids have alkamines with 1-3 oxygen atoms, and occur as such or as monoglycosides.

name: Cerveratrum-type alkaloids
description: Steroidal alkaloids containing the cevane (23-methyl-4- azahexacyclo[12.11.0.0^{2,11}.0^{4,9}.0^{15,24}.0^{18,23}]pentacosane) moiety, which is a six ring system. Cerveratrum alkaloids have 7-9 oxygen atoms and occur as free alkamines or esters of simple aliphatic or aromatic acids.

name: Pregnane-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the pregnane skeleton, which is characterized by the presence of monomethylamino or dimethylamino substituents either at C-3 and/or at the C-20 position in basic steroidal skeleton.

name: Conanine-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the conanine skeleton.

name: Atisane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the atisane skeleton, which is a tetracyclic compound containing the [2,2,2]bicyc1ic ring system with the C15-C16 bridge attached at C12.

name: Benzodifurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a to furan rings fused to a central benzene ring. They can be grouped in angular and linear benzodifurans.

name: Angular benzodifurans
description: Benzodifurans containing angularly fused benzene and furan rings.

name: Vobasan alkaloids
description: Alkaloids containing the vobasan skeleton.

name: Lysergamides
description: Amides of Lysergic acids.

name: Clavines and derivatives
description: Hydroxy and dehydro derivatives of 6,8-dimethylergolenes and the corresponding ergolines.

name: Ibogan-type alkaloids
description: Indole alkaloids with a structure based on the ibogamine skeleton or a derivative thereof. Ibogamine is a pentacyclic heterocyclic compound consisting of an indole fused to an azepane-containing tricyclic moiety ring. Iboga alkaloids arise from the cyclization of a secodine-type precursor through the formation of a 16,21 bond.

name: Strychnos alkaloids
description: Alkaloids having a core structure based on the strychnan, stemmadenine (seco-curan), or the akuammicine (curan) skeleton.

name: Corynanthean-type alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the corynanthean nucleus, which is a tetracycle characterized by an indole fused to a quinolizidine. Additionally, the quinolizidine ring system is substituted to a 2-methylpropyl group and one ethyl group.

name: Cinnamyl alcohols
description: Aromatic alcohols containing a 3-phenylprop-2-en-1-ol moiety.

name: Aspidospermatan-type alkaloids
description: Tryptophan-derived alkaloids that are derived from the fusion of tryptamine and a terpene unit (generally either 9 or 10 carbons). Aspidospermine and aspidospermidine (along with tabersonine) are the archetypical members of the Aspidosperma alkaloids.

name: Vinca alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a dimeric chemical structure composed of an indole nucleus (catharanthine), and a dihydroindole nucleus (vindoline), joined together.

name: Amidoximes
description: Amidines, in which the imino nitrogen is substituted by a hydroxy group.

name: 3-sulfobenzoic acids
description: Sulfobenzoic acid carrying the sulfonyl group at the 3-position of the benzene group.

name: 4-sulfobenzoic acids
description: Sulfobenzoic acid carrying the sulfonyl group at the 4-position of the benzene group.

name: Iodophenols
description: Halophenols carrying a iodine on the benzene ring.

name: Bromophenols
description: Halophenols carrying a bromine on the benzene ring.

name: Fluorophenols
description: Halophenols carrying a fluorine on the benzene ring.

name: Chlorophenols
description: Halophenols carrying a chlorine on the benzene ring.

name: M-bromophenols
description: Bromophenols carrying a iodine at the C3 position of the benzene ring.

name: O-bromophenols
description: Bromophenols carrying a iodine at the C2 position of the benzene ring.

name: P-bromophenols
description: Bromophenols carrying a iodine at the C4 position of the benzene ring.

name: M-chlorophenols
description: Chlorophenols carrying a iodine at the C3 position of the benzene ring.

name: O-chlorophenols
description: Chlorophenols carrying a iodine at the C2 position of the benzene ring.

name: P-chlorophenols
description: Chlorophenols carrying a iodine at the C4 position of the benzene ring.

name: M-fluorophenols
description: Fluorophenols carrying a iodine at the C3 position of the benzene ring.

name: O-fluorophenols
description: Fluorophenols carrying a iodine at the C2 position of the benzene ring.

name: P-fluorophenols
description: Fluorophenols carrying a iodine at the C4 position of the benzene ring.

name: M-iodophenols
description: Iodophenols carrying a iodine at the C3 position of the benzene ring.

name: O-iodophenols
description: Iodophenols carrying a iodine at the C2 position of the benzene ring.

name: P-iodophenols
description: Iodophenols carrying a iodine at the C4 position of the benzene ring.

name: Erythrinanes
description: Erythrina alkaloids possessing either a 6-5-6-6-membered indoloisoquinoline core or a derivative thereof.

name: Pyridodiazepines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyridine fused to a diazepine ring. Pyridine is 6-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and a nitrogen atom. Diazepine is a 7-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers.

name: M-sulfanylbenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids (or derivatives) which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 3, respectively.

name: P-sulfanylbenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids (or derivatives) which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 4, respectively.

name: M-sulfanylbenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 3, respectively.

name: P-sulfanylbenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 4, respectively.

name: 1,3-oxazinanes
description: Compounds contain an oxazinane ring with the nitrogen atom and the oxygen atom at positions 1  and 3, respectively.

name: Pavine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the pavine skeleton.

name: Organoboron compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a carbon-boron bond.

name: 1,2,3-triazinanes
description: Triazinanes having three nitrogen ring atoms at the 1-, 2-, and 3- positions.

name: 1,2,4-triazinanes
description: Triazinanes having three nitrogen ring atoms at the 1-, 2-, and 4- positions.

name: 1,3,5-triazinanes
description: Triazinanes having three nitrogen ring atoms at the 1-, 3-, and 5- positions.

name: Organic trisulfides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RSSSR' (R,R'=alkyl, aryl).

name: Organic disulfides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RSSR' (R,R' = alkyl, aryl).

name: Prenylated hydroquinones
description: Quinones with a structure characterized by the hydroquinone ring substituted by an prenyl side-chain.

name: Prenylquinones
description: Quinones with a structure characterized by the quinone ring substituted by an prenyl side-chain.

name: Thianthrenes
description: Organic compounds containing a thianthrene moiety. Thianthrene is a tricyclic ring system that consists of two benzene rings fused to each other through a 1,4-dithiin ring.

name: Benzodithiins
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a dithiin ring. Dithiin is an unsaturated six-member heterocycle containing four carbon atoms, two sulfur atoms and two double bonds.

name: 1,4-benzodithiins
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,4-dithiin ring.

name: N-methylpyrroles
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a N-methylated pyrrole.

name: Cinnamic acid amides
description: Amides of cinnamic acids. Cinnamic acid is an aromatic compound containing a benzene and a carboxylic acid group forming 3-phenylprop-2-enoic acid.

name: Phenylpropanes
description: Organic compounds containing a phenylpropane moiety.

name: O-glucuronides
description: Glucuronides in which the aglycone is linked to the carbohydrate unit through an O-glycosidic bond.

name: C-glucuronides
description: Glucuronides in which the aglycone is linked to the carbohydrate unit through a C-glycosidic bond.

name: S-glucuronides
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing glucuronic acid linked to another substance through a S-glycosidic bond.

name: Dibenzopyrans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure containing a dibenzopyran moiety, made up of two benzene rings fused to a central pyran ring.

name: Dibenzothiophenes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure containing a dibenzothiophene moiety, made up of two benzene rings fused to a central thiophene ring.

name: Isoflav-3-enes
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on the 3-phenylchromene skeleton, with a double bond between the C3 and C4 carbon atoms of the chromene moiety.

name: Isoflav-3-enones
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on an isoflav-3-ene skeleton bearing an oxo-group at position C2.

name: Aloperine and related alkaloids
description: Lupin Alkaloids with a structure based on the aloperine skeleton. Aloperine is a tetracyclic compound made up of a quinolizidine and a decahydroquinoline joined to  form 3,15-diazatetracycloheptadecane.

name: Pyrido[2,3,4-kl]acridines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure based on the pyrido[2,3,4-kl]acridine skeleton.

name: Pyrrolo[4,3,2-de]quinolines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure based on the Pyrrolo[4,3,2-de]quinoline skeleton.

name: 5-methoxypsoralens
description: Psoralens containing a methoxy group attached at the C5 position of the psoralen group.

name: 8-methoxypsoralens
description: Psoralens containing a methoxy group attached at the C8 position of the psoralen group.

name: Thiochromanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a thiochromane moiety.

name: Isothiochromanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an isothiochromane moiety.

name: Pyrazolidinones
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazolidinone moiety.

name: Hydrocarbons
description: Organic compounds made up only of carbon and hydrogen atoms.

name: Olefins
description: Acyclic and cyclic hydrocarbons having one or more carbon-carbon double bonds, apart from the formal ones in aromatic compounds. The class of olefins subsumes alkenes and cycloalkenes and the corresponding polyenes.

name: Acyclic olefins
description: Olefins that do not contain a ring in their structure.

name: Cyclic olefins
description: Olefins that contain at least one ring in their structure.

name: Alkatrienes
description: Acyclic hydrocarbons that contain exactly three carbon-to-carbon double bonds.

name: Alkatetraenes
description: Acyclic hydrocarbons that contain exactly four carbon-to-carbon double bonds.

name: Acetylenes
description: Acyclic (branched or unbranched) and cyclic (with or without side chain) hydrocarbons having one or more carbon to carbon triple bonds.

name: Cyclic acetylenes
description: Cyclic hydrocarbons containing one or more acetylene groups.

name: Acyclic acetylenes
description: Acyclic hydrocarbons containing one or more acetylene groups.

name: Monocyclic acetylenes
description: Monocyclic hydrocarbons containing one or more acetylene groups.

name: Polycyclic acetylenes
description: Polycyclic hydrocarbons containing one or more acetylene groups.

name: Aziridinones
description: Compounds with a structure containing an aziridines ring bearing one carbonyl group. They are cyclic amides of acetic acid.

name: Lactims
description: Cyclic amides of carboximidic acids. Lactams are tautomers of lactams, having an endocyclic carbon-nitrogen double bond.

name: Phosphorus mustard compounds
description: Compounds having two beta-haloalkyl groups bound to a phosphorus atom.

name: 1,1-diols
description: Alcohols in which two hydroxy groups are bonded to the same atom.

name: Organic phosphoric acid monoamides
description: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RNP(O)(O)=O (R=alkyl, aryl).

name: Vinyl fluorides
description: Vinyl halides in which a fluorine atom is bonded to an sp2-hybridised carbon atom.

name: Vinyl iodides
description: Vinyl halides in which a iodine atom is bonded to an sp2-hybridised carbon atom.

name: Vinyl chlorides
description: Vinyl halides in which a chlorine atom is bonded to an sp2-hybridised carbon atom.

name: Vinyl bromides
description: Vinyl halides in which a bromine atom is bonded to an sp2-hybridised carbon atom.

name: Acyl halides
description: Organic compounds with the general structure RC(=O)X, where X is a halogen atom.

name: Aryl halides
description: Organic compounds containing an aromatic ring (or ring system) carrying a C-X bond.

name: Alkyl halides
description: Organic compounds containing a linear aliphatic chain (or ring system) carrying a C-X bond, where X is a halogen atom.

name: Vinyl halides
description: Organic compounds in which the halogen atom is bonded to an sp2-hybridised carbon atom of a carbon-carbon double bond (C=C).

name: Imidoyl halides
description: Organic compounds containing the imidoyl halide functional group, with the general structure R(X)C=NR' (R, R'=H, alkyl, aryl; X = halogen).

name: Elemane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the elemane skeleton. Elemane is a monocyclic compound consisting of a cyclohexane ring substituted with a methyl group, an ethyl group, and two 1-methylethyl groups at the 1-, 1-, 2-, and 4-position, respectively.

name: Pseudoguaianes
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the pseudoguaiane skeleton, which arises by the migration of the a methyl group of the bicyclic guaiane skeleton from the C4 to the C5 position.

name: Guaianes
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based on the guaiane skeleton. Guaiane is a bicyclic compound consisting of a decahydroazulene moiety, substituted with two methyl groups and a 1-methylethyl group at the 1-, 4-, and 7-position, respectively.

name: Tigliane and ingenane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids containing the tigliane or ingenane carbon skeleton. The tigliane skeleton is a tetracyclic ring that consists of the 4/7/6/3 ring junction. It is derived from casbane by 6,10- and 5,14-cyclizations and is a framework of phorbol. The ingenane skeleton is derived by rearrangement of tigliane.

name: Jatrophane and cyclojatrophane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the jatrophane or the 9,13-jatrophane skeleton. Jatrophane can be derived from casbane by 6,10-cyclization and opening of the cyclopropane. Cyclojatrophane diterpenoids are based on the 9,13-cyclization of the jatrophane skeleton yields the 9,13-cyclojatrophane skeleton.

name: Scalarane sesterterpenoids
description: Sesterterpenoids with a structure based on the scalarane backbone. Scalarane is a tetracyclic compound, which is similar the homoandrostane with five methyl groups at the 4-, 4-, 8-, 17-, 17a-positions.

name: Briarane diterpenoids
description: Marine diterpenoids with a structure based on the briarane (3,8-cyclocembrane) skeleton.

name: Quinonimines
description: Imines derived from quinones by replacement of one or both oxygens by =NR.

name: M-quinonimines
description: Quinonimines in which the imine groups are in a meta-relationship.

name: O-quinonimines
description: Quinonimines in which the imine groups are in a ortho-relationship.

name: P-quinonimines
description: Quinonimines in which the imine groups are in a para-relationship.

name: Isoflavonoid C-glycosides
description: C-glycosylated derivatives of isoflavonoids, which are natural products derived from 3-phenylchromen-4-one.

name: Homoisoflavanones
description: Homoisoflavonoids with a structure based on the chromanone system. Chromanone is a bicyclic compound consisting of a 3,4-dihydro-1-benzopyran, which bears a ketone group at the 4-position.

name: 1,2-diaryl-2-propen-1-ols
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on the 1,2-diaryl-2-propen-1-ol skeleton.

name: Isoflav-2-enes
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on the 3-phenylchromene skeleton, with a double bond between the C2 and C3 carbon atoms of the chromene moiety.

name: Milbemycins
description: A group of macrolides with a structure containing a 16-membered lactone ring fused to a 1,7-dioxaspiroundecane ring system and to either a benzofuran (or hydrogenated derivative thereof). In some cases (e.g. Milbemycin E), the tetrahydrofuranyl ring is missing. Milbemycins can be o-glycosylated at C13 to form Avermectins. Milbemycins are produced by Streptomyces species.

name: Perylenequinones
description: Heterocyclic compounds characterized by  two 8-hydroxy-1,4-dihydronaphthalen-1-one moieties joined together one or two CC-bonds.

name: 1,2-dithiole-3-thiones
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiole ring that bears a C=S group.

name: Phorbol esters
description: Tigliane diterpenoids which are esters of phorbol.

name: 4-hydroxycoumarins
description: Coumarins that contain one or more hydroxyl groups attached to C4-position the coumarin skeleton.

name: Hydroxycoumarins
description: Coumarins that contain one or more hydroxyl groups attached to the coumarin skeleton.

name: 7-hydroxycoumarins
description: Coumarins that contain one or more hydroxyl groups attached to the C7 position the coumarin skeleton.

name: Borinanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a saturated aliphatic six-membered ring consisting of five carbon atoms and one boron atom.

name: Alpha-hydroxy ketones
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxylic acid, and an amine group attached to the alpha carbon atom, relative to the C=O group.

name: Beta-hydroxy ketones
description: Ketones containing a hydroxyl group attached to the beta-carbon atom, relative to the C=O group.

name: 3-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-3 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 3'-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-3' position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Eunicellane and asbestinane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on either the eunicellane (5,14-cyclocembrane) or the asbestinane skeleton.

name: Phenyltropanes
description: Compounds containing a phenyl group linked to a tropane moiety. Tropane is an organonitrogenous  [3.2.1] bicyclic organic compound.

name: Diazepanes
description: Compounds containing a diazepane rings, which is a saturated seven-membered ring with 2 nitrogen atoms and five carbon atoms.

name: 1,2-diazepanes
description: Diazepanes having the two nitrogen atoms at position 1 and 2 of the diazepane ring.

name: 1,3-diazepanes
description: Diazepanes having the two nitrogen atoms at position 1 and 3 of the diazepane ring.

name: 1,4-diazepanes
description: Diazepanes having the two nitrogen atoms at position 1 and 4 of the diazepane ring.

name: 1,2,4-oxadiazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxadiazole ring with the oxygen and the two nitrogen atoms at positions 1, 2, and 4, respectively.

name: 1,3,4-oxadiazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxadiazole ring with the oxygen and the two nitrogen atoms at positions 1, 3, and 4, respectively.

name: Ortho esters
description: Compounds having the general structure RC(OR')3 ( R' not H), or the structure C(OR')4 ( R' not H).

name: Ortho amides
description: Hypothetical  Compounds having the general structure RC(NH2)3, and N-substituted derivatives thereof.

name: Ortho acids
description: Ortho acid derivatives of carboxylic acids, with the general formula RC(OH)3.

name: Sulfimides
description: Organic derivatives of sulfimide, with the general formula RN=S(R=organic group).

name: Mutilane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the mutilane skeleton.

name: Aphidicolane and stemodane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the aphidicolane or the stemodane  skeleton.

name: 1,3-isoquinolinediones
description: Isoquinoline derivatives carrying one C=O group at positions 1, and 3 respectively.

name: 1,4-isoquinolinediones
description: Isoquinoline derivatives carrying a C=O group at positions 1 and 4, respectively.

name: Flavonoid O-glucuronides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to glucuronic acid.

name: Cycloheptafurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a cycloheptane derivative fused to a furan. Furan is a five-membered aromatic ring with four carbon atoms and one oxygen atom.

name: Cycloheptapyrans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a cycloheptane derivative fused to a pyran. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds.

name: Cyclopentanols
description: Compounds containing a cyclopentane ring that carries an alcohol group.

name: Dioxepines
description: Compounds containing a dioxepane ring, which is a seven-membered aliphatic unsaturated ring with two oxygen atoms and five carbon atoms.

name: 1,4-dioxepines
description: Dioxepines with the two ring oxygen atoms at position 1 and 4, respectively.

name: Dioxepanes
description: Compounds containing a dioxepane ring, which is a seven-membered aliphatic saturated ring with two oxygen atoms and five carbon atoms.

name: 1,3-dioxepanes
description: Dioxepanes with the two ring oxygen atoms at position 1 and 3, respectively.

name: 1,4-dioxepanes
description: Dioxepanes with the two ring oxygen atoms at position 1 and 4, respectively.

name: Guanidinobenzoic acids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a guanidine group linked to the benzene ring of a benzoic acid.

name: Aminobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids containing an amine group attached to the benzene moiety.

name: Long-chain fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with an aliphatic tail that contains between 13 and 21 carbon atoms.

name: Very long-chain fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with an aliphatic tail that contains at least 22 carbon atoms.

name: Long-chain fatty alcohols
description: Fatty alcohols that have an aliphatic tail of 13 to 21 carbon atoms.

name: Piperidinesulfonamides
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfonamide group linked to a piperidine ring.

name: Tetrahydroisoquinolines
description: Tetrahydrogenated isoquinoline derivatives.

name: 1-phenyltetrahydroisoquinolines
description: Compounds containing a phenyl group attached to the C1-atom of a tetrahydroisoquinoline moiety.

name: 4-phenyltetrahydroisoquinolines
description: Compounds containing a phenyl group attached to the C4-atom of a tetrahydroisoquinoline moiety.

name: Dihydroisoquinolines
description: Isoquinoline derivatives where exactly two carbon atoms joined by an aromatic bond are linked with a hydrogen atom each, resulting in a CC single bond.

name: Sulfonohydrazides
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RS(=O)(=O)NHNH2.

name: 3-hydroxyacyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a 3-hydroxyl acylated coenzyme A derivative.

name: Phytoceramides
description: N-acylated 4-hydroxysphinganine.

name: N-formyl-alpha amino acids
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid which bears a formyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: N-formyl-alpha amino acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an alpha amino acid (or a derivative thereof) which bears a formyl group at its terminal nitrogen atom.

name: Tetracarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids containing exactly four carboxyl groups.

name: Hexacarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids containing exactly six carboxyl groups.

name: 3-hydroxy delta-1-steroids
description: 3-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2.

name: 3-hydroxy delta-1,4-steroids
description: 3-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2, as well as positions 4 and 5.

name: 3-hydroxy delta-4-steroids
description: 3-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 4 and 5.

name: 3-hydroxy delta-5-steroids
description: 3-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 5 and 6.

name: 3-oxo delta-1-steroids
description: 3-oxo steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2.

name: 3-oxo delta-1,4-steroids
description: 3-oxo steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2, as well as positions 4 and 5.

name: 3-oxo delta-4-steroids
description: 3-oxo steroids containing a double bond between positions  3 and 4.

name: 3-oxo delta-5-steroids
description: 3-oxo steroids containing a double bond between positions 4 and 5.

name: Delta-1-steroids
description: Steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2.

name: Delta-1,4-steroids
description: Steroids containing a double bond between positions 1 and 2, as well as positions 4 and 5.

name: Delta-4-steroids
description: Steroids containing a double bond between positions 4 and 5.

name: Delta-5-steroids
description: Steroids containing a double bond between positions 5 and 6.

name: N-phenylthioureas
description: Compounds containing a N-phenylthiourea moiety, which is structurally characterized by a phenyl group linked to one nitrogen atom of a thiourea group.

name: N-acyl-phenylthioureas
description: Thiourea derivatives where one nitrogen atom of the urea group is linked to a phenyl group and the other is acylated.

name: N-acyl-phenylureas
description: Urea derivatives where one nitrogen atom of the urea group is linked to a phenyl group and the other is acylated.

name: Acylguanidines
description: N-acylated derivatives of guanidines.

name: Delta-7-steroids
description: Steroids containing a double bond between positions 7 and 8.

name: 3-hydroxy delta-7-steroids
description: 3-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 7 and 8.

name: 3-oxo delta-7-steroids
description: 3-oxo steroids containing a double bond between positions 6 and 7.

name: 6-aminopurines
description: Purines that carry an amino group at position 6. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: 4-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-4 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 4'-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-4' position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 6-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-6 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids in which one or more hydroxyl groups are attached to the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 5-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-5 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 7-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-7 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: 8-hydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group at the C-8 position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Pentacarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Carboxylic acids containing exactly five carboxyl groups.

name: Anthocyanidin-3-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing one anthocyanidin moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety at the C3-position.

name: Anthocyanidin-5-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing one anthocyanidin moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety at the C5-position.

name: C19-gibberellins
description: Gibberellins containing 19 carbon atoms, with the COOH group in position 7. In nearly all C19-gibberellins, the carboxyl group at C-4 forms a lactone  ring at C-10, a configuration which arises in connection with the loss of the extra C-20 atom.

name: C20-gibberellins
description: Gibberellins with carboxy groups in positions 7 and 18 and some also in 20, while others have an aldehyde group in the latter position.

name: Alpha-halocarboxylic acids
description: Carboxylic acids containing a halogen atom bonded to the alpha carbon atom.

name: Alpha-halocarboxylic acid derivatives
description: Carboxylic acid derivatives containing a halogen atom bonded to the alpha carbon atom.

name: Hydroxycinnamic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of hydroxycinnamic acids.

name: Hydroxycinnamic acid glycosides
description: Glycosylated hydoxycinnamic acids derivatives.

name: Sulfated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids that are sulfated at one or more positions.

name: Monohydroxyflavonoids
description: Flavonoids that bear one hydroxyl group on the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Phenanthrols
description: Compounds containing a phenanthrene (or its hydrogenated derivative) to which a hydroxyl group is attached.

name: Aminosalicylic acids and derivatives
description: Salicylic acids or derivatives carrying an amino group on the benzene ring.

name: Aminosalicylic acids
description: Salicylic acids carrying an amino group on the benzene ring.

name: 4-aminosalicylic acids
description: Aminosalicylic acids carrying an amino group at the C-4 atom of the benzene ring.

name: Flavan-3-ols
description: Flavans that bear and hydroxyl group at position 3 (B ring), but not at position 4.

name: Flavan-4-ols
description: Flavans that bear and hydroxyl group at position 4 (B ring), but not at the 3-position.

name: Organophosphinic acids and derivatives
description: P-hydrocarbyl derivatives of phosphinic acid.

name: Phosphinic acid esters
description: Compounds containing a phosphinic acid ester group.

name: Benzacridines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds with a structure characterized by a benzene ring fused to an acridine ring system.

name: Isoaporphines
description: Alkaloids with a structure that contains the isoaporphine skeleton. Isoaporphine is an isomer of aporphine, with the difference that the N atom of the quinoline moiety is at the 1-position instead of the 6-position. This compounds also include oxoisoaporphines, which bear an oxo group at the 7-position. Oxoisoaporphines are believed to arise from aporphines via a spirodienone rearrangement.

name: N-acylpyrrolidines
description: N-Acylated Pyrrolidine derivatives. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Gamma-glutamyl amino acids
description: Dipeptides consisting of any C-terminal amino acid having a gamma-glutamyl residue attached at the N alpha-position.

name: Gamma-glutamyl peptides
description: Oligo- and polypeptides consisting of any C-terminal alpha peptide having a gamma-glutamyl residue attached at the N alpha-position.

name: 3-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 3-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 3-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 3-position of the steroid backbone.

name: Polychlorinated dibenzofurans
description: Organic compounds containing two or more chlorine atoms attached to a dibenzofuran moiety.

name: Polychlorinated biphenyls
description: Organic compounds containing at least two chlorine atoms attached to either benzene ring of the biphenyl moiety.

name: Pyrrolidine-2-ones
description: Pyrrolidines which bear a C=O group at position 2 of the pyrrolidine ring.

name: Pyrrolidine-3-ones
description: Pyrrolidines which bear a C=O group at position 3 of the pyrrolidine ring.

name: Dicarboximides
description: Carboxylic acid amides in which the two acyl groups linked to the central nitrogen atoms are carboacyl groups.

name: C-nitroso compounds
description: Nitroso compounds with he general formula RN=O, where R is an organic group.

name: 4-aminosalicyclic acids and derivatives
description: Aminosalicylic acids or derivatives carrying an amino group at the C-4 atom of the benzene ring.

name: Folic acids
description: Heterocyclic compounds based on the 4-[(pteridin-6-ylmethyl)amino]benzoic acid skeleton conjugated with one or more L-glutamate units.

name: Tetrahydropteroic acids and derivatives
description: Heterocyclic compounds based on the 5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteroic acid skeleton (or derivative thereof).

name: N-acylneuraminic acids
description: Neuraminic acids carrying an N-acyl substituent.

name: N-acylneuraminic acids and derivatives
description: Neuraminic acids (or derivatives thereof) carrying an N-acyl substituent.

name: Neuraminic acids
description: Carbohydrate derivatives containing a neuraminic acid moiety.

name: 25-azasteroids and derivatives
description: Azasteroids where the carbon atom at position 25 is replaced by a nitrogen atom.

name: 4-azasteroids and derivatives
description: Azasteroids where the carbon atom at position 4 is replaced by a nitrogen atom.

name: p-Bromobenzenesulfonates
description: Benzenesulfonic acids (or derivative thereof) carrying a bromine at the para- position.

name: 20-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 20-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 11-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 11-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 16-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 16-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: C24-propyl sterols and derivatives
description: Sterols that carry a hydroxyl group at the 3-position, and a propyl group at the 24-position of the steroid backbone.

name: Indan-1-spirocyclohexanes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a cyclohexane moiety linked to the 1-position of an indane moiety in a spiro configuration.

name: Carbapenams
description: Beta-lactams with a saturated carbapenem skeleton.

name: Glycosyldiacylglycerols
description: Diacylglycerols that carry a saccharide moiety linked to the glycerol.

name: Trisubstituted amine oxides and derivatives
description: Amine oxides where the N atom is trisubstituted with three organic groups.

name: 1,8-naphthalic anhydrides
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene carrying two carboxyl groups at the 1- and 8-positions. In naphthalene anhydrides, the two carboxyl groups at the 1- and 8-positions share one oxygen atom.

name: 1-carboxy-2-haloaromatic compounds
description: Aromatic compounds containing 1 carboxyl group and a C-X (X = halogen) group at adjacent positions of an aromatic ring.

name: Aromatic alcohols
description: Compounds containing an alcohol group attached to an aromatic carbon.

name: Arylsufonic acids
description: Organic compounds containing an aryl group attached to the sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof).

name: 1-sulfo,2-unsubstituted aromatic compounds
description: An arylsulfonic acid carrying the sulfonic acid group at the 1-position, and no substitute at the 2-position of the aromatic ring.

name: Aldoximes
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RC(H)=NOH (R = organyl).

name: Ketoximes
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RC(R')=NOH (R,R' = organyl).

name: N-aliphatic s-triazines
description: N-aliphatic amine derivatives of 1,3,5-triazines. 1,3,5-triazines are aromatic compounds having three nitrogen ring atoms at the 1-, 3-, and 5- positions.

name: Acylsulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Acylated products of sulfonic acids (or derivatives).

name: Acylsulfonic acids
description: Acylated derivatives of sulfonic acids.

name: 2-polyprenyl-6-methoxyphenols
description: Compounds containing a polyisoprene chain attached at the 2-position of a 6-methoxyphenol group.

name: Chlorohydroquinones
description: Organic compounds containing a chlorine atom attached to a hydroquinone.

name: Peroxybenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds with a structure containing a benzoic acid or a derivative thereof.

name: Medium-chain fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with an aliphatic tail that contains between 4 and 12 carbon atoms.

name: Benzylpiperidines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a piperidine ring conjugated to a benzyl group.

name: 2-benzylpiperidines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzyl group attached to the 2-position of a piperidine.

name: 3-benzylpiperidines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzyl group attached to the 3-position of a piperidine.

name: 4-benzylpiperidines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzyl group attached to the 4-position of a piperidine.

name: N-acylimines
description: N-acyl derivatives of imines. Imines are compounds containing an imine functional group, with the general structure RN=CR2 (R = H, hydrocarbyl).

name: Thiadiazinanes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a six-membered saturated heterocycle with two nitrogen, one sulfur, and three carbon atoms.

name: 21-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 21-position of the steroid backbone.

name: Halobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids or derivatives carrying a halogen atom on the benzene ring.

name: Halobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids carrying a halogen atom on the benzene ring.

name: 2-halobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids or derivatives carrying a halogen atom at the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: 3-halobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids or derivatives carrying a halogen atom at the 3-position of the benzene ring.

name: 4-halobenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids or derivatives carrying a halogen atom at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: 2-halobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids carrying a halogen atom at the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: 3-halobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids carrying a halogen atom at the 3-position of the benzene ring.

name: 4-halobenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids carrying a halogen atom at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: O-sulfanylbenzoic acids and derivatives
description: Benzoic acids (or derivatives) which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: O-sulfanylbenzoic acids
description: Benzoic acids which bear a sulfanyl group (R-SH) attached to the benzene ring at positions 1 and 2, respectively.

name: Carbothioic S-acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RCS-OH (R=H, organic group).

name: Carbothioic O-acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RCO-SH (R=H, organic group).

name: Hydrazinesulfinic acids
description: Sulfinic acids with the general formula R-N-NS(=O)=O.

name: Sulfonimidic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RS(O)(=NH)-OH (R=H, organic group).

name: Seleninyl compounds
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RSe(=O)R' (R =  organyl).

name: Selenonyl compounds
description: Organoselenium compounds with the general formula RSe(=O)(=O)R'

name: Sulfinyl compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfinyl group with the general formula RS(=O)R' (R = organyl, R' = any atom but O).

name: Alpha,beta-unsaturated carbonyl compounds
description: Carbonyl compounds with the general structure R#CC(=O)R' or R=CC(=O)R', where R=organyl, R'=H, N, O, organyl group or halide group.

name: Hydrazinecarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organonitrogen compounds with the general formula RN(H)N(H)C(=O)OR' (R = organyl, R = any).

name: Hydrazinecarboxylic acids

name: Hydrazinecarboxamides

name: Aminosulfonyl compounds

name: Hydrazinosulfonyl compounds
description: Hydrazine derivatives with the general formula RS(=O)(=O)N(H)N (R = organyl).

name: Aminosulfinyl compounds
description: Organic sulfinyl compounds with the general formula RS(=O)N(R')R\" (R=organyl; R'-R\" = any atom but N).

name: Carboximidamides

name: Carboximidohydrazides

name: Sulfonimidamides
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RS(=O)=NR' (R = organyl, R' = any atom but N).

name: OS-thioperoxols
description: Thioperoxols with the general formula R-OSH (R = organyl group).

name: SO-thioperoxols
description: Thioperoxols with the general formula R-SOH (R = organyl group).

name: Thioperoxols
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula R-OSH or R-SOH (R = organyl group).

name: Carboperoxoic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RCO-OOH (R=H, organic group).

name: Carboperoxothioic OO-acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RCS-OOH (R=H, organic group).

name: Very long-chain fatty acyl CoAs
description: Acyl CoAs where the group acylated to the coenzyme A moiety is a very long aliphatic chain of 22 carbon atoms or more.

name: Long-chain 3-oxoacyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A derivative, which is  3-oxo acylated long aliphatic chain of 13 to 21 carbon atoms.

name: Very-long-chain 3-oxoacyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A derivative, which is  3-oxo acylated long aliphatic chain of 22 carbon atoms or more.

name: Enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to an acyl chain.

name: 2-enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to a 2-enoyl chain.

name: 3-enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to a 3-enoyl chain.

name: Long-chain enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to a long-chain enoyl chain.

name: Long-chain 2-enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to a long-chain 2-enoyl chain of 13 to 21 carbon atoms.

name: N-acyl-phosphatidylethanolamines
description: Phosphatidylethanolamines with a N-acylated ethanolamine moiety.

name: Glycero-3-phospho-N-acyl-ethanolamines
description: Glycerophosphoethanolamines with a n-acylated ethanolamine moiety.

name: Acyl homoserines
description: N-acylated homoserine derivatives.

name: Sulfonyl azides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RS(=O)(=O)N=[N+][N-] (R = organyl).

name: Urazoles
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a 1,3,4-triazolidine ring carrying two C=O groups at positions 2 and 5.

name: Maleimides
description: Compounds containing a 2,5-pyrroledione moiety.

name: Medium-chain fatty acyl CoAs
description: Acyl CoAs where the group acylated to the coenzyme A moiety is a medium aliphatic chain of 6 to 12 carbon atoms.

name: Medium-chain 2-enoyl CoAs
description: Organic compounds containing a coenzyme A substructure linked to a medium-chain 2-enoyl chain of 5 to 12 carbon atoms.

name: 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl CoAs
description: Acyl-CoAs carrying a 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl chain.

name: Carbo-azosulfones
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RS(R')(=N)=O (R,R' = alkyl groups).

name: 5-monosubstituted hydantoins
description: Organic compounds containing a hydantoin moiety substituted at exactly one position.

name: Aryl-aldehydes
description: Compounds containing an aldehyde group directly attached to an aromatic ring.

name: 2-phenylindoles
description: Indoles substituted at the 2-position with a phenyl group.

name: Thiophene sulfoxides
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a thiophene ring carrying a S=O bond (in some cases, a [S+][O-]).

name: 3-aroylthiophenes
description: Thiophenes which are substituted by an aroyl group at the 3-position.

name: 2-amino-3-aroylthiophenes
description: 3-aroylthiophenes which are substituted by an amino group at the 2-position.

name: 3-aroylfurans
description: Compounds containing a furan moiety which is acylated at the 3-position with an aromatic moiety.

name: Borinic acid derivatives
description: Compounds comprising any derivative of the boronic acid functional group, with the general structure RB(OR'')R' (R,R'=organyl; R''=H atom or Organyl group).

name: Borinic acid esters
description: Compounds comprising the boronic acid ester functional group RB(R')OR'' (R,R',R''=organyl; X= any O,N,Hal residue).

name: Borinic acids
description: Compounds comprising any derivative of the boronic acid functional group, with the general structure RB(R')OH (R,R'=organyl).

name: Organoboroxines
description: Organic compounds containing a boroxine ring B-substituted with an organyl group.

name: Acetohydroxamic acids
description: Organic compounds that contain a hydroxamic acid group carrying a methyl group attached to its carbon center.

name: 3-beta-hydroxy delta-5-steroids
description: 3beta-hydroxy steroids containing a double bond between positions 5 and 6.

name: 11-beta-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a beta-hydroxyl group at the 11-position.

name: 11-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 11-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 16-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 16-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 16-alpha-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a alpha-hydroxyl group at the 16-position.

name: 16-beta-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a beta-hydroxyl group at the 16-position.

name: 3-alpha-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a alpha-hydroxyl group at the 3-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 3-beta-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a beta-hydroxyl group at the 3-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 11-alpha-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a alpha-hydroxyl group at the 11-position.

name: 17-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 17-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 7-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 7-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 7-alpha-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a alpha-hydroxyl group at the 7-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 12-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 12-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 12-alpha-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a alpha-hydroxyl group at the 12-position.

name: 12-beta-hydroxysteroids
description: Hydroxysteroids carrying a beta-hydroxyl group at the 12-position.

name: 7-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 7-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 3-oxo-5-alpha-steroids
description: 5-alpha-steroids carrying a C=O group at the 3-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 6-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 6-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 5,6-epoxysteroids
description: Steroid derivatives sharing two carbon atoms  at the 5- and 6- positions with an epoxide ring.

name: 3-oxo-4-azasteroids
description: Steroids with a structure characterized a C=O group at the 3-position and a nitrogen atom replacing the carbon atom at the 4-position.

name: 3-oxo-5-beta-steroids
description: 5-beta-steroids carrying a C=O group at the 3-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: GalNAcb1-4Galb1-4Glc- (Ganglio series)
description: Neutral glycosphingolipids in which the root sequence is GalNAcb1-4Galb1-4Glc.

name: Glycosphingolipids
description: Sphingolipids containing a saccharide moiety glycosidically attached to the sphingoid base. Although saccharide moieties are mostly O-glycosidically linked to the ceramide moiety, other sphingolipids with glycosidic bonds of other types (e.g. S-,C-, or N-type) has been reported.

name: Sulfenyl compounds
description: Organosulfur compounds a sulfenyl group with the general formula RS (R = organyl).

name: Sulfenyl halides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RSX (R = organyl, X = halogen atom).

name: Sulfinyl halides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula RS(=O)X (R = organyl, X = halogen atom).

name: Monoalkylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids containing exactly one aliphatic chain linked to the glycerol moiety. This chain is the only one linked to the glycerol.

name: Glycerol vinyl ethers
description: Lipids containing a vinyl ether derivative of glycerol.

name: Tosyl compounds
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a tosyl group, with the general formula CH3C6H4S(O2)R (R =  any atom).

name: p-Nitrobenzenesulfonates
description: Benzenesulfonic acids (or derivative thereof) carrying a nitro group at the para- position.

name: p-Methylbenzenesulfonates
description: Benzenesulfonic acids (or derivative thereof) carrying a methyl group at the para- position.

name: Ynolates
description: Organooxygen compounds with the general formula R=C=O (R = organyl).

name: N-hydroxyguanidines
description: Compounds containing a guanidine group in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen at position 1 is substituted by a hydroxyl group.

name: N-arylamides
description: Organic compounds that contain a carboxamide group that is N-linked to a aryl group. They have the generic structure RC(=O)N(R')H, R = organyl group and R'= aryl group.

name: N-aryl-N-hydroxylamides
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring N-linked to a N-hydroxylamide group. They have the generic structure [H]ON(R)C(R')=O, where R= aryl group, R'= organyl group.

name: N-alkylated hydrazones
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a hydrazone group that is substituted with an alkyl group. They have the generic structure RNN=C(R')R\" (R= alkyl group; R',R\"= H or organyl group).

name: Organic Polymers
description: Organic compounds, generally large molecules or macromolecules, which are composed of many repeating units.

name: Polypeptides
description: Peptides containing ten or more amino acid residues.

name: Aminosaccharides
description: Saccharides containing a sugar unit that bears an amino group.

name: Monosaccharide sulfates
description: Monosaccharides that contain a sulfate group linked to the sugar moiety.

name: Disaccharide sulfates
description: Disaccharides carrying  one or more sulfate group on a sugar unit.

name: Oligosaccharide sulfates
description: Carbohydrates containing between 3 and 9 sugar units, one of which bear one or more sulfate groups.

name: Naphthalene sulfonates
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group at one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: Alkanesulfonic acids
description: Organic acids containing an alkane chain linked to a sulfonic acid group. They have the general structure RS(=O)2-OH (R = alkyl).

name: Phenyl-1,2,4-triazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazole substituted by a phenyl group.

name: Phenyl-1,2,3-triazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2,3-triazole substituted by a phenyl group.

name: Pyridyltriazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring attached to a triazole ring.

name: Pyridyl-1,2,3-triazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring attached to a 1,2,3-triazole ring.

name: Pyridyl-1,2,4-triazoles
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring attached to a 1,2,4-triazole ring.

name: Wax monoesters
description: Waxes bearing an ester group at exactly one position.

name: Fatty acyl thioesters
description: Thioester derivatives of a fatty acid with the general formula RC(=O)SR', where R is the fatty acyl chain.

name: 6,6a-secoaporphines
description: Alkaloids with a structure that contains an aminoethylphenanthrene moiety.

name: Polyethylene glycols
description: Oligomers or polymers of ethylene oxide, with the general formula (C2H4O)n (with n>=3).

name: 2-amino-3-benzoylthiophenes
description: Compounds containing a thiophene ring which is substituted at the 2-position by an amine and at the 3-position by a benzoyl group.

name: 2-amino-3-aroyl-4,5-alkylthiophenes
description: 3-aroylthiophenes which are substituted at the 2-position by an amine group and the 4-, and 5-position by an alkyl group.

name: N-hydroxyl-alpha-amino acids
description: Alpha amino acids that carry a hydroxyl group at the N-terminal.

name: 1,2,3-oxadiazoles
description: Compounds containing an oxadiazole ring with the oxygen and the two nitrogen atoms at positions 1, 2, and 3, respectively.

name: Thienopyridazines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a thiophene ring fused to a pyridazine ring. A thiophene is a five-member aromatic ring with one sulfur and four carbon atoms, while a pyridazine is a six-membered aromatic ring with two adjacent nitrogen atoms and four carbon atoms.

name: Thieno[3,4-d]pyridazines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds consisting of a thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine moiety. Thieno[3,4-d]pyridazine is a bicyclic compound made up of a thiophene ring fused to a pyridazine ring so that the sulfur atom and the two nitrogen atoms are at the 1-, 4-, and 5-position, respectively.
