name: N-alkylpiperazines
description: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries an alkyl group.

name: N-methylpiperazines
description: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries a methyl group.

name: N-arylpiperazines
description: Organic compounds containing a piperazine ring where the nitrogen ring atom carries an aryl group.

name: Pyrazinium compounds
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a pyriazinium ring.

name: 2-aminopyrazinium compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a pyrazinium ring that carries an amine group at the 2-position.

name: Steroid acids
description: Compounds containing a carboxyl group attached to a steroid backbone.

name: 3-carboxy steroids
description: Steroid compounds that carry a carboxyl group at the C3-atom of the steroid backbone.

name: Azobenzenes
description: Organonitrogen aromatic compounds that contain a central azo group, where each nitrogen atom is conjugated to a benzene ring.

name: Isodiazenes
description: Organonitrogen compounds with the formula RN(R')N or R[N+](R')N-, where R and R' are organic groups.

name: 1,2-dithiolanes
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiolane ring. 1,2-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered  saturated aliphatic ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 2- ring positions.

name: 1,3-dithiolanes
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,3-dithiolane ring. 1,3-dithiolane moiety is a 5-membered saturated aliphatic ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: alpha-Mercaptocarboxylic acids
description: Carboxylic acids that bear a thiol group at the C-2 position. Alpha-mercaptocarboxylic acids have the general formula RC(S)C(=O)O, where R = H, organyl group.

name: Thiophosphate monoesters
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly one R-group is an organyl group.

name: Thiophosphate diesters
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly two R-groups are organyl groups.

name: Thiophosphate triesters
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where exactly three R-groups are organyl groups.

name: Organic dithiophosphoric acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds that contain dithiophosphoric acid or a derivative thereof, with the general formula ROP(S)(=S)OR', (R,R'=H, or organyl group).

name: Dithiophosphate S-esters
description: S-ester derivatives of dithiophosphates, with the general structure RSP(O)(O)=S (R = organyl group).

name: Glycerophosphoglycerophosphoglycerols
description: Glycerophospholipids that contain three glycerol moieties sequentially linked to each other with a phosphate group. They include cardiolipins.

name: Phosphosphingolipids
description: Sphingolipids with a structure based on a sphingoid base that is attached to a phosphate head group. They differ from phosphonospingolipids which have a phosphonate head group.

name: (3'->5')-dinucleotides
description: Dinucleotides where the two bases are connected via a (3'->5')-phosphodiester linkage.

name: Amphilectane, neoamphilectane, cycloamphilectane, and adociane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the amphilectane or a seco-,neo-, or cyclo- derivative thereof. Amphilectane is a tricyclic structure made up of three cyclohexane fused together, with a methyl group at the C11-, C7-, and C3- positions. Additionally, it carries a 2-methylpropyl group at the C1-position. Amphilectanes are presumably derived from serrulatanes. Cycloamphilectanes represent a further cyclisation.

name: Villanovane, atisane, trachylobane or helvifulvane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on the villanovane, atisane, trachylobane or helvifulvane skeleton. The astisane and atisane skeletons arise from the rearrangement of the beyerane cation intermediate. The trachylobane and helvifulvane skeletons are formed by rearrangement of the beyerane cation intermediate followed by cyclisation.

name: Monomethylphosphatidylethanolamines
description: Lipids with a structure containing a glycerol moiety linked at its  terminal C3 atom to a N-methylphosphoethanolamine group, and at its C1 and C2 terminal atoms by an acyl group.

name: Dimethylphosphatidylethanolamines
description: Lipids with a structure containing a glycerol moiety linked at its  terminal C3 atom to a N,N-dimethylphosphoethanolamine group, and at its C1 and C2 terminal atoms by an acyl group.

name: 2-arylbenzofuran flavonoids
description: Phenylpropanoids containing the 2-phenylbenzofuran moiety.

name: 3-arylcoumarin flavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids that bear a ketone group at the C2-position.

name: Isobenzofurans
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing an isobenzofuran moiety.

name: Isobenzofuranones
description: Compounds containing a 2-benzofuran moiety that carries an oxo group at the 1 position.

name: 1-benzopyrans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a pyran, so that the oxygen atom is at the 1-position.

name: 2-benzopyrans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a pyran, so that the oxygen atom is at the 2-position.

name: Benzothiopyrans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a pyran ring. Pyran a six-membered heterocyclic, non-aromatic ring, made up of five carbon atoms and one oxygen atom and containing two double bonds.

name: 1-benzothiopyrans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzothiopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a thiopyran, so that the sulfur atom is at the 1-position.

name: 2-benzothiopyrans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that 1-benzothiopyran, a bicyclic compound made up of a benzene ring fused to a thiopyran, so that the sulfur atom is at the 2-position.

name: Angucyclines
description: Polyketides with a structure based on then benz[a]anthracene skeleton, with the particularity that the central ring of the anthracene moiety is a para-quinone.

name: Methyl esters
description: Organic compounds containing a carboxyl group that is esterified with a methyl group. They have the general structure RC(=O)OR', where R=H or organyl group and R'=methyl group.

name: Fatty acid methyl esters
description: Compounds containing a fatty acid that is esterified with a methyl group. They have the general structure RC(=O)OR', where R=fatty aliphatic tail or organyl group and R'=methyl group.

name: Cyclobutane lignans
description: Lignans with a structure characterized by to phenylpropanoid units coupled together through the C7-C7' and C8-C8' bonds, forming a cyclobutane ring with the C7, C7', C8', and C8 atoms.

name: Alpha-acyloxy ketones
description: Ketones that have an acyloxy substituent alpha to the carbonyl group. They have the general structure R4C(=O)OC(R2)(R3)C(R1)=O (R1=organyl, R4=H or organyl; R2,R3 = any atom).

name: 7,9'-epoxylignans
description: Lignans that contain the 7,9'-epoxylignan skeleton, which consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries a phenyl group, a methyl group, and a benzyl group at the 2-, 3-, 4-position, respectively.

name: 7,7'-epoxylignans
description: Lignans with a structure based on a 2,5-diaryl-3, 4-dimethyltetrahydrofuran skeleton.

name: 9,9'-epoxylignans
description: Lignans with a structure based on the 9,9'-epoxylignan skeleton, which consists of a tetrahydrofuran that carries two benzyl groups at the 3- and 4-positions. Additionally they are oxygenated at the 2-position to form dibenzylbutyrolactones (oxo group) or a dibenzylbutyrolactols (hydroxyl group).

name: Aryltetralin lignans
description: Lignans with a structure based on the 1-phenyltetralin skeleton.

name: Stemona alkaloids
description: Alkaloids are characterized by a pyrrolo[1,2- a]azepine nucleus usually linked with two carbon chains mostly forming terminal lactone rings. They can be clasified in different subgroups, based on the different carbon chains attached to C-9 of the pyrroloazepine nucleus.

name: Dithiocarboxylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing a dithiocarboxylic acid with the general formula RC(=S)SR' (R = organyl group, R' = H or organyl group).

name: Dithiocarboxylic acid esters
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RC(=S)SR', where R and R' are organyl groups.

name: S-alkyl-CoAs
description: Alkyl sulfides consisting of coenzyme A that carries an S-alkyl substituent.

name: S-alkyl-L-cysteines
description: Cysteine derivatives that carry an alkyl chain attached to the sulfanyl group.

name: S-alkyl thiosulfates
description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a alkyl chain that is attached to the sulfur atom of thiosulfuric acid (or its conjugated base).

name: Glycerone and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing the glycerone moiety or a derivative (ether or ester) thereof.

name: Glycerone phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a glycerone moiety that carries a phosphate group at the O-1 or O-2 position.

name: N-alkylpyrrolidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrrolidine moiety that is substituted at the N1-position with an alkyl group. Pyrrolidine is a five-membered saturated aliphatic heterocycle with one nitrogen atom and four carbon atoms.

name: Acyl-L-homoserine lactones
description: L-isomers of N-acyl-homoserine-lactones.

name: Acyl L-homoserines
description: L-isomers of Acyl homoserines.

name: 6-thiopurines
description: Compounds containing a purine that carries a thiol group at the 6-position. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: 6-alkylaminopurines
description: Compounds that contain an alkylamine group attached at the 6-position of a purine. Purine is a bicyclic aromatic compound made up of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: Sulfuric acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfate group that carries one or two O-ester groups.

name: Alkyl sulfates
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfate group that carries an alkyl group through an ether group.

name: Alkyl phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphate group that is linked to one or more alkyl chains.

name: Monoalkyl phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphate group that is linked to exactly one alkyl chain.

name: Dialkyl phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphate group that is linked to exactly two alkyl chain.

name: Trialkyl phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphate group that is linked to exactly three alkyl chains.

name: Alkanesulfinic acids and derivatives
description: Organosulfur compounds containing an aliphatic group attached to a sulfinic acid group (or a derivative thereof), with the general formula RSO2R' (R= alkyl, R'=any atom).

name: Alkanesulfinic acids
description: Organosulfur compounds containing an aliphatic group attached to a sulfinic acid group (or a derivative thereof), with the general formula RSO2R' (R= alkyl, R'=H).

name: Linear 1,3-diarylpropanoids
description: Organic compounds with a structure based on a C6-C3-C6 skeleton, where the two benzene rings are not linked together.

name: (5'->5')-dinucleotides
description: Dinucleotides where the two bases are connected via a (5'->5')-phosphodiester linkage.

name: N-benzylbenzamides
description: Compounds containing a benzamide moiety that is N-linked to a benzyl group.

name: 2'-Hydroxychalcones
description: Organic compounds containing chalcone skeleton that carries a hydroxyl group at the 2'-position.

name: 2'-Hydroxy-dihydrochalcones
description: Organic compounds containing dihydrochalcone skeleton that carries a hydroxyl group at the 2'-position.

name: Retrochalcones
description: A form of normal chalcones that are structurally distinguished by the lack of oxygen functionalities at the C2'- and C6'-positions.

name: Retro-dihydrochalcones
description: A form of normal dihydrochalcones that are structurally distinguished by the lack of oxygen functionalities at the C2'- and C6'-positions.

name: 2,3-Cyclopentanoindolines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing an indoline ring system that shares its C2-C3 bond with a cyclopentane ring.

name: Azaphilones
description: A structurally variable family of fungal polyketide metabolites possessing a highly oxygenated pyranoquinone bicyclic core, usually known as isochromene, and a quaternary carbon center.

name: O-cinnamoyl glycosides
description: O-glycoside derivatives of cinnamic acid. Cinnamic acid is an aromatic compound containing a benzene and a carboxylic acid group forming 3-phenylprop-2-enoic acid.

name: Cinnamic acid esters
description: Compound containing an ester derivative of cinnamic acid.

name: 2,5-disubstituted thiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing a thiophene that is disubstituted at the C-2,  and C5-positions.

name: 2,3,5-trisubstituted thiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing a thiophene that is trisubstituted at the C-2, C3- and C5-positions.

name: Benzoxanthenes
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a xanthene ring system. Xanthene is a tricyclic compound made up of two benzene rings linearly fused to each other through a pyran ring.

name: Pyranocoumarins
description: Organic compounds containing a pyran (or a hydrogenated derivative) fused to a coumarin moiety.

name: Angular pyranocoumarins
description: Organic compounds containing a pyran (or a hydrogenated derivative) angularly fused to a coumarin moiety.

name: Linear pyranocoumarins
description: Organic compounds containing a pyran (or a hydrogenated derivative) linearly fused to a coumarin moiety.

name: Cyclic ketones
description: Organic compounds containing a ketone that is conjugated to a cyclic moiety.

name: 2,4-diphenylfurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a furan ring substituted with a phenyl group only the C2- and C4-positions.

name: 2,5-diphenylfurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a furan ring substituted with a phenyl group only the C2- and C5-positions.

name: 3,4-diphenylfurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a furan ring substituted with a phenyl group only the C3- and C4-positions.

name: Diphenylfurans
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a furan ring substituted with a phenyl group at exactly two positions.

name: 4-carboxy steroids
description: Steroid compounds that carry a carboxyl group at the C4-atom of the steroid backbone.

name: Rhamnofolane and daphnane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on one the rhamnofolane or daphnane skeleton. The rhamnofolane and daphnane skeletons are closely related, being formally derived from casbane by two cyclizations (6,10 and 5,14) followed by cleavage of the 1,15 (daphnane) or 2,15 (rhamnofolane) cyclopropane bonds.

name: Cinnamylphenols
description: Organic compounds containing the 1,3-diphenylpropene moiety with one benzene ring bearing one or more hydroxyl groups.

name: 3-prenylated flavones
description: Flavones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 3-position.

name: 3'-prenylated flavones
description: Flavones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 3'-position.

name: 6-prenylated flavones
description: Flavones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 6-position.

name: 8-prenylated flavones
description: Flavones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 8-position.

name: 3'-prenylated flavanones
description: Flavanones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 3'-position.

name: 6-prenylated flavanones
description: Flavanones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 6-position.

name: 8-prenylated flavanones
description: Flavanones that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 8-position.

name: 3-prenylated chalcones
description: Chalcones featuring a C5-isoprenoid unit at the 3-position.

name: 4-prenylated 2-arybenzofurans
description: 2-arylbenzofuran flavonoids featuring a C5-isoprenoid unit at the 4-position.

name: 4'-prenylated 2-arybenzofurans
description: 2-arylbenzofuran flavonoids featuring a C5-isoprenoid unit at the 4'-position.

name: 2-prenylated xanthones
description: Organic compounds containing a C5-isoprenoid group linked to a xanthone moiety at the 2-position. Xanthone is a tricyclic compound made up of two benzene rings linearly fused to each other through a pyran ring that carries a ketone group.

name: 4-prenylated xanthones
description: Organic compounds containing a C5-isoprenoid group linked to a xanthone moiety at the 4-position. Xanthone is a tricyclic compound made up of two benzene rings linearly fused to each other through a pyran ring that carries a ketone group.

name: 8-prenylated xanthones
description: Organic compounds containing a C5-isoprenoid group linked to a xanthone moiety at the 8-position. Xanthone is a tricyclic compound made up of two benzene rings linearly fused to each other through a pyran ring that carries a ketone group.

name: Pyranoflavonoids
description: Compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a 2-phenyl-1,4-benzopyran skeleton.

name: Pyranoxanthones
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a pyran or a hydrogenated derivative fused to a xanthone ring system.

name: 2,2-dimethyl-1-benzopyrans
description: Organic compounds containing a 1-benzopyran moiety that carries two methyl groups at the 2-position.

name: 6-prenylated isoflavanones
description: Isoflavanones featuring a C5-isoprenoid unit at the 6-position.

name: 8-prenylated isoflavanones
description: Isoflavanones featuring a C5-isoprenoid unit at the 8-position.

name: Rotenones
description: Rotenoids with a structure based on a 6a,12a-dihydrochromeno[3,4-b]chromen-12(6H)-one skeleton.

name: Pyranoisoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids that contain a pyran ring fused to either of the A, B, or C ring of the isoflavonoid skeleton.

name: Flavonoid-3-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to carbohydrate moiety at the C3-position.

name: Flavonoid-3-O-glucuronides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to glucuronic acid at the C3-position.

name: Flavonoid-7-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to carbohydrate moiety at the C7-position.

name: Flavonoid-7-O-glucuronides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to glucuronic acid at the C7-position.

name: Flavonoid 8-C-glycosides
description: Compounds containing a carbohydrate moiety which is C-glycosidically linked to 8-position of a 2-phenylchromen-4-one flavonoid backbone.

name: Dinaphthofurans
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain two naphthalene moieties fused to each other through a furan ring. Furan is a 5 membered- ring aromatic ring with four carbon and one oxygen atoms. Naphthalene is a polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon  made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Gallic acids
description: Organic compounds that contain a 3,4,5-trihydroxybenzoic acid moiety.

name: Galloyl esters
description: Organic compounds that contain an ester derivative of 3,4,5-trihydroxybenzoic acid.

name: Flavonoid-8-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing a flavonoid moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to carbohydrate moiety at the C8-position.

name: Furanochalcones
description: Compounds containing a furan ring fused to either ring of a chalcone moiety.

name: Pyranochromenes
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyran ring fused to a chromene (1-benzopyran) moiety.

name: Methyl-branched fatty acids
description: Fatty acids with an acyl chain that has a methyl branch. Usually, they are saturated and contain only one or more methyl group. However, branches other than methyl may be present.

name: Fusicoccane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids with a structure based on a 20-carbon dicyclopenta[a,d]cyclooctane  skeleton  (5->8->5 ring system) known as fusicoccane.

name: Anthocyanin-3'-O-glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing one anthocyanidin moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety at the C3'-position.

name: Anthocyanidin-7-O-Glycosides
description: Phenolic compounds containing one anthocyanidin moiety which is O-glycosidically linked to a carbohydrate moiety at the C7-position.

name: 19-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 19-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 17-oxosteroids
description: Steroid derivatives carrying a C=O group at the 17-position of the steroid skeleton.

name: 5,10-cycloaromadendrane sesquiterpenoids
description: Aromadendrane sesquiterpenoids that arise from the C5-C10 cyclization of the aromadendrane skeleton.

name: Cholestane steroids
description: Steroids with a structure containing the 27-carbon cholestane skeleton.

name: Ergostane steroids
description: Steroids with a structure based on the ergostane skeleton, which arises from the methylation of cholestane at the 24-position.

name: Androstane steroids
description: Steroids with a structure based on the 19-carbon androstane skeleton.

name: Pregnane steroids
description: Steroids with a structure based on the 21-carbon pregnane skeleton.

name: Estrogens and derivatives
description: Steroids with a structure containing a 3-hydroxylated estrane.

name: 4,5-disubstituted 2-deoxystreptamines
description: 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides that a glycosidically linked to a pyranose of furanose unit at the C4- and C5-positions.

name: 4,6-disubstituted 2-deoxystreptamines
description: 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides that a glycosidically linked to a pyranose of furanose unit at the C4- and C6-positions.

name: 2-deoxystreptamine aminoglycosides
description: Aminoglycosides containing the 2-deoxystreptamine (1,3-diaminocyclohexane-4,5,6-triol) core.

name: Streptamine aminoglycosides
description: Aminoglycosides containing the aminocyclitol the streptamine (1,3-diaminocyclohexane-2,4,5,6-tetrol) core.

name: 6-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 6-position of the steroid backbone.

name: Angular triquinanes
description: Triquinane with a structure based on a [6.3.0.0^1,5] undecane carbon skeleton.

name: Linear triquinanes
description: Triquinane with a structure based on a [6.3.0.0^2,6] undecane carbon skeleton.

name: Imidazopyrazines
description: Organic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a pyrazine ring fused to an imidazole ring. These also include hydrogenated derivatives of the imidazopyrazine moiety. Imidazole is 5-membered ring consisting of three carbon atoms, and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3-positions. Pyrazine is a 6-membered ring consisting of six carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at ring positions 1 and 4.

name: Imidazo-[4,5-c]pyridines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazo-[4,5-c]pyridine ring system. Imidazo-[4,5-c]pyridine consists of an imidazole ring fused to a pyridine, so that the three ring nitrogen atoms are at the 1-, 2-, and 5-position, respectively.

name: Naphthalene sulfonamides
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonamide (or a derivative thereof) at one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 1-naphthalene sulfonamides
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonamide (or a derivative thereof) at the 1-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 2-naphthalene sulfonamides
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonamide (or a derivative thereof) at the 1-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: Naphthalene sulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof) at one or more positions. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 1-naphthalene sulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof) at the 1-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 2-naphthalene sulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof) at the 2-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 1-naphthalene sulfonates
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group at the 1-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 2-naphthalene sulfonates
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a naphthalene moiety that carries a sulfonic acid group at the 2-position. Naphthalene is a bicyclic compound that is made up of two fused benzene ring.

name: 2-bromoanilines
description: Organic compounds that contain an aniline carrying a bromine atom at the C2-position.

name: Organic anions
description: Organic compounds that have a negative electric charge.

name: Organic cations
description: Organic compounds with a positive electric charge.

name: Organic zwitterions
description: Organic neutral compounds having formal unit electrical charges of opposite sign.

name: Glycerophosphonolipids
description: Lipids that contain a phosphonate group attached at a terminal carbon of a glycerol backbone.

name: 1,2-dithiole-3-ones
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,2-dithiole ring that bears a C=O group.

name: 1,2-dithioles
description: Compounds containing a 5-membered unsaturated ring with three carbon atoms and two adjacent sulfur atoms.

name: 1,3-dithioles
description: Compounds containing a 5-membered unsaturated ring with three carbon atoms, and two sulfur atoms at the 1- and 3-positions, respectively.

name: Enoate esters
description: An alpha,beta-unsaturated carboxylic ester of general formula R1C(R2)=C(R3)C(=O)OR4 (R4= organyl compound) in which the ester C=O function is conjugated to a C=C double bond at the alpha,beta position.

name: Ynoate esters
description: An alpha,beta-unsaturated carboxylic ester of general formula R1C#CC(=O)OR2 (R2= organyl compound) in which the ester C=O function is conjugated to a C#C double bond at the alpha,beta position.

name: Alpha,beta-unsaturated carboxylic esters
description: Carboxylic esters of general structure R1C(R2)=C(R3)C(=O)OR4 (R4= organyl compound) or R1C#CC(=O)OR2 (R2= organyl compound), in which the ester group is conjugated to an unsaturated C-C bond.

name: Carbenes
description: The electrically neutral species H2C and its derivatives, in which the carbon is covalently bonded to two univalent groups of any kind or a divalent group and bears two non-bonding electrons, which may be spin-paired (singlet state) or spin-non-paired (triplet state). Subclasses of carbenes include acyl carbenes, imidoyl carbenes, and vinyl carbenes.

name: Organic 1,3-dipolar compounds
description: Electrically neutral organic molecules carrying a positive and a negative charge in one of their major canonical descriptions. In most dipolar compounds the charges are delocalized; however the term is also applied to species where this is not the case. The term 1,3-dipolar compounds is used for those in which a significant canonical resonance form can be represented by a separation of charge over three atoms (in connection with 1,3-dipolar cycloadditions).

name: Allyl-type 1,3-dipolar organic compounds
description: Organic 1,3-dipolar compounds with the general structure  X=Y+-Z- <-> X--Y+=Z<-> X+-Y-Z-<-> X-=Y-Z+ (X, Z = C, N, or O; Y = N or O).

name: Carbene-type 1,3-dipolar compounds
description: 1,3-dipolar compounds with the general structure X:-C=Z<-> X+=C-Z- (X = C or N; Z = C, N, or O).

name: Propargyl-type 1,3-dipolar organic compounds
description: Organic 1,3-dipolar compounds with the general structure  X#N+-Z- <-> X-=N+=Z <-> X-=N-Z+ <-> X-N=Z (X = C or O, Z = C, N, or O).

name: Acyl carbenes
description: Any compound with the general structure acyl-C:-R. In organic chemistry, an unspecified acyl carbene is commonly a carboxylic acyl carbene RC(=O)-C:-R.

name: Vinyl carbenes
description: Carbenes having a vinylic group on a carbenic carbon atom R2C=CRC:R <-> R2C+-CR=C-R.

name: Flav-3-enes
description: Flavonoids with a structure based on the 2-phenylchromene skeleton, with a double bond between the C3 and C4 carbon atoms of the chromene moiety.

name: 3-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 3-position.

name: 4-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 4-position.

name: 8-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 8-position.

name: 3'-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 3'-position.

name: 2'-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 2'-position.

name: 6-prenylated flavans
description: Flavans that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at the 6-position.

name: Prenylated neoflavonoids
description: Neoflavonoids that features a C5-isoprenoid substituent at any position of the A, B, or C ring. Neoflavonoids are compounds with a structure based on the 4-phenylchromene backbone.

name: 3'-hydroxy,4'-methoxyisoflavonoids
description: Isoflavonoids carrying a methoxy group attached to the C4' atom, as well as a hydroxyl group at the C3'-position of the isoflavonoid backbone.

name: Pyranoneoflavonoids
description: Compounds containing a pyran ring fused to either ring A, B, or C of the neoflavonoid skeleton. Neoflavonoids are compounds with a structure based on the 4-phenylchromene backbone.

name: 1,1'-azonaphthalenes
description: Organonitrogen aromatic compounds that contain a central azo group, where each nitrogen atom is conjugated to the 1-position of a naphthalene ring system. Naphthalene is a compound made up of two fused benzene rings.

name: Eremophilane, 8,9-secoeremophilane and furoeremophilane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiterpenoids with a structure based either on the eremophilane skeleton, its 8,9-seco derivative, or the furoeremophilane skeleton. Eremophilanes have been shown to be derived from eudesmanes by migration of the methyl group at C-10 to C-5.

name: Organic phosphoric acid diamides
description: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RNP(R2)(O)=O (R=alkyl, aryl; R2 = amine group).

name: 1,2-dihalobenzenes
description: Organic compounds that contain a benzene ring that is substituted by halogen atoms at exactly two carbon atoms, which are adjacent.

name: 1,4-dihalobenzenes
description: Organic compounds that contain a benzene ring that is substituted by halogen atoms at exactly two carbon atoms, C1 and C4, respectively.

name: Aryl ketones
description: Organic aromatic compounds that contain a ketone group substituted at one C-atom with an aryl group. They have the generic structure RC(=O)R', where R = aryl group and R'=organyl group.

name: Aryl alkyl ketones
description: Ketones have the generic structure RC(=O)R', where R = aryl group and R'=alkyl group.

name: Alpha,beta-unsaturated ketones
description: Ketones with the general structure R#CC(=O)R' or R=CC(=O)R', where R=organyl and R'= organyl group.

name: b'-hydroxy-alpha,beta-unsaturated ketones
description: Alpha,beta-unsaturated ketones that carry a hydroxyl group at the beta'-position.

name: Alpha-branched alpha,beta-unsaturated ketones
description: Alpha,beta-unsaturated ketones that carry a branch on the alpha carbon. They have the generic structure RC(=O)C(R')=C, R = organyl group and R'= any heteroatom.

name: Alpha-hydroxyaldehydes
description: Organic compounds containing an aldehyde substituted with a hydroxyl group on the adjacent carbon.

name: Enol ester epoxides
description: Epoxide containing derivatives of enol esters. They have an acyloxy substituent on either carbon atom of the epoxide ring and their general structure is CC1OC1OC(R)=O, R = H or organyl chain.

name: Alpha-acyloxy carbonyl compounds
description: Carbonyl compounds that have an acyloxy substituent alpha to the carbonyl group. They have the general structure R4C(=O)OC(R2)(R3)C(R1)=O (R1,R4=H or organyl; R2,R3 = any atom).

name: Flavonoid 3-O-p-coumaroyl glycosides
description: Flavonoid 3-O-glycosides where the carbohydrate moiety is esterified with a p-coumaric acid. P-coumaric acid is an organic derivative of cinnamic acid, that carries a hydroxyl group at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: Thioflavones
description: Organic compounds that contains the 2-phenyl-4H-1-benzothiopyran-4-one skeleton, which consists of a 1-benzothiopyran-4-one substituted at the 2-position by a phenyl group. These compounds are thio analogues of flavones.

name: Thioflavans
description: Compounds containing a thiochromane skeleton substituted at the 2-position with a phenyl group.

name: 2,5-dioxopiperazines
description: Organic heterocyclic compounds that contain a piperazine with the oxo groups at the 2- and 5-positions. Piperazine is a six-membered heterocyclic compound consisting of two nitrogen atoms and four carbon atoms.

name: Alpha-acyloxy aldehydes
description: Aldehydes that have an acyloxy substituent alpha to the carbonyl group. They have the general structure R4C(=O)OC(R2)(R3)C(R1)=O (R1=H, R4=H or organyl; R2,R3 = any atom).

name: Furanoid lignans
description: Lignans with a structure that contains either a tetrahydrofuran ring, a furan ring, or a furofuan ring system, that arises from the joining of the two phenylpropanoid units.

name: Diazo compounds
description: Organic compounds having the divalent diazo group, =N+=N-, attached to a carbon atom.

name: Pyrano[3,4-c]pyridazines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyrano[3,4-c]pyridazine moiety. Pyrano[3,4-c]pyridazine is a 10-membered bicyclic compound made up of a pyran ring fused to a pyridazine ring so that the two nitrogen atoms and the oxygen atom are located at the 1-, 2-, and 8-position, respectively.

name: Tyrosols
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a phenethyl alcohol moiety that carries a hydroxyl group at the 4-position of the benzene group.

name: 1-pyranosylindoles
description: Nucleoside and nucleotide analogs with a structure that consists of an indole base which is N-substituted at the 1-position with a pyranose moiety. Nucleotide analogues contain a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon atom of the pyranose.

name: 1,3-substituted cyclopentyl purine nucleosides
description: Nucleoside analogues with a structure that consists of a cyclobutane that is substituted a the 1-position with a hydroxyl group and at the 3-position with either a purine base.

name: Nucleoside and nucleotide analogues
description: Analogues of nucleosides and nucleotides. These include phosphonated nucleosides, C-glycosylated nucleoside bases, analogues where the sugar unit is a pyranose, and carbocyclic nucleosides, among others.

name: Cyclopentyl nucleosides
description: Nucleoside analogues with a structure that consists of a cyclobutane that is substituted a the 1-position with a hydroxyl group and at the 2- or the 3- position with either a purine or pyrimidine base.

name: 1,3-substituted cyclopentyl nucleosides
description: Nucleoside analogues with a structure that consists of a cyclobutane that is substituted a the 1-position with a hydroxyl group and at the 3-position with either a purine or pyrimidine base.

name: Pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidine glycosides
description: Nucleosides or derivatives thereof that consist of a pyazolo[3,2-d]pyrimidine ring system that is N-glycosidically linked to a ribose or deoxyribose. They bear the sugar moiety on the pyrimidine part of the molecule.

name: Cedrane and isocedrane sesquiterpenoids
description: Sesquiternoids with a structure based on the cedrane or the isocedrane skeleton. Cedrane is a tricyclic molecules a 3,6,8,8-tetramethyl-1H-3a,7-methano-azulene moiety. Isocedrane is a rearranged cedrane arising from the migration of methyl group moved from the 6-position to the 4-position.

name: Aspidofractine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure that is based on the hexacyclic aspidofractine core. These compounds are related to the Aspidosperma group by formation of a C-2 to C-18 bond.

name: Gelsemium alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure that is based on the tetracyclic gelsemium skeleton. These alkaloids contain an oxindole function and a cage-like, hydroaromatic residue which is believed to arise from an intermediate related to anhydrovobasinediol by formation of a 6,20 bond and rearrangement to an oxindole. The major alkaloids in this group are related to Gelsemine; however, a smaller group, characterized by Gelsedine, lack the 6,20 bond, and have also lost C-21.

name: Macroline alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure that is based on the tetracyclic macroline skeleton. The macroline skeleton arises by scission of the C-21 to N-4 bond  of the akuammilan skeleton, and mostly occurs in bisindole alkaloids.

name: Pyrrolo[3,4-d]pyridazines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyrrolo fused to a pyridazine ring. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyridazine is a six-membered aromatic ring with two adjacent nitrogen atoms, and for carbon atoms.

name: Allocolchicine alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the tricyclic allocolchicine skeleton, which consists of a dibenzocycloheptane where the cycloheptane moiety carries the N-acetamide group.

name: Cephalotaxus alkaloids
description: Alkaloids with a structure based on the cephalotaxine skeleton, a tetracyclic 1,3-benzodioxole-containing compound which arises from the skeletal rearrangement of the hydroaromatic component of the Erythrina group.

name: Hetisine-type diterpenoid alkaloids
description: Alkaloid diterpenoids with a structure based on the hetisine skeleton, which is a heptacyclic compound with an additional N-C-6 bond as compared with the hetidine-type, and thus, is one of most complex entries in the atisane-class.

name: Kaurane diterpenoids
description: Diterpene alkaloids with a structure that is based on the kaurane skeleton. Kaurane is a tetracyclic compound that arises by cyclisation of a pimarane precursor followed by rearrangement. It possesses a [3,2,1]-bicyclic ring system with C15-C16 bridge connected to C13, forming the five-membered ring D.

name: Quinolidines
description: Organic compounds containing a quinolidine or decahydroquinoline moiety, which is a bicyclic skeleton consisting of a piperidine fused to a cyclohexane ring.

name: Aconitane-type diterpenoid alkaloids
description: Alkaloid diterpenoids with a structure based on the hexacyclic aconitane skeleton. These compounds have no oxygen functionality at the C7 atom.

name: (3'->5')-dinucleotides and analogues
description: Cyclic compounds consisting of two ribose moieties connected by one 5',3'-phosphodiester bond to form a cycle. Each ribose unit is N-linked to a nucleic base or an analogue thereof. Synthetic derivatives are generally more elaborated molecules in which one or the two nucleobase moieties, and/or sugar residues, and/or phosphodiester linkers have been modified.

name: Indolonaphthyridine alkaloids
description: A numerous and relatively straightforward subgroup of the b-carbolines, e.g. Canthin-6-one, in which an additional C3 unit is attached between C-1 and the indole nitrogen to form an additional ring. The group includes a few dimeric examples, such as Haplophytine.

name: Glycero-3-pyrophosphates
description: Lipids structurally characterized by the presence of a glycerol moiety bonded to one or two chains, and to a pyrophosphate group at the O3-position.

name: Monoradylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety.

name: Diradylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids that carry exactly two acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety.

name: Dialkylglycerols
description: Glycerides consisting of two fatty acid chains covalently bonded to a glycerol molecule through ether linkages.

name: 1-alkyl,3-acylglycerols
description: Glycerides consisting of two fatty acyl chains covalently bonded to a glycerol molecule at the 1- and 3-positions through an ether and an ester linkage, respectively.

name: Alkyldiacylglycerols
description: Triradylglycerols that carry exactly two acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage,  and one attached through an ester linkage.

name: Triradylcglycerols
description: Glycerolipids that carry exactly three acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety.

name: Dialkylmonoacylglycerols
description: Triradylglycerols that carry exactly two acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety through an ether linkage,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ester linkage.

name: Glycosyldiradylglycerols
description: Glycosylglycerols that carry exactly two acyl chains attached to the glycerol moiety.

name: 1-acyl,2-(1Z-alkenyl)-glycerophosphocholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O1-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O2-position.

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acyl-glycerophosphocholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position.

name: 1-alkyl,2-acylglycero-3-phosphocholines
description: Glycerophosphocholines that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one alkyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position.

name: 1-alkyl,2-acylglycerophosphoethanolamines
description: Glycerophosphoethanolamines that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one alkyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position.

name: 1-(1Z-alkenyl),2-acylglycerophosphoethanolamines
description: Glycerophosphoethanolamines that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage at the O2-position,  and one 1Z-alkenyl chain attached through an ether linkage at the O1-position.

name: Monoacylglycerophosphomonoradylglycerols
description: Glycerophosphomonoradylglycerols that carry exactly one acyl chain attached to the glycerol moiety through an ester linkage.

name: Dolichols
description: A group of long-chain mostly unsaturated organic compounds that are made up of varying numbers of isoprene units terminating in an alpha-saturated isoprenoid group, containing an alcohol functional group. The three isoprene units at the distal end  are trans-linked.

name: Dolichyl monophosphates
description: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a monophosphate group substituted by a dolichyl moiety.

name: Dolichyl diphosphates
description: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a diphosphate group substituted by a dolichyl moiety.

name: Bactoprenol monophosphates
description: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a monophosphate group substituted by a bactoprenyl moiety.

name: Bactoprenol diphosphates
description: Polyprenyl compounds consisting of a diphosphate group substituted by a bactoprenyl moiety.

name: Fatty acyl glycosides of mono- and disaccharides
description: Compounds composed of a mono- or disaccharide moiety linked to one hydroxyl group of a fatty alcohol or of a phosphorylated alcohol (phosphoprenols), a hydroxy fatty acid or to one carboxyl group of a fatty acid (ester linkage) or to an amino alcohol.

name: Dialkylthioethers
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by two alkyl groups.

name: Alkylarylthioethers
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by an alkyl and an aryl group.

name: Diarylthioethers
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by two aryl groups.

name: Organic salts
description: Organic compounds consisting of an assembly of cations and anions.

name: Phosphoric monoester monoamides
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid monoester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(OH)N(R3)R4, where R1 = organyl group and R3-R4 = H or organyl.

name: Phosphoric diester monoamides
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid diester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(OR2)N(R3)R4, where R1-R2 = organyl group and R3-R4 = H or organyl.

name: Phosphoric monoester diamides
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a monoamide derivative of a phosphoric acid diester functional group. They have the general structure R1OP(=O)(N(R2)R3)N(R4)R5, where R1 = organyl group and R2-R5 = H or organyl.

name: Carbothioic S-esters
description: Ester derivatives of carbothioic S-acids, with the general structure RSC(=O)R' where R = organyl group and R' = H or organyl group.

name: Carbothioic S-lactones
description: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=O)SR', R-R' = organyl group, where the central atom is part of the ring.

name: Carbothioic O-esters
description: Ester derivatives of carbothioic O-acids, with the general structure ROC(=S)R' where R = organyl group and R' = H or organyl group.

name: Carbothioic O-lactones
description: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=S)OR', R-R' = organyl group, where the central atom is part of the ring.

name: Carbothioic halides
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general structure RC(=S)X, where R = organyl group and X = halogen atom.

name: Carbodithioic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of a carbodithioic acid (RC(=S)SH).

name: Carbodithiolactones
description: Cyclic organosulfur compounds with the general formula RC(=S)SR', where the central carbon atom is part of a ring; R,R' = organyl group.

name: Oxime esters
description: Organic compounds containing an ester derivative of the oxime functional group.

name: Cyclic carboximidic acids
description: Organic acids with the general formula RC(=N)-OH (R=H, organic group), where the carboximidic acid group is part of a cycle.

name: Imidolactones
description: Cyclic organooxygen compounds with the general structure R(=N)OR' where the central carbon atom is part of a ring, and R,R' = organyl group.

name: Imidothiolactones
description: Analogs of imidolactones where the oxygen atom is replaced by a sulfur atom. They have the general structure RC(=N)SR' where the central carbon atom is part of a ring. R,R' =  organyl group.

name: Imidolactams
description: Cyclic organooxygen compounds containing the structure RC(=N)N where the central carbon atom and one of the linked nitrogen atoms are part of the same ring( R here is an organyl group). They can also be viewed as analogs of lactams where the oxygen atom is replaced by a nitrogen atom.

name: Cyclic imidoyl halides
description: Imidoyl halides with the general formula R(X)C=NR' (R, R'=H, alkyl, aryl), where the central carbon atom is part of a ring.

name: Vinylogous halides
description: Organic compounds containing a halogen atom, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety.

name: Vinylogous acids
description: Organic compounds containing a hydroxyl group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety.

name: Vinylogous amides
description: Organic compounds containing an amine group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety.

name: Vinylogous esters
description: Organic compounds containing an ester group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety.

name: Phosphonic acid diesters
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a diester derivative of phosphonic acid, with the general structure ROP(=O)OR' (R,R' = organyl group).

name: Phosphonic amide esters
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a diester derivative of phosphonic acid amide, with the general structure ROP(=O)N(R')R\" (R = organyl group, R'-R\" = H or organyl group).

name: Aralkylamines
description: Alkylamines in which the alkyl group is substituted at one carbon atom by an aromatic hydrocarbyl group.

name: Dialkylarylamines
description: Aliphatic aromatic amines in which the amino group is linked to two aliphatic chains and one aromatic group.

name: Alkyldiarylamines
description: Tertiary alkylarylamines having two aryl and one alkyl groups attached to the amino group.

name: Haloalkenes
description: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a halogen atom.

name: Bromoalkenes
description: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a bromine atom.

name: Chloroalkenes
description: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a chlorine atom.

name: Fluoroalkenes
description: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with a fluorine atom.

name: Iodoalkenes
description: Compounds derived from an alkene by replacing a hydrogen atom with an iodine atom.

name: Fatty Acyls
description: Organic molecules synthesized by chain elongation of an acetyl-CoA primer with malonyl-CoA (or methylmalonyl-CoA) groups that might contain a cyclic functionality and/or are substituted with heteroatoms.

name: 2-aroylquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline which carries an aroyl group at the 2-position. An aroyl group is a univalent radical R-CO- derived from an aromatic carboxylic acid.

name: 4-aroylquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline which carries an aroyl group at the 4-position. An aroyl group is a univalent radical R-CO- derived from an aromatic carboxylic acid.

name: Saccharolipids
description: Compounds in which fatty acids are linked directly to a sugar backbone, forming structures that are compatible with membrane bilayers. In the saccharolipids, a sugar substitutes for the glycerol backbone that is present in glycerolipids and glycerophospholipids. The most familiar saccharolipids contain an acylated glucosamine. In contrast to others glycolipids, the fatty acid is not glycosidically linked to the sugar moiety.

name: Acetate salts
description: Organic compounds containing acetic acid as its acid component.

name: Acetamides
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RNHC(=O)CH3, where R= organyl group.

name: Phenylalkylamines
description: Organic amines where the amine group is secondary and linked on one end to a phenyl group and on the other end, to an alkyl group.

name: Alkylglucosinolates
description: Organic compounds containing a glucosinolate moiety that carries an alkyl chain.

name: Beta-diketones
description: Organic compounds containing two keto groups separated by a single carbon atom.

name: Dithiocarbamic acids and derivatives
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula SC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group.

name: Dithiocarbamic acid esters
description: Organosulfur compounds with the general formula R3SC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group, R3 = organyl.

name: Phosphine sulfides
description: Compounds having the general formula R3P=S <=> R3P+S-.

name: Organic oxides
description: Organic compounds containing an oxide group.

name: Nitrosamides
description: Organonitrogen compounds with the general formula O=CN(R)-N=O, where R=H or organyl group.

name: Dialkyl peroxides
description: Organic compounds containing a peroxide group substituted by two alkyl groups.

name: 2-aminoanthraquinones
description: Organic compounds containing an anthraquinone ring system, which is substituted at the 2-position by an amino group.

name: 8-hydroxyquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety, which carries a hydroxy group at the 8-position. Quinoline consists of a benzene ring fused to a pyrimidine ring to form benzo[b]azabenzene.

name: Polybrominated biphenyls
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a biphenyl moiety, which is substituted at two or more ring positions by a bromine atom.

name: Benzidines
description: Organic compounds containing the benzidine skeleton, made up of a biphenyl ring system substituted at the 4- and 4'-positions with a unsubstituted amine group.

name: 3,3'-disubstituted benzidines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzidine skeleton, which is substituted only at the 3-  and 3'-positions.

name: Perfluorooctanoic acid and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an octyl chain attached to the C-alpha of a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof), where all hydrogens of the octyl chain are replaced by fluorine atoms.

name: Perfluorooctane sulfonic acid and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an octyl chain attached to the sulfur of a sulfonic acid (or a derivative thereof), where all hydrogens of the octyl chain are replaced by fluorine atoms.

name: Perfluoroalkyl sulfonic acid and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an alkyl chain attached to the sulfur of a sulfonic acid group (or a derivative thereof), where all hydrogens of the alkyl chain are replaced by fluorine atoms.

name: Perfluoroalkyl carboxylic acid and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing an alkyl chain attached to the C-alpha of a carboxylic acid group (or a derivative thereof), where all hydrogens of the alkyl chain are replaced by fluorine atoms.

name: Aminotoluenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene that carries a single methyl group and one amino group.

name: Diaminotoluenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene that carries a single methyl group exactly 2 amino groups.

name: Dinitroanilines
description: Organic compounds containing an aniline moiety, which is substituted at 2 positions by a nitro group.

name: Dinitrotoluenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene that carries a single methyl group and exactly two nitro groups.

name: Halopyridines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at one or more positions by a halogen atom.

name: Polyhalopyridines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at two or more positions by a halogen atom.

name: 3-pyridinecarbonitriles
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at the 3-position by a carbonitrile group.

name: Hydroxybenzaldehydes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring carrying an aldehyde group and a hydroxyl group.

name: Benzyl bromides
description: Organic compounds containing  a benzene skeleton substituted with a bromomethyl group.

name: Benzyl chlorides
description: Organic compounds containing  a benzene skeleton substituted with a chloromethyl group.

name: Benzyl halides
description: Organic compounds containing  a benzene skeleton substituted with a halomethyl group.

name: Arsines
description: AsH3 and compounds derived from it by substituting one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups: R3As, RAsH2, R2AsH, R3As (R is not H) are called primary, secondary and tertiary arsines, respectively.

name: Arsine oxides
description: Hydrocarbyl derivatives of H3As=O.

name: Acylals
description: Diesters of geminal diols.

name: Organosulfonic anhydrides
description: Organic compounds having the structure RS(=O)2OS(=O)2R', where R = organyl group and R' = H or organyl group.

name: Organic triazanes
description: Organic compounds containing the triazane group (NH2NHNH2) or a hydrocarbyl derivative thereof.

name: Aminoxides
description: Hydrocarbyl derivatives of the aminoxide anion, with the general formula R3N+[O-] or R3N=O.

name: Organic metalloid salts
description: Organic salt compounds containing a metalloid atom in its ionic form.

name: Methoxyanilines
description: Organic compound containing an aniline group substituted at one or more positions by a methoxy group.

name: 2-aminobenzamides
description: Organic compounds containing a benzamide moiety with an amine group attached to the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: 2-amino-1,3,4-thiadiazoles
description: Thiadiazoles with an amino group attached to the 2-position of a 1,3,4-thiadiazole ring.

name: 2-amino-5-substituted-1,3,4-thiadiazoles
description: Thiadiazoles with an amino group attached to the 2-position of a 1,3,4-thiadiazole ring, as well as a substituent at the 5-position.

name: 2-amino-1,3-thiazoles
description: Compounds containing a 1,3-thiazole ring substituted by an amine group at the 2-position.

name: 2-aminothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group conjugated to a thiophene ring at the 2-position.

name: 3,4,5-trisubstituted-2-aminothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing a thiophene ring substituted  at the 2-,3-,4-, and 5-position, with an amine group at the 2-position.

name: N-arylated-2-aminothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing an arylated amino group conjugated to a thiophene ring at the 2-position.

name: Benzazocines
description: Organic compounds containing the benzazocine ring system, which consists of a benzene ring bound to an azocine ring.

name: Chloroquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety, which carries one or more chlorine atoms.

name: Phthalate esters
description: Ester derivatives of phthalic acids, which are based on a benzene dicarboxylic acid skeleton.

name: m-Phthalate esters
description: Ester derivatives of m-phthalic acids, which are based on a benzene 1,3-dicarboxylic acid skeleton.

name: p-Phthalate esters
description: Ester derivatives of p-phthalic acids, which are based on a benzene 1,4-dicarboxylic acid skeleton.

name: C19-gibberellin 6-carboxylic acids
description: C19-gibberellins with a carboxyl group at the 6-position.

name: C20-gibberellin 6-carboxylic acids
description: C20-gibberellins with a carboxyl group at the 6-position.

name: Vinylogous thioesters
description: Organic compounds containing a thioester group, which is indirectly attached to a carbonyl via an intervening vinyl (>C=C<) moiety.

name: Organic metal salts
description: Organic salt compounds containing a metal atom in its ionic form.

name: Trivalent organic arsenic compounds
description: Organoarsenic compounds in which a carbon is linked to a trivalent arsenic atom.

name: Pentavalent organic arsenic compounds
description: Organoarsenic compounds in which a carbon is linked to a pentavalent arsenic atom.

name: Trialkylarsanes
description: Organoarsenic compounds containing a trivalent arsenic atom linked to three alkyl groups.

name: Vinylaziridines
description: Compounds containing an aziridine ring substituted by one or more vinyl groups.

name: N-vinylaziridines
description: Compounds containing an aziridine ring where the nitrogen atom is substituted by a vinyl group.

name: Iridoid O-glycosides
description: Iridoid monoterpenes containing a glycosyl (usually a pyranosyl) moiety linked to the iridoid skeleton.

name: 1-benzylquinolines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a quinoline that is substituted at the 1-position by a benzyl group.

name: Dialkyldisulfides
description: Organic compounds containing a disulfide group R-SS-R' where R and R' are both alkyl groups.

name: Alkyl nitrates
description: Organic compounds containing a nitrate that is O-linked to an alkyl group.

name: Alkyl nitrites
description: Organic compounds containing an alkyl group linked to a nitrite group.

name: 1-phenethylisoquinolines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a quinoline ring system substituted at the 1-position by a phenethyl group.

name: Mitomycins, mitosane and mitosene derivatives
description: A group of pyrroloindolediones, which carry a methyl group at the 6-position of their quinone moiety. The mitosane (containing an aziridine) and mitosene server as backbone for mitomycins and their derivatives.

name: 1,4-benzodiazepines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a 1,4-azepine.

name: Imidazo[1,5-a][1,4]benzodiazepines
description: Compounds containing an imidazole ring and a 1,4-benzodiazepine ring system, both sharing one nitrogen atom.

name: 1,3,5-triazines
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring, which is a heterocyclic ring, similar to the six-member benzene ring but with three carbons replaced by nitrogen atoms, at ring positions 1, 3, and 5.

name: 1,2,3-triazines
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring, which is a heterocyclic ring, similar to the six-member benzene ring but with three carbons replaced by nitrogen atoms, at ring positions 1, 2, and 3.

name: 1,2,4-triazines
description: Compounds containing a triazine ring, which is a heterocyclic ring, similar to the six-member benzene ring but with three carbons replaced by nitrogen atoms, at ring positions 1, 2, and 4.

name: Nitrotoluenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene that carries a single methyl group and at least 1 nitro group.

name: Menaquinones
description: Vitamin K2 compounds consisting of a naphtho-1,4-quinone ring system, which is substituted at the 2-position by an isoprenyl side-chain, and usually, at the 3-position by a methyl group.

name: 1-benzoylpiperidines
description: Compounds containing a piperidine ring substituted at the 1-position with a benzoyl group.

name: Dimethoxybenzenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a monocyclic benzene moiety carrying exactly two methoxy groups.

name: Benzoyl peroxides
description: Organic compounds containing two benzoyl groups O-linked to each other via a peroxide group. Their skeleton has the general formula [C6H5C(O)]2O2.

name: Methoxybenzenes
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a monocyclic benzene moiety carrying exactly or one more methoxy groups.

name: N,S-acetals
description: Organosulfur compounds with the generic structure RC(SR')N([H])C=O, where R,R'= H or organyl group.

name: C-nitro compounds
description: Compounds having the nitro group, -NO2 (free valence on nitrogen), which is attached to carbon.

name: Oxoisoaporphines
description: Alkaloids with a structure that contains the isoaporphine skeleton with an oxo group at the 7-position.

name: Lycorine-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids compounds containing the lycorine skeleton, made up of a pyrrolo[d,e]phenanthridine ring system.

name: Norbelladine-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids compounds containing the norbelladine skeleton.  They are derived initially from the condensation of tyramine and protocatechuic aldehyde or its derivatives in plants.

name: Homolycorine-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids compounds containing the homolycorine skeleton, made up of a [3,4-g]benzopyranone ring due to the oxidation of the hydroxyl group at the C6. They are biogenetically formed through a restructuring of lycorine-type alkaloids.

name: Crinine- and Haemanthamine-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids compounds with a structure based on the crinine or haemanthamine backbone. Both backbones have a common 5,10b-ethano bridge moiety in their frameworks, which is a very significant taxonomic feature, and the configurations of the 5,10b-ethano bridge are opposite to each other.

name: Galanthamine-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids with a structure characterized a tetracyclic skeleton with two ortho aromatic protons in ring A.

name: Phenanthridine- and phenanthridone-type amaryllidaceae alkaloids
description: Amaryllidaceae alkaloids compounds based on the phenanthridine or the phenanthridone skeleton. Phenanthridone-type alkaloids have the highest oxygenated C ring in all Amaryllidaceae alkaloids, and they always show an amide group in ring B. On the contrary, alkaloids of the phenanthridine type often show completely aromatic ring system, occasionally with a methylation quaternary nitrogen atom.

name: 6,7-benzomorphans
description: Opioid alkaloids based on the tricyclic 6,7-benzomorphan skeleton. Benzomorphans are derived from morpholine, but lack its C ring.

name: Alpha-imino acid and derivatives
description: Organic acids containing an imino group attached to a carbon, which in turn is immediately linked to a carboxyl group (or a derivative thereof).

name: Alpha-imino acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of alpha-imino acids. They have the general structure RN=CC(=O)OR', where R = H, organyl group and R' = organyl group.

name: Azacyclic compounds
description: Organic compounds containing an heterocycle with at least one nitrogen atom and one carbon atom linked to each other.

name: Oxacyclic compounds
description: Organic compounds containing an heterocycle with at least one oxygen atom linked to a ring carbon.

name: Phosphacyclic compounds
description: Organic compounds containing an heterocycle with at least one phosphorus atom and one carbon atom linked to each other.

name: Methionine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing methionine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of methionine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Heteroaromatic compounds
description: Compounds containing an aromatic ring where a carbon atom is linked to an hetero atom.

name: D-alpha-amino acids
description: Alpha amino acids which have the D-configuration of the alpha-carbon atom.

name: L-alpha-amino acids
description: Alpha amino acids which have the L-configuration of the alpha-carbon atom.

name: Phenylpyridazines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridazine ring substituted by a phenyl group.

name: N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acids
description: N-acylated alpha amino acids which have the L-configuration of the alpha-carbon atom.

name: Polycyclic hydrocarbons
description: Polycyclic organic compounds made up only of carbon and hydrogen atoms.

name: Hydrocarbon derivatives
description: Derivatives of hydrocarbons obtained by substituting one or more carbon atoms by an heteroatom. They contain at least one carbon atom and heteroatom.

name: Hydroxypyridines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at one or more positions by a hydroxyl group.

name: Methylpyridines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at one or more positions by a methyl group.

name: Cladiellane diterpenoids
description: Diterpenoids containing a cladiellane skeleton. Cladiellane is a tricyclic ring system derived from eunicellane.

name: Hydroxyisoflavonoids
description: Organic compounds containing an isoflavonoid skeleton carrying one or more hydroxyl groups.

name: Diphenylethers
description: Aromatic compounds containing two benzene rings linked to each other through an ether group.

name: Halomethanes
description: Organic compounds in which at least one of the four hydrogen atoms of methane (CH4) are replaced by halogen atoms.

name: 1-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 1-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 18-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 18-position of the steroid backbone.

name: Trihalomethanes
description: Organic compounds in which exactly three of the four hydrogen atoms of methane (CH4) are replaced by halogen atoms.

name: Hydroxypyrimidines
description: Organic compounds containing a hydroxyl group attached to a pyrimidine ring. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

name: Hydroxyindoles
description: Organic compounds containing an indole moiety that carries a hydroxyl group.

name: Thioselenides
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfur-selenium bond. This class is restricted to compounds where at least one of the sulfur or selenium atoms is linked to a carbon atom.

name: Dithiophosphate O-esters
description: O-ester derivatives of dithiophosphates, with the general structure RSP(O)(O)=S (R = organyl group).

name: Phenolic glycosides
description: Organic compounds containing a phenolic structure attached to a glycosyl moiety. Some examples of phenolic structures include lignans, and flavonoids. Among the sugar units found in natural glycosides are D-glucose, L-Fructose, and L rhamnose.

name: Perimidines
description: Organic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a quinazoline ring system. They are analogues of phenalenes where two carbon atoms in exactly one ring are replaced by nitrogen atoms to form a pyrimidine.

name: Selenophenes
description: Organic compounds containing selenophene, a five-membered monocyclic aromatic ring composed of four C atoms and one selenium atom.

name: Oxirenes
description: Organic compounds containing oxirene, an unsaturated three-membered ring with two carbon atoms and one oxygen atom.

name: 2-Thiopyrimidines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrimidine ring where the carbon at the 2-position involved in a C=S bond.

name: Thiopyrimidines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrimidine ring that has one or more carbon atoms involved in a C=S bond.

name: S-alkylsulfenates
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a sulfenic acid, where the sulfur atom is linked to an alkyl group. They have the general formula RSOH, where R is an alkyl group.

name: Amino acids
description: Organic compounds that contain at least one carboxyl group and one amino group.

name: Ethylene bisdithiocarbamates
description: Dithiocarbamic acids (or derivatives) resulting from the formal addition of  a molecule of carbon disulfide to each amino group of ethylenediamine. In addition, compounds containing a 1,2-ethanediyl carbamodithioate moiety are also members of this class.

name: 3-sulfated flavonoids
description: Flavonoids that are sulfated at the 3-ring position of the flavonoid skeleton.

name: Long-chain alkyl amine oxides
description: Aminoxides that carry an alkyl chain ranging from C10 to C24.

name: Trialkyl amine oxides
description: Hydrocarbyl derivatives of the aminoxide anion, with the general formula R3N+[O-] or R3N=O, where R is an alkyl group.

name: Phthalocyanines
description: Cyclic tetrapyrroles that contain a phthalocyanine skeleton, which consists of four isoindole-type units, with the connecting carbon atoms in the macrocycle replaced by nitrogen.

name: Coumarans
description: Compounds containing the coumaran skeleton, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a 2,3-dihydrofuran ring.

name: 1-phenylcoumarans
description: Compounds containing a coumaran ring system substituted at the 1-position with phenyl group.

name: Isocoumarans
description: Compounds containing the coumaran skeleton, which consists of a benzene ring fused to a 1,3-dihydrofuran ring.

name: 14-alpha-methylsteroids
description: Steroids substituted at the 14-position with a methyl group in the alpha-configuration.

name: Thienothiophenes
description: Organic compounds containing two thiophene rings fused to each other.

name: Allyl sulfur compounds
description: Compounds containing an allylsulfur group, with the general structure H2C(=CH2)CS.

name: 3-alkylindoles
description: Compounds containing an indole moiety that carries an alkyl chain at the 3-position.

name: N-alkylindoles
description: Compounds containing an indole moiety that carries an alkyl chain at the 1-position.

name: Dithiazinanes
description: Cyclic compounds that contain a dithiazinane ring, which is a saturated heterocycle that consisting of one nitrogen atom, two sulfur atoms, and 2 carbon atoms.

name: 1,3,5-dithiazinanes
description: Cyclic compounds that contain a dithiazinane ring, which is a saturated heterocycle that consisting of one nitrogen atom, two sulfur atoms at the 1-,3-, and 5- position, respectively.

name: Triazolobenzothiazoles
description: Compound containing a triazole ring fused to the benzene or the thiazole moiety of the benzothiazole ring system.

name: 1-sulfamoyl-1,2,3-triazoles
description: Compounds containing a 1,2,3-triazole that carries a sulfamoyl group at the 1-position.

name: Phenyl-beta-methoxyacrylates
description: Aromatic compounds containing a methyl-3-methoxyacrylate moiety that carries a benzyl group at the C-alpha carbon.

name: Phenylbenzamines
description: Aromatic compounds consisting of a benzyl group that is N-linked to a benzamine.

name: Furancarboxamides
description: Compounds containing a furan ring that carries a carboxamide group.

name: Pyrazole-4-carboxamides
description: Compounds containing a pyrazole ring that carries a carboxamide group at the 4-position.

name: Pyrazole-5-carboxamides
description: Compounds containing a pyrazole ring that carries a carboxamide group at the 4-position.

name: Xylenes
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a xylene moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups.

name: m-Xylenes
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a m-xylene moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups at the 1- and 3-positions.

name: o-Xylenes
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a o-xylene moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups at the 1- and 2-positions.

name: p-Xylenes
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a p-xylene moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups at the 1- and 4-positions.

name: Xylenols
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a xylene moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups, and at least one hydroxyl group.

name: p-Xylenols
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a p-xylenol moiety, which is a monocyclic benzene carrying exactly two methyl groups at the 1- and 4-positions, and at least one hydroxyl group.

name: Allylamines
description: Organic compound containing an allyl group and an amine group, with the general structure R2C=C(H)N(R'2), where R-R'=H or organyl.

name: Toluamides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a toluene, which carries a carboxamide group.

name: m-Toluamides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a toluene, which carries a carboxamide group a the 3-position.

name: o-Toluamides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a toluene, which carries a carboxamide group a the 2-position.

name: p-Toluamides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a toluene, which carries a carboxamide group a the 4-position.

name: N,N-dialkyl-m-toluamides
description: Aromatic that contain a m-toluamide, where the carboxamide group is N- substituted with two alkyl chains.

name: N,N-dialkyl-p-toluamides
description: Aromatic that contain a m-toluamide, where the carboxamide group is N- substituted with two alkyl chains.

name: Tetraalkylammonium salts
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a quaternary ammonium substituted with four alkyl chains.

name: Benzenesulfonyl compounds
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzenesulfonyl group, which consists of a monocyclic benzene moiety that carries a sulfonyl group.

name: Benzenesulfonyl chlorides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzenesulfonyl group, where the sulfonyl moiety is singly boned to a chloride atom.

name: Tertiary arsines
description: Organoarsenic compounds with a trisubstituted arsenic atom. They have the general formula R[As](R')R\", R,R',R\"=organyl group.

name: Pentaorganoarsanes
description: Organoarsenic compounds containing an arsenic compound that is pentasubstituted by only organic groups.

name: Sulfur-containing organoarsenic compounds
description: Organoarsenic compounds that containing a sulfur atom.

name: Organoarsenic sulfides
description: Organoarsenic compounds with the general formula R[As]S, where R = organyl group.

name: N-acetyl-2-arylethylamines
description: Compounds containing an acetamide group that is N-linked to an arylethylamine.

name: 2-arylethylamines
description: Primary amines that have the general formula RCCNH2, where R is an organic group.

name: Arylsulfates
description: Organic compounds containing a sulfate group that carries an aryl group through an ether group.

name: Pyridoxamine 5'-phosphates
description: Heterocyclic aromatic compounds containing a pyridoxamine that carries a phosphate group at the 5'-position.

name: N-acyl-L-glutamines
description: N-acylated glutamine which has the L-configuration of the alpha-carbon atom.

name: 3-Acylpyruvic acids
description: Compounds containing a pyruvic acid substituted at the 3-position by an acyl group.

name: N-acylserotonins
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a serotonin, in which the amine group is acylated.

name: N-acyldopamines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a dopamine, in which the amine group is acylated.

name: 1-O-alkylglycerols
description: Glycerolipids containing a glycerol moiety that carries an alkyl group at the 1-position.

name: 1-O-alkyl-sn-glycerols
description: Glycerolipids containing a chiral glycerol moiety that carries an alkyl group at the 1-position.

name: Polyprenyl monophosphates
description: Prenol lipids in which the monophosphate group is linked to one end of the polyprenol moiety.

name: Polyprenyl diphosphates
description: Prenol lipids in which the diphosphate group is linked to one end of the polyprenol moiety.

name: Oxygen-containing organoarsenic compounds
description: Organoarsenic compounds that containing an oxygen atom.

name: 1,2,4-benzothiadiazine-1,1-dioxides
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,2,4-benzothiadiazine ring system with two S=O bonds at the 1-position.

name: 1-benzothiophenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compound containing the Benzo[b]thiophene ring system.

name: 2-benzothiophenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compound containing the 2-benzothiophene ring system, in which the benzene ring is fused to the thiophene ring across positions 3 and 4.

name: Phenylketones
description: Aromatic compounds containing a ketone substituted by one aryl group.

name: Aryl-phenylketones
