description: Aromatic compounds containing a ketone substituted by one aryl group, and a phenyl group.

name: Alkyl-phenylketones
description: Aromatic compounds containing a ketone substituted by one alkyl group, and a phenyl group.

name: 4-Hydrocarbylideneazlactones
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a substituted 1,3-oxazoline ring, and with the general structure RC(R')=C1N=C(R'')OC1=O. They are often referred to as 'unsaturated azlactones'.

name: Glycosyl-N-acylsphingosines
description: Compounds containing a sphingosine linked to a simple glucosyl moiety.

name: Benzenesulfonyl halides
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzenesulfonyl group, where the sulfonyl moiety is singly boned to an halogen atom.

name: Benzenesulfonate esters
description: Arenesulfonate esters that result from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of an alcohol, enol, phenol or heteroarenol with benzenesulfonic acid.

name: Valine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing valine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of valine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Histidine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing cysteine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of cysteine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Asparagine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing asparagine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of asparagine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Cysteine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing cysteine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of cysteine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Alanine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing alanine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of alanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Glutamine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing glutamine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of glutamine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Serine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing serine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of serine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Aspartic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing an aspartic acid or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of aspartic acid at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Tyrosine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing tyrosine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of tyrosine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Arginine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing arginine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of arginine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Phenylalanine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing phenylalanine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of phenylalanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Proline and derivatives
description: Compounds containing proline or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of proline at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Glutamic acid and derivatives
description: Compounds containing glutamic acid or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of glutamic acid at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Cyclohexenones
description: Compounds containing a cylohexenone moiety, which is a six-membered aliphatic ring that carries a ketone and has one endocyclic double bond.

name: Leucine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing leucine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of leucine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Isoleucine and derivatives
description: Compounds containing isoleucine or a derivative thereof resulting from reaction of isoleucine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of glycine by a heteroatom.

name: Imidazoquinolines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a quinoline ring system. In some configurations, the imidazole ring shares a nitrogen atom with the quinoline moiety.

name: Nitrothiophenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compound containing a nitro group attached to a thiophene ring.

name: 2-nitrothiophenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compound containing a nitro group attached to a thiophene ring a the 2-position.

name: 3-nitrothiophenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compound containing a nitro group attached to a thiophene ring a the 3-position.

name: Phenyl-1,3-oxazoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,3-oxazole substituted at one or more positions by a phenyl group.

name: Aminocyclitols
description: Cyclitols with at least one hydroxyl group replace by an amino group.

name: Deoxyribo- and ribonucleoside phosphonates
description: N-glycosyl compound that possess both a nucleobase, usually a purine or a pyrimidine, linked to either a ribose or deoxyribose, which in turn carries a phosphonate group at the 5'-position.

name: Oligonucleotides
description: Organic polymers made up of a sequence of 3 to 12 purine or pyrimidine nucleotide residues linked to one another from the 5' -end to the 3'-end through a phosphate group.

name: Imidazole[4,5-c]pyridine ribonucleosides and ribonucleotides
description: Organic compounds in which the C-1 of a ribosyl moiety is N-linked to an imidazole[4,5-c]pyridine ring system. Nucleotides have a phosphate group linked to the C5 carbon of the ribose (or deoxyribose) moiety.

name: Phenyloxadiazoles
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a 1,2,4-oxadiazole ring through a CC or CN bond.

name: Acylaminobenzoic acid and derivatives
description: Derivatives of amino benzoic acid derivatives where the amine group is N-acylated.

name: Purine ribonucleoside phosphonates
description: N-glycosyl compound that possess both a purine nucleobase linked to either a ribose or deoxyribose, which in turn carries a phosphonate group at the 5'-position.

name: Ribonucleoside phosphoramidites
description: Ribonucleoside analogues that consist of a nucleobase (usually purine or pyrimidine), linked to a ribose or deoxyribose, which is protected at the 2',3', or 5'-position by a phosphoramidite group.

name: Pyrazolo[3,4-b]pyrazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazole ring and a pyrazine ring fused to one another without sharing a nitrogen atom.

name: Pyrazolo[1,5-a][1,3,5]triazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazole ring fused to and sharing a nitrogen atom with a 1,3,5-triazine ring.

name: Pyrazolo[1,5-d][1,2,4]triazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazole ring fused to and sharing a nitrogen atom with a 1,2,4-triazine ring.

name: Imidazo[1,2-a]pyrazin-8-ones
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a pyrazine ring. The bicyclic moiety carries an oxo group at the 8-position.

name: Imidazo[1,2-a]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a pyrimidine ring.

name: Imidazo[1,2-a][1,2,4]triazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a 1,2,4-triazine ring. In imidazo[1,2-a][1,2,4]triazines the 1,2,4-triazine ring shares the atom at the 2-position with the imidazole ring.

name: Imidazo[1,2-d][1,2,4]triazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a 1,2,4-triazine ring. In imidazo[1,2-d][1,2,4]triazines the 1,2,4-triazine ring shares the atom at the 4-position with the imidazole ring.

name: Imidazo[2,1-c][1,2,4]triazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a 1,2,4-triazine ring.

name: Pyrazolo[1',5':1,6]pyrimido[4,5-d]pyridazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrimidine fused to both a pyrazole and a pyridazine rings. In this ring system, pyrimidine shares one atom with the pyrazole ring, and no nitrogen atom with the pyrazole ring.

name: Pyrazolo[1',5':1,6]pyrimido[4,5-d]pyridazin-4-ones
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrimidine fused to both a pyrazole and a pyridazine rings. The resulting ring system carries an oxo group at the 4-position. Here, the pyrimidine ring shares one atom with the pyrazole ring, and no nitrogen atom with the pyrazole ring.

name: Pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidine ring system, which consists of a pyrazole ring fused to but and not sharing a nitrogen atom with a pyrimidine ring.

name: Imidazo[1,5-a]pyrazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a pyrazine ring.

name: 2'-Aminoanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an anilide moieties that carries an amino group at the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: Pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidine ring system, which consists of a pyrazole ring fused to and sharing exactly one nitrogen atom with a pyrimidine ring.

name: Pyrrolo[2,3-a]carbazoles
description: A subclass of pyrrolocarbazoles, where the pyrrole ring fused to the carbazole contains a nitrogen atom adjacent to the C2-atom of the carbazole ring.

name: Imidazo[1,2-a]pyridines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to and sharing one nitrogen with a pyridine ring.

name: 5-piperazinylimidazo[1,2-a]pyridines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a piperidine ring that is N-linked to the 5-position of an imidazo[1,2-a]pyridine ring system.

name: 6-piperazinylimidazo[1,2-a]pyridines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a piperidine ring that is N-linked to the 5-position of an imidazo[1,2-a]pyridine ring system.

name: 1,3-thiazolo[5,4-d]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,3-thiazolo[5,4-d]pyrimidine ring system, which consists of a 1,3-thiazole ring fused to but not sharing a nitrogen atom with a pyrimidine ring.

name: 7-oxo-1,3-thiazolo[5,4-d]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,3-thiazolo[5,4-d]pyrimidine ring system that carries an oxo group at the 7-position. 1,3-thiazolo[5,4-d]pyrimidine consists of a 1,3-thiazole ring fused to but not sharing a nitrogen atom with a pyrimidine ring.

name: Haloquinolines
description: Compounds containing a quinoline moiety, which is substituted at one or more ring positions by n halogen atom.

name: Ribonucleoside 3'-phosphates
description: Ribonucleosides that contain a phosphate group attached to the C-3 carbon of the ribose or deoxyribose moiety. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives.

name: Pyridopyrazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a pyridine ring fused to a pyrazine ring.

name: 3-arylsulfonyl-pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds that contain a pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine ring system, which is substituted at the 3-position by an arylsulfonyl group.

name: Furopyridines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a furopyridine ring system, which consists of a furan ring fused to a pyridine ring.

name: Furo[2,3-c]pyridines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a furopyridine ring system, where the O- and the N-atom are at the 1- and 6- position, respectively.

name: Furo[3,2-c]pyridines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a furopyridine ring system, where the O- and the N-atom are at the 1- and 5- position, respectively.

name: Cephalosporin 3'-carbamates
description: Cephalosporins that are substituted at the 3'-position by a carbamate group.

name: Cephalosporin 3'-esters
description: Cephalosporins that are esterified at the 3'-position.

name: 3'-quaternary ammonium cephalosporins
description: Cephalosporins that are substituted at the 3'-position by a quaternary ammonium group.

name: Anthranilamides
description: Aromatic compound containing a benzene carboxamide moiety that carries an amine group at the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: N-benzoylpyrazoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrazole ring that is N-substituted at the 1-position by a benzoyl group.

name: Pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidine ring system, which is an pyrrolopyrimidine isomers having the 3 ring nitrogen atoms at the 1-, 5-, and 7-positions.

name: Furo[2,3-d]pyrimidines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a furo[2,3-d]pyrimidine ring system, which is a furopyrimidine isomer having the on ring oxygen atom, and 2 nitrogen atoms at the 1-, 5-, and 7-positions, respectively.

name: Pyrido[2,3-d]pyrimidines
description: Compounds containing the pyrido[2,3-d]pyrimidine ring system, which is a pyridopyrimidine isomer with three ring nitrogen atoms at the 1-, 3-, and 8- position.

name: Pyrrolo[2,1-f][1,2,4]triazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrolo[2,1-f][1,2,4]triazine ring system. Pyrrolo[2,1-f][1,2,4]triazine consists of a 1,2,4-triazine ring fused to and sharing the N2-atom with a pyrrole ring.

name: Pyrido[3,4-d]pyrimidines
description: Compounds containing the pyrido[3,4-d]pyrimidine ring system, which is a pyridopyrimidine isomer with three ring nitrogen atoms at the 1-, 3-, and 7- position.

name: Pyrrolo[3,2-c]quinolines
description: Aromatic organonitrogen heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrolo[3,2-c]quinoline, a pyrroloquinoline isomer that posseses two ring nitrogen atoms at the 1- and 5-positions.

name: Organic sulfonic acids and derivatives
description: Compounds containing a sulfonic acid or derivative, with the general structure RS(=O)2X (R= H or organyl group, X=any heteroatom).

name: Sulfonic acid esters
description: Esters of sulfonic acid, which have the general structure RS(=O)2OR' (R,R' = organyl group or H).

name: Organic sulfonamides
description: Organic compounds containing the sulfonamide functional group, an amide of sulfonic acid with the general structure R1S(=O)2N(R2)R3 (R1=H or organyl; R2,R3=H, alkyl, aryl).

name: Acrylic acids and derivatives
description: Organic compounds containing acrylic acid CH2=CHCO2H or a derivative thereof.

name: Acrylic acid esters
description: Organic compounds containing and ester acrylic acid (CH2=CHC(=O)OH).

name: Alpha-aminonitriles
description: Organonitrogen compounds that contain an amino group located on the carbon at the position alpha to a carbonitrile group.  They have the general formula RC(NH2)C#N, where the amine group can be substituted.

name: Alpha-hydroxynitriles
description: Organonitrogen compounds that contain a hydroxyl group located on the carbon at the position alpha to a carbonitrile group. They have the general formula RC(OH)C#N.

name: Organic sulfites
description: Organic compounds containing the selenite oxoanion, with the formula  [SO3]2-, or its conjugated base.

name: Triazolines
description: Compounds that contain the triazoline ring, which is a five-membered unsaturated ring having two carbon atoms, three nitrogen atoms and one double bond.

name: Carbides
description: Inorganic compounds containing a carbon atom combined with one or more elements of similar or lower electronegativity.

name: Ketals
description: Acetals derived from ketones by replacement of the oxo group by two hydrocarbyloxy groups R2C(OR)2 ( R not Hydrogen ). This term, once abandoned, has been reinstated as a subclass of acetals.

name: Saturated hydrocarbons
description: Hydrocarbons that contains only saturated carbon atoms, which are linked to one another through single bonds. These includes alkanes and cycloalkanes.

name: Unsaturated hydrocarbons
description: Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms. These compounds contain one or more double, triple, or aromatic bonds.

name: Unsaturated aliphatic hydrocarbons
description: Aliphatic Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms. These compounds contain one or more double or triple bonds.

name: Aromatic hydrocarbons
description: Aromatic compounds that are made up of carbon and hydrogen atoms only.

name: Acetylides
description: Compounds arising by replacement of one or both hydrogen atoms of acetylene (ethyne) by a metal or other cationic group. E.g. NaC#CH monosodium acetylide. By extension, analogous compounds derived from terminal acetylenes, RC#CH. The class is limited here to derivatives of acetylene where the hydrogen atom is replaced with an element with similar or lower electronegativity that carbon.

name: Dialkyl alkylphosphonates
description: Compounds containing a phosphonic acid that is diesterified with alkyl groups, and the phosphorus atom is also directly attached to an alkyl group.

name: Alkylphosphonofluoridic acids and esters
description: Organophosphorus compounds containing a phosphonic acid or an ester derivative thereof, where the phosphorus atom is directly attached to an alkyl group.

name: Trialkylphosphites
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphorous acid, which is tri-esterified with alkyl groups.

name: Cyclohexyl halides
description: Organohalogen compounds containing a monocyclic cyclohexane moiety that is substituted at one or more positions by an halogen atom.

name: O-alkylpyrimidines
description: Compounds containing a pyrimidine , which is O-alkylated at one or more ring positions.

name: 14-hydroxysteroids
description: Steroids carrying a hydroxyl group at the 14-position of the steroid backbone.

name: 2',3'-dideoxy-3'-thionucleosides
description: 2',3'-deoxyribonucleosides, where the ribose unit is thio-substituted at the 3'-position. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives.

name: 5'-deoxyribonucleosides
description: Nucleosides in which the oxygen atom at the 5'position of the ribose moiety has been replaced by another atom. The nucleobases here are limited to purine, pyrimidine, and pyridine derivatives.

name: 5'-deoxy-5'-thionucleosides
description: 5'-deoxyribonucleosides  in which the ribose is thio-substituted at the 5'position by a S-alkyl group.

name: Organic cyanides
description: Organic nitrogen compounds that contain the cyano (C#N) group. The group can be present either in the anionic or covalently bond form.

name: Dinitrophenols
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a benzene that carries a single phenol group and exactly two nitro groups.

name: N-acetylarylamines
description: Acetamides where one or more amide hydrogens is substituted by an aryl group.

name: Phosphiranes
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a phosphirane, which is a three-membered saturated ring made up of two carbon atoms and phosphorus atoms.

name: Alkylhydrazines
description: Organonitrogen compounds that containing a hydrazine group to which an alkyl group is attached.

name: 1,2-diacyl-1-alkylhydrazines
description: Hydrazine derivatives where the hydrazine group is N-acylated at both nitrogen atoms, one of which also carries an alkyl group.

name: N-benzoyl-N'-phenylureas
description: N-acyl-phenylureas that have the acyl group substituted by a phenyl group.

name: Sulfonyl isocyanates
description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfonyl group connected to an isocyanate group.

name: P-toluenesulfonamides
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a toluene that is p-substituted with a sulfonamide group.

name: N,N-disubstituted p-toluenesulfonamides
description: P-toluenesulfonamide derivatives in which the sulfonamide moiety is N,N-disubstituted.

name: Polybrominated dibenzofurans
description: Organic compounds containing two or more bromine atoms attached to a dibenzofuran moiety.

name: Brominated dibenzofurans
description: Organic compounds containing a bromine atom attached to a dibenzofuran moiety.

name: Hydrofluorocarbons
description: Alkyhalide compounds that are composed only of hydrogen, fluorine, and carbon atoms.

name: Triphenyl compounds
description: Aromatic compounds containing a triphenyl moiety.

name: Chlorophenoxyacetates
description: Compounds containing a phenoxyacetate that carries one or more chlorine atoms on the benzene ring.

name: Chloroacetamides
description: Organic compounds with the general formula RNHC(=O)CH2Cl, where R= organyl group.

name: Halotoluenes
description: Aromatic compounds containing a toluene that is substituted at one or more ring positions with a halogen atom.

name: 3-methylindoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds that contain an indole moiety substituted at the 3-position with a methyl group.

name: 2-halopyrimidines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a pyrimidine ring substituted at the 2-position with a halogen atom.

name: 2-halopyridines
description: Organic compounds containing a pyridine ring substituted at the 2-position by a halogen atom.

name: Arylbiguanides
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a biguanide that is N-substituted at one or more position with an aryl moiety.

name: 1-arylbiguanides
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a biguanide that is N-arylsubstituted at only the 1-position.

name: 4-aminoquinolines
description: Organic compounds containing an amino group attached to the 4-position of a quinoline ring system.

name: 4-quinolinemethanols
description: Organoheterocyclic compounds containing a quinoline moiety substituted at the 4-position with a methanol.

name: N-methylpyridinium compounds
description: Methylpyridines that carry a methyl group at the 1-position.

name: Arylhydroxamates
description: Aromatic compounds containing an hydroxamate group attached to an aromatic moiety.

name: 5'-acylphosphoadenosines
description: Ribonucleoside derivatives containing an adenoside moiety, where the phosphate group is acylated.

name: Trifluoromethylbenzenes
description: Organofluorine compounds that contain a benzene ring substituted with one or more trifluoromethyl groups.

name: Indazole-3-carboxamides
description: Aromatic compounds containing an indazole ring system that is substituted at the 3-position with a carboxamide group.

name: L-cysteine-S-conjugates
description: Compounds containing L-cysteine where the thio-group is conjugated.

name: Organopnictogen compounds
description: Compounds containing a bond between carbon a pnictogen atom. Pnictogens are p-block element atoms that are in the group 15 of the periodic table.

name: N-cinnamoylanthranilic acids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a cinnamic acid conjugated to an anthranilic acid.

name: Haloacetylenes and derivatives
description: Organohalogen compounds containing an acetylene group substituted with one or more halogen atoms.

name: Alkylboranes
description: Organoboron compounds where the boron atom is substituted by one or more alkyl groups.

name: Alkylhaloboranes
description: Organoboron compounds with the general formula RBX2 or R2BX (R=alkyl, X=halogen).

name: Alkylhalophosphines
description: Organophosphorus compounds with the general formula RPX2 or R2PX (R=alkyl, X=halogen).

name: Monoalkylboranes
description: Organoboron compounds where the boron atom is substituted by only one alkyl group.

name: Dialkylboranes
description: Organoboron compounds where the boron atom is substituted by only two alkyl groups.

name: Trialkylboranes
description: Organoboron compounds where the boron atom is substituted by only three alkyl groups.

name: Acylsalicylic acids and derivatives
description: Salicylic acids or derivatives, that are O-acylated.

name: Acylsalicylic acids
description: O-acylated derivatives of salicylic acid.

name: Acylsalicylamides
description: O-acylated derivatives of salicylamide.

name: Diacyl peroxides
description: Organooxygen compounds containing a peroxide disubstituted with acyl groups.

name: Trifluoromethanesulfonates
description: Alkanesulfonic acids, that contain a sulfonate group that is substituted with a trifluoromethyl group.

name: Alkyl hydroperoxides
description: Organooxygen compounds containing a hydroperoxide group substituted with an alkyl group. They have the general formula ROOH, where R is the alkyl group.

name: Allylic hydroperoxides
description: Organooxygen compounds containing a hydroperoxide group substituted with an allyl group. They have the general formula RCH=CR'CH2OSO2CF3.

name: Diazoethers
description: Organooxygen compounds with the general formula RN=NOR' (R=H or organyl, R'=organyl).

name: Arenediazoates
description: Diazoethers which are N-substituted with an aryl group through a CN bond.

name: Organic oxygen compounds
description: Organic compounds that contain one or more oxygen atoms.

name: Fluorodinitromethyl compounds
description: C-nitro compounds with the general structure F(O2N)2C-R.

name: Nitroaromatic compounds
description: C-nitro compounds where the nitro group is C-substituted with an aromatic group.

name: Nitrobenzaldehydes
description: Nitrobenzenes that carry an aldehyde group at any position of the benzene ring.

name: Aryl phosphates
description: Organophosphorus compounds having a phosphate group substituted by one or more aryl groups.

name: Aryl phosphomonoesters
description: Aryl phosphates in which the phosphate is monosubstituted.

name: Aryl phosphodiesters
description: Aryl phosphates in which the phosphate is esterified at exactly two positions.

name: Aryl phosphotriesters
description: Aryl phosphates in which the phosphate is esterified at exactly three positions.

name: Branched alkanes
description: Acyclic branched hydrocarbons having the general formula CnH2n+2.

name: Branched unsaturated hydrocarbons
description: Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms, and an aliphatic branch.

name: Aryl thiophosphates
description: Organic compounds containing the thiophosphoric acid functional group or a derivative thereof, with the general structure ROP(OR')(OR'')=S, where at least one R-group is an aryl group.

name: Pyridine-2-carboxylic acids
description: Compounds containing a pyridine ring bearing a carboxylic acid group at the 2-position.

name: 5-alkoxy-2-carboxypyrimidines
description: Pyrimidine-2-carboxylic acids that carry an alkoxy substituent at the 5-position of the  pyridine ring.

name: 5-alkyl-2-carboxypyrimidines
description: Pyrimidine-2-carboxylic acids that carry an alkyl group at the 5-position of the  pyridine ring.

name: 4-alkoxyphenols
description: Phenols that carry an alkoxy group at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: Benzyl sulfoxides
description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfoxide group substituted by a benzyl group. They have the general structure RS(=O)R' ( R=benzyl, R'=organyl).

name: Benzyl alkyl sulfoxides
description: Organosulfur compounds that contain a sulfoxide group substituted by a benzyl group, and an alkyl group. They have the general structure RS(=O)R' ( R=benzyl, R'=alkyl).

name: Aryl thioethers
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a thioether group that is substituted by an aryl group.

name: Phenyl sulfoxides
description: Organosulfur compounds containing a sulfoxide group substituted with a phenyl group.

name: Dibenzothiophene-5,5-dioxides
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a dibenzothiophene disubstituted at the 5-position with two dioxide groups.

name: Alkyl-2-thio-S-triazines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring that is substituted at the 2-position with a S-alkyl group.

name: Alkoxy-S-triazines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring that is substituted at the 2-position with an alkoxy group.

name: Halo-S-triazines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring that is substituted at the 2-position with a halogen atom.

name: Phenyl methylcarbamates
description: Aromatic compounds containing a methylcarbamic acid esterified with a phenyl group.

name: Alkylarsine oxides
description: Hydrocarbyl derivatives of H3As=O, where the Arsenic atom is linked to one or more alkyl groups.

name: 2(hydroxyphenyl)acetic acids
description: Phenylacetic acids that carry a hydroxyl group at the 2-position.

name: 1-hydroxy-2-unsubstituted benzenoids
description: Phenols that a unsubstituted at the 2-position.

name: 1-hydroxy-4-unsubstituted benzenoids
description: Phenols that are unsubstituted at the 4-position.

name: 1-hydroxylamino, 2-unsubstituted benzenoids
description: Benzenoids in which the benzene moiety is N-linked to an hydroxylamine at the 1-position, and unsubstituted at the 2-position.

name: 1-hydroxylamino, 4-unsubstituted benzenoids
description: Benzenoids in which the benzene moiety is N-linked to an hydroxylamine at the 1-position, and unsubstituted at the 4-position.

name: N-phenylhydroxylamines
description: Hydroxylamines that are N-substituted with a phenyl group.

name: O-phenylhydroxylamines
description: Hydroxylamines that are O-substituted with a phenyl group.

name: N-alkyl-O-phenylhydroxylamines
description: Hydroxylamines that are O-substituted with a phenyl group, and N-substituted by an alkyl group.

name: N-aryl-N-phenylhydroxylamines
description: Hydroxylamines that are N,N-disubstituted by a phenyl and another aryl group.

name: o-Aminophenols
description: Phenols that are substituted with an amine group at the 2-position of the benzene ring.

name: m-Aminophenols
description: Phenols that are substituted with an amine group at the 3-position of the benzene ring.

name: p-Aminophenols
description: Phenols that are substituted with an amine group at the 4-position of the benzene ring.

name: 5-unsubstituted pyrrogallols
description: Pyrrogallols that are unsubstituted at th5-position of the benzene ring.

name: Benzo-1,2,3-triazines
description: Organic compounds containing a 1,2,3-triazine ring fused to a benzene ring.

name: Phosphorodithioic acid O-monoesters
description: Organooxygen compounds that contain a phosphorodithioic acid, which is O-monosubstituted by an organyl group.

name: Phosphorodithioic acid O,O-diesters
description: Organooxygen compounds that contain a phosphorodithioic acid, which is O,O-disubstituted by an organyl group.

name: Nitroguanidines
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing a nitro group, which is N-linked to a guanidine.

name: 1,3,4-thiadiazol-2-ylureas
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,4-thiadiazole ring, which is substituted at the 2-position with urea.

name: Pyrimidinyloxybenzylamines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a diarylether group substituted with a 3-phenylmethanamine and a pyrimidine.

name: Aminophenyl ethers
description: Aromatic compounds that contain a phenol ether, which carries an amine group on the benzene ring.

name: Nitrophenyl ethers
description: Aromatic compounds containing a nitrobenzene moiety that carries an ether group on the benzene ring.

name: Benzoylcyclohexane-1,3-diones
description: Alkyl-phenylketones where the alkyl group is a cyclohexane 1,3-dione.

name: Aryloxyphenoxypropionic acids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a phenoxypropionic acid that is para-substituted with an aryl group.

name: 2-phenoxypropionic acids
description: Aromatic compounds hat contain a phenol ether attached to the C2-atom of a phenylpropionic acid.

name: 2-phenoxypropionic acid esters
description: Aromatic compounds hat contain a phenol ether attached to the C2-atom of a phenylpropionic acid ester.

name: 1,2,4-triazolopyrimidine-2-sulfonamides
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine ring system, which is substituted with a sulfonamide at the 2-position.

name: 1,2,4-triazolopyrimidine-2-sulfonanilides
description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine ring system, which is substituted with a sulfonanilide at the 2-position.

name: Aryl 1,2,4-triazolones
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazolone moiety that is substituted at the 5-position with an aryl group.

name: Diacylhydrazines
description: Carboxylic acid hydrazides with the formula RC(=O)NNC(R')=O ( R,R'=H or organyl group).

name: Naphthalene-1-carboxanilides
description: Naphthalene-1-carboxamides, where the carboxamide group is substituted with an aniline.

name: Naphthalene-2-carboxanilides
description: Naphthalene-2-carboxamides, where the carboxamide group is substituted with an aniline.

name: 1-hydroxynaphthalene-2-carboxanilides
description: Naphthalene-2-carboxamides, where the carboxamide group is substituted with an aniline, and the naphthalene ring system is hydroxylated at the ring 1-position.

name: 1-benzothiophene-2-carboxanilides
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds that contain a 1-benzothiophene ring system, which is substituted with an anilide at the 2-position.

name: 1,4-dihydroxy-2-halobenzenoids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,-2-dihydroxybenzene moiety, which carries an halogen atom at the ring 2-position.

name: Phenyl phosphates
description: Aromatic organooxygen compounds containing a phosphate group, which is O-esterified with a phenyl group.

name: m-Hydroxybenzoic acid esters
description: Benzoic acid esters where the benzene ring is meta-substituted with a hydroxy group.

name: o-Hydroxybenzoic acid esters
description: Benzoic acid esters where the benzene ring is ortho-substituted with a hydroxy group.

name: p-Hydroxybenzoic acid esters
description: Benzoic acid esters where the benzene ring is para-substituted with a hydroxy group.

name: p-Hydroxybenzoic acid alkyl esters
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzoic acid, which is esterified with an alkyl group and para-substituted with a hydroxyl group.

name: Benzoylpyrazoles
description: Aromatic compounds containing a benzoyl group substituted with a pyrazole ring.

name: Pyrimidinyl-2-sulfonylureas
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrimidine ring which is substituted with a sulfonylurea at the ring 2-position.

name: S-triazinyl-2-sulfonylureas
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a s-triazine ring which is substituted with a urea at the ring 2-position.

name: Organic nitrogen compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a nitrogen atom.

name: 2-pyridylmethylamines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds contaning a pyridine ring which is substituted at the 2-position with a methylamine.

name: 6-substituted-2-pyridinylmethylamines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds contaning a pyridine ring which is substituted at the 2-position with a methylamine, and at the 6-position with any non-hydrogen atom.

name: 2-benzimidazolylcarbamic acids
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds that contain a carbamyl group N-linked to the C2-atom of a benzimidazole moiety.

name: 2-benzimidazolylcarbamic acid esters
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds that contain a carbamic acid ester group, which is N-linked to the C2-atom of a benzimidazole moiety.

name: Aromatic anilides
description: Aromatic compounds containing an anilide group in which the carboxamide group is substituted with an aromatic group. They have the general structure RNC(=O)R', where R= benzene, and R = aryl group.

name: Benzanilides
description: Aromatic compounds containing an anilide group in which the carboxamide group is substituted with a benzene ring. They have the general structure RNC(=O)R', where R,R'= benzene.

name: Phenylcarbamic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of phenylcarbamic acids.

name: Hydrazinecarboxylic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of hydrazinecarboxylic acids.

name: Haloacetanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetamide group conjugated to a phenyl group, which is in turn substituted with one or more halogen atoms.

name: M-haloacetanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetamide group conjugated to a phenyl group, which is in turn meta-substituted with a halogen atom.

name: O-haloacetanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetamide group conjugated to a phenyl group, which is in turn ortho-substituted with a halogen atom.

name: P-haloacetanilides
description: Organic compounds containing an acetamide group conjugated to a phenyl group, which is in turn para-substituted with a halogen atom.

name: N-acylcarbazoles
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a carbazole moiety, which is N-acylated.

name: Chloro-s-triazines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring that is substituted at the 2-position with a chlorine atom.

name: Cyclic dithiocarbamic acid esters
description: Organosulfur cyclic compounds with the general formula R3SC(=S)N(R1)R2; R1-R2 =  H or organyl group, R3 = organyl. Here, the dithiocarbamyl group is part of a ring.

name: Cyclopropylisoxazoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazole ring substituted at one or more positions with a cyclopropyl group.

name: 3-cyclopropylisoxazoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazole ring substituted at the ring 3-position with a cyclopropyl group.

name: 5-cyclopropylisoxazoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing an isoxazole ring substituted at the ring 5-position with a cyclopropyl group.

name: Formamidines
description: Amidines with the general structure Amidines with the general structure RN=CHN(R')R\", where R, R',and R\" are any atoms not part of an amide or a thioamide group.

name: 2-methoxy-1,3,5-triazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring, which is substituted at the 2-position with a methoxy group.

name: 2-benzylamino-s-triazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a S-triazine ring, which is N-substituted at the 2-position with a benzylamine.

name: 1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring which is 2,4-disusbtituted wit amine groups.

name: Methylthio-s-triazines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 1,3,5-triazine ring that is substituted at the 2-position with a methylthio group.

name: Oxadiazines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containing an oxadiazine ring, which is an unsaturated six-membered heterocycle that consists of one oxygen 2 nitrogen, and 3 carbon atoms.

name: 1,3,5-oxadiazines
description: Heterocyclic compounds containig an oxadiazine ring with one oxygen atom at the 1-position, and two nitrogen atoms at the 3-, and 5-position, respectively.

name: Phenoxy compounds
description: Aromatic compounds contaning a phenoxy group.

name: 3-phenoxypropionic acids
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 3-phenoxypropionic acid.

name: Phenylenediamines
description: Aromatic compound containing a benzene ring which carries 2 amino groups.

name: M-phenylenediamines
description: Aromatic compound containing a benzene ring which carries 2 amino groups, at the 1- and 3-positions.

name: P-phenylenediamines
description: Aromatic compound containing a benzene ring which carries 2 amino groups, at the 1- and 4-positions.

name: Phenyl thiophosphates
description: Organothiophosphorus compounds that contain a thiophosphoric acid O-esterified with a phenyl group.

name: Phthalimides
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,3-dioxoisoindoline moiety. They are imide derivatives of phthalic anhydrides.

name: Oxime carbamates
description: Oxime ether derivatives with the general formula CC(R)=NOC(=O)N(R')R\", where R-R\" = H or organyl.

name: Furanilides
description: Aromatic anilides with the general structure RC(=O)N(R')R\", where R=furan, and R\"=benzene.

name: 2-furanilides
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds contaning a furan ring that is substituted at the 2-position with an anilide.

name: 3-furanilides
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds contaning a furan ring that is substituted at the 3-position with an anilide.

name: Furoic acid and derivatives
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a furan ring, which carries a carboxyl group or a derivative thereof.

name: Furan-3-carboxylic acid and derivatives
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a furan ring, which carries a carboxyl group or a derivative thereof at the ring 3-position.

name: Furan-3-carboxylic acids
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a furan ring, which carries a carboxyl group at the ring 3-position.

name: Furan-3-carboxylic acid esters
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a furan ring, which carries a carboxylic ester at the ring 3-position.

name: Precocenes
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds that contain a 2,2-dimethyl-1-benzopyran moiety, which carries a methoxy group at the ring 7-position.

name: Phenylphosphonothioates
description: Aromatic compound contaning a phosphonothioate, which is C-substituted with a phenyl group.

name: Cyanoacrylates
description: Organonitrogen compounds containing an acrylic acid ester, which carries a nitrile group. They have the general structure ROC(=O)C(=C)C#N, where R is an organic group.

name: 3-methoxychromones
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a chromone ring system, which carries a methoxy group at the 3-position.

name: Chromeno[2,3-b]pyridines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing pyridine linearly fused to the pyran moiety of a benzofuran ring system.

name: Chromeno[2,3-b]pyridine-5-ones
description: Compounds containing a Chromeno[2,3-b]pyridine moiety that carries an oxo group at the 5-position.

name: Organic nitroso compounds
description: Organic compounds having the nitroso group, -NO, attached to carbon, or to another element, most commonly nitrogen or oxygen.

name: Organic N-nitroso compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a n-nitroso group -NN=O.

name: Organic O-nitroso compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a n-nitroso group -ON=O.

name: Organic S-nitroso compounds
description: Organic compounds containing a n-nitroso group -SN=O.

name: Acyl phosphates
description: Organic compounds containing a phosphate linked to an acyl group. They have the general structure  R-CO-P(O)(O)O, R=H or organyl.

name: Trialkylglycerols
description: Triradylglycerols that carry three chains attached to the glycerol moiety through ether linkages.

name: Sulfonated stilbenes
description: Stilbenes that carry a sulfone group at one or more positions of either benzene rings.

name: N-acylimidazoles
description: Compounds containing an imidazole ring, which is N-substituted by an acyl group.

name: Methylcarbamates
description: Methyl esters of carbamic acid.

name: Diazanaphthalenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic chemical compounds containing a naphthalene derivative, where two carbon atoms are replaced by nitrogen atoms. They are subdivided in benzodiazines and naphthyridines.

name: Benzodiazines
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a benzene ring fused to a diazine ring. The diazine ring is an analogue of benzene, where two carbon atoms are replaced by nitrogen atoms.

name: Furanonaphthodioxoles
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a 1,3-dioxole ring linearly fused to the a naphthofuran.

name: Chloronaphthalenes
description: Aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a naphthalene moiety substituted at one or more positions by a chlorine atom.

name: Phenylisopropylamines
description: Organic aromatic compounds containing a 1-phenylpropan-2-amine moiety.

name: 1,3-oxazolobenzo-1,4-diazepines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,3-oxazole ring fused to the 1,-4-diazepine moiety of a 1,4-benzodiazepine ring system.

name: 2',5'-dideoxyribonucleosides
description: Nucleosides characterized by a purine or pyrimidine base, which is N-linked to a 2',5'-dideoxyribose moiety.

name: 2-benzylaminopyridines
description: Aromatic compounds containing pyridine ring substituted at the 2-position by a benzylamine group.

name: Furoic acid esters
description: Ester derivatives of furoic acid.

name: Alpha-haloketones
description: Organic compounds contaning a halogen atom attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group.

name: Alpha-chloroketones
description: Organic compounds contaning a chlorine atom attached to the alpha carbon atom relative to C=O group.

name: Acenaphthylenes
description: Aromatic polycyclic compounds containing an acenaphthylene moiety. Acenaphthylene is a carbotricyclic compound, consisting of a naphthalene with positions C1 and C8 connected by an ethylene bridge.

name: Ecdysteroids
description: Polyhydroxylated oxosteroids possessing a cyclopentano-perhydro-phenantrene with beta side-chain at C-17, which is the product of terpene biosynthesis through mevalonic acid, cholesterol and related sterols. Ecdysteroids are found in certain plants and animals.

name: Fluoromethoxy benzamides
description: Organic compounds containing a benzamide, which is substituted by a fluoromethoxy group.

name: N'-substituted-N,N'-diacylhydrazines
description: Hydrazine derivatives where the hydrazine group is N-acylated at both nitrogen atoms, only one of which is substituted.

name: 2-heteroaryl carboxamides
description: Compounds containing a heteroaromatic ring that carries a carboxamide group.

name: B-type proanthocyanidins
description: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of two or more flavonoid units linked to each other only by either one 4->6, one 4->8, or one 8->8 CC-bond.

name: 4-hydroxy-6,7-benzomorphans
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 6,7-benzomorphan skeleton, which is hydroxylated at the ring 4-position.

name: 2,6-dimethyl-3-benzazocines
description: Aromatic compounds containing a 6,7-benzomorphan skeleton, which is substituted by methyl group at the 2- and 6-positions.

name: Pyridinolates
description: Aromatic compounds similar to phenoxide, with the difference that one carbo atom of the benzene ring is replaced by a nitrogen compound.

name: 1,2,4-triazolo[3,4-a]phthalazines
description: Aromatic heteropolycyclic compounds containing a 1,2,4-triazole fused to and sharing a nitrogen atom with the diazine ring of a phthalazine moiety.

name: A-type proanthocyanidins
description: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of two or more flavonoid units linked to each other by both a 2->7 and a 4->b (or 4->8) interflavonoid CC-bonds.

name: C-type proanthocyanidins
description: Proanthocyanidins, which are characterized by the presence of three or more flavonoid units linked to each other by exactly 4->8 interflavonoid CC-bonds.

name: Dipeptides
description: Organic compounds containing a sequence of exactly two alpha-amino acids joined by a peptide bond.

name: Oligopeptides
description: Organic compounds containing a sequence of between three and ten alpha-amino acids joined by peptide bonds.

name: Chemical entities
description: Constitutionally or isotopically distinct atoms, molecules, ions, ion pairs, radicals, radical ions, complexes, conformers etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.
